                2 => [
                    'id' => 3,
                    'doc_category_id' => 1,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-your-business-information-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up Your Business Information in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide shows you how to set up and change your business details in Menumium. It covers contact information, location, branding, and customer support.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-business-information-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Business Information Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Business Information</strong> in the left-hand navigation panel.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-info-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Business Info Navigation" class="wp-image-11041" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-info-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-info-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-info-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-info-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-info-navigation-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-fill-out-business-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Fill Out Business Details</h2><p>On the <strong>Setup Business Information</strong> page, complete the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Restaurant Name</strong> – Enter the official name of your business.</li><li><strong>Contact Phone Number</strong> – Provide a valid business contact number.</li><li><strong>Currency</strong> – Select the currency used for pricing.</li><li><strong>Country, State, City, Time Zone</strong> – Choose your geographical location and time zone.</li><li><strong>Email</strong> – Enter a business email address.</li><li><strong>Business Address</strong> – Provide the full address of your business.</li><li><strong>Language</strong> – Select the primary language for your menu.</li><li><strong>Zip Code</strong> – Enter the postal code of your business location.</li><li><strong>Street</strong> – Add the street name and number.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-business-info-1024x582.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-9011" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-business-info-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-business-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-business-info-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-business-info-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-business-info.webp 1900w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-set-the-business-location-on-the-map" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Set the Business Location on the Map</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the <strong>Map</strong> section below the business address fields.</li><li>Use the <strong>search bar</strong> to find your exact location.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-business-location-1024x579.webp" alt="Business Location" class="wp-image-9012" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-business-location-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-business-location-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-business-location-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-business-location-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-business-location.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-add-business-logos-and-icons" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Add Business Logos and Icons</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Scroll to the <strong>Add Restaurant Logo</strong> and <strong>Add Business Icon</strong> sections.</li><li>Click <strong>Browse</strong> to upload your restaurant logo.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Max size: 2 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: <strong>4:1</strong></li></ul></li><li>Upload your <strong>Business Icon</strong> in the same supported formats.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-business-logo-and-icon-1024x582.webp" alt="Business Logo and Icon" class="wp-image-9013" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-business-logo-and-icon-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-business-logo-and-icon-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-business-logo-and-icon-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-business-logo-and-icon-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-business-logo-and-icon.webp 1900w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5add-business-contact-info-and-configure-customer-support-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5:Add Business Contact Info and Configure Customer Support Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the Business Contact Info section.</li><li>You can choose Same as Business Details or enter details manually:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Contact Person Name</li><li>Contact Phone Number</li><li>Contact Email</li></ul></li><li>Contact Person Name</li><li>Contact Phone Number</li><li>Contact Email</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-business-contact-info-1024x580.webp" alt="Business Contact Info" class="wp-image-9014" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-business-contact-info-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-business-contact-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-business-contact-info-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-business-contact-info-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-business-contact-info.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the <strong>Customer Support Information</strong> section.</li><li>Toggle ON to enable custom support details for your <strong>Website </strong>or <strong>POS.</strong></li><li>Choose a <strong>Support Number Type</strong>:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Phone Number</li><li>Telephone</li><li>Hotline</li></ul></li><li>Enter the support number and email address.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-contact-support-information-1024x579.webp" alt="Contact Support Information" class="wp-image-9017" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-contact-support-information-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-contact-support-information-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-contact-support-information-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-contact-support-information-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-contact-support-information.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save Your Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all fields are complete, click <strong>Save</strong> (top-right corner).</li></ul><p>A success message will appear: <em>“Business information was updated successfully.”</em></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:51.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:51.000000Z',
                ],
                3 => [
                    'id' => 4,
                    'doc_category_id' => 1,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-log-in-for-existing-users',
                    'title' => 'How to Log In for Existing Users',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Already have a Menumium account? Logging in is quick and simple.</p><h2 id="step-1-go-to-the-login-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Go to the Login Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Open your browser and navigate to:<a href="https://portal.menumium.com/auth/sign-in"> https://portal.menumium.com/auth/sign-in</a></li></ul><h2 id="step-2-enter-login-credentials" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enter Login Credentials</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Type your <strong>registered email</strong>.</li><li>Enter your <strong>password</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-using-email-and-pass-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Login Using Email &amp; Pass" class="wp-image-11996" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-using-email-and-pass-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-using-email-and-pass-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-using-email-and-pass-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-using-email-and-pass-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-using-email-and-pass-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-click-login" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Click Login</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Login</strong> button to access your account.</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-alternative-login-option" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Alternative Login Option</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>For faster access, click <strong>Continue with Gmail</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-continue-with-google-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Login Continue With Google" class="wp-image-11998" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-continue-with-google-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-continue-with-google-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-continue-with-google-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-continue-with-google-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-continue-with-google-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-use-remember-me-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Use “Remember Me” (Optional)</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Check the <strong>Remember Me</strong> box if you want the system to save your credentials.</li><li>This way, you won’t need to enter your password each time you log in.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-remember-me-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Login Remember Me" class="wp-image-11999" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-remember-me-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-remember-me-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-remember-me-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-remember-me-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/login-remember-me-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You are now logged in and ready to use your Menumium account.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:51.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:51.000000Z',
                ],
                4 => [
                    'id' => 5,
                    'doc_category_id' => 1,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-reset-your-password',
                    'title' => 'How to Reset Your Password',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>If you’ve forgotten your Menumium password, you can easily reset it by following these steps:</p><h2 id="step-1-go-to-the-login-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Go to the Login Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Open your browser and navigate to:<a href="https://portal.menumium.com/auth/sign-in"> https://portal.menumium.com/auth/sign-in</a></li></ul><h2 id="step-2-click-forgot-password" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Click “Forgot Password”</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the login screen, click the <strong>Forgot Password</strong> link.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/forget-password-link-marked-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Forget Password Link Marked" class="wp-image-12002" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/forget-password-link-marked-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/forget-password-link-marked-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/forget-password-link-marked-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/forget-password-link-marked-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/forget-password-link-marked-0a.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter your <strong>registered email address</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="729" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-your-password.webp" alt="Reset Your Password" class="wp-image-9984" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-your-password.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-your-password-300x214.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-your-password-768x547.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-verify-with-otp" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Verify with OTP</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Check your email inbox for a <strong>One-Time Password (OTP)</strong>.</li><li>Enter the OTP in the provided field before it expires.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="716" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-password-enter-otp-1024x716.webp" alt="Reset Password - Enter OTP" class="wp-image-11020" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-password-enter-otp-1024x716.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-password-enter-otp-300x210.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-password-enter-otp-768x537.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reset-password-enter-otp.webp 1335w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-set-a-new-password" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Set a New Password</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Type your <strong>new password</strong> and confirm it.</li><li>Click the <strong>Save</strong> button to finalize the reset.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="723" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-a-new-password.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-9991" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-a-new-password.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-a-new-password-300x212.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-a-new-password-768x542.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You can now log in securely with your updated credentials.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:52.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:52.000000Z',
                ],
                5 => [
                    'id' => 6,
                    'doc_category_id' => 1,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-sign-in-as-an-employee',
                    'title' => 'How to Sign In as an Employee',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Employees who have already been invited by the Admin (Tenant) can log in to Menumium with their credentials.</p><h2 id="step-1-go-to-the-login-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Go to the Login Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Open your browser and navigate to the Menumium login page:<br><a href="https://portal.menumium.com/auth/sign-in">https://portal.menumium.com/auth/sign-in</a></li></ul><h2 id="step-2-select-employee-account-type" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select Employee Account Type</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the login screen, choose <strong>Employee</strong> as your account type.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-employee-account-type.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-9994" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-employee-account-type.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-employee-account-type-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-employee-account-type-768x433.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-enter-login-credentials" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Enter Login Credentials</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter your <strong>username</strong> and <strong>password</strong> as set during registration.</li><li>Click <strong>Login</strong> to access your account.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/build-business.webp" alt="Build Business" class="wp-image-9999" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/build-business.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/build-business-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/build-business-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>Employees cannot register independently. They must be invited by the Admin (Tenant) to receive login access. For details, see the <strong><a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/employee-management/how-to-invite-an-employee-for-a-role-in-menumium/">Employee Management</a></strong> documentation.</p></div></div><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:53.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:53.000000Z',
                ],
                6 => [
                    'id' => 7,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-a-new-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Create a New Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to create a new branch from your Menumium dashboard, fill out branch details, and assign a menu to the branch for independent management.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Branch Setup</strong> from the dropdown menu.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-create-a-new-branch" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Create a New Branch</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Branch Setup page, you’ll see a list of existing branches.</li><li>Click <strong>Create Branch</strong> (top-right corner).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-branch-1024x576.webp" alt="Create New Branch" class="wp-image-9724" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-branch-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-branch-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-branch-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-branch-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-branch.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-out-branch-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill Out Branch Information</h2><p>A form will appear. Complete the required details:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Branch Name</strong> – Enter the name of the new location.</li><li><strong>Contact Person Name</strong> – Provide the branch manager or primary contact’s name.</li><li><strong>Designation</strong> – Enter the contact person’s title (e.g., Manager).</li><li><strong>Contact Person Phone Number</strong> – Add their phone number.</li><li><strong>Contact Person Email</strong> – Add their email address.</li><li><strong>Availability Status</strong> – Toggle ON to activate the branch (ready to accept orders).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-branch-information-1024x580.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-8210" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-branch-information-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-branch-information-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-branch-information-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-branch-information-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-branch-information.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Once done, click <strong>Create</strong>.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation message will appear: <em>“The branch was created successfully.”</em></li></ul><h2 id="step-4-assign-a-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Assign a Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the new branch in your Branch List.</li><li>On the right-hand side of the branch row, you’ll see a few action buttons.</li><li>Click the <strong>Assign Menu</strong> button (located next to the <strong>three-dot menu</strong>).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-1024x576.webp" alt="Assign Menu Icon" class="wp-image-9738" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the pop-up, choose the menu for this branch and click <strong>Save</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear: <em>“Branch updated in the menu successfully!”</em></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-1024x577.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-8211" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch.webp 1914w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You have now successfully created a new branch and assigned a menu to it. This branch can now be managed independently within your Menumium account.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:54.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:54.000000Z',
                ],
                7 => [
                    'id' => 8,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-delivery-areas-and-charges',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up Delivery Areas and Charges',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will explain how to configure your delivery fees and available delivery areas. Menumium offers three flexible methods to manage your delivery charges. You can use one or a combination of them to create a delivery fee structure that perfectly matches your business needs.</p><h2 id="1-accessing-delivery-area-setup" class="wp-block-heading">1. Accessing Delivery Area Setup</h2><p>First, navigate to the section where you can manage your delivery settings.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium portal.</li><li>From the side navigation menu, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>Restaurant Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Delivery Area Setup</strong>.</li></ul><p>On this page, you will find three distinct methods for setting up your delivery charges. You can activate the ones that best suit your operational model.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accessing-delivery-area-setup0A-1024x580.webp" alt="Accessing Delivery Area Setup" class="wp-image-10654" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accessing-delivery-area-setup0A-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accessing-delivery-area-setup0A-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accessing-delivery-area-setup0A-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accessing-delivery-area-setup0A-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/accessing-delivery-area-setup0A.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="method-1-kilometer-wise-delivery-charge" class="wp-block-heading">Method 1: Kilometer-Wise Delivery Charge</h2><p>This method allows you to charge a fee based on the distance from your restaurant to the customer’s location. It’s ideal for a straightforward, distance-based pricing model.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the toggle switch to enable the <strong>Setup Kilometer Wise Delivery Charge</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-km-wise-charge-toggle-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Setup KM Wise Charge Toggle" class="wp-image-10979" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-km-wise-charge-toggle-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-km-wise-charge-toggle-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-km-wise-charge-toggle-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-km-wise-charge-toggle-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-km-wise-charge-toggle-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The configuration panel will appear.</li><li>In the <strong>Charge ($)</strong> field, enter the amount you want to charge per kilometer.</li><li>In the <strong>Set Radius (km)</strong> field, enter the maximum distance you are willing to deliver from your restaurant. The map will automatically display a circle representing your total delivery coverage area.</li><li>Click the <strong>Save</strong> button to apply the settings.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-set-delivery-charge-per-kilometer-1024x581.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-8243" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-set-delivery-charge-per-kilometer-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-set-delivery-charge-per-kilometer-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-set-delivery-charge-per-kilometer-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-set-delivery-charge-per-kilometer-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-set-delivery-charge-per-kilometer.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="method-2-area-zip-code-charges" class="wp-block-heading">Method 2: Area/Zip Code &amp; Charges</h2><p>Use this method to set fixed, flat-rate delivery fees for specific areas, cities, or postal codes. This is useful when you have standard charges for different neighborhoods.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the toggle switch to enable <strong>Setup Area/Zip Code &amp; Charges</strong>.</li><li>Click the <strong>+ Add New</strong> button to define a new area.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-toggle-navigation-1024x581.webp" alt="Area Wise Charge Toggle Navigation" class="wp-image-10657" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-toggle-navigation-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-toggle-navigation-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-toggle-navigation-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-toggle-navigation-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-toggle-navigation.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window will appear.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Area</strong> field, enter the name of the area or the specific Zip/Postal Code (e.g., “10001”).</li><li>In the <strong>Delivery Charge $</strong> field, enter the flat delivery fee for that area.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-setup-1024x580.webp" alt="Area Wise Charge Setup" class="wp-image-10660" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-setup-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-setup-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-setup-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-setup-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-setup.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>4. Click <strong>Save</strong>.</p><p>5. The new area and its corresponding charge will be added to your list. You can repeat this process to add as many different areas or zip codes as you need.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-area-or-zip-wise-charge-1024x579.webp" alt="Set Area Or Zip Wise Charge" class="wp-image-10662" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-area-or-zip-wise-charge-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-area-or-zip-wise-charge-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-area-or-zip-wise-charge-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-area-or-zip-wise-charge-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-area-or-zip-wise-charge.webp 1908w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="method-3-delivery-zones-charges" class="wp-block-heading">Method 3: Delivery Zones &amp; Charges</h2><p>This powerful option lets you create custom-drawn delivery zones on a map, each with its own flat-rate delivery charge. This provides the most control for defining precise service areas.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the toggle switch to enable <strong>Setup Delivery Zones &amp; Charges</strong>.</li><li>Click the <strong>+ Add New</strong> button.</li><li>In the “Create Zone” panel, fill in the <strong>Zone Name</strong> (e.g., “Downtown Zone”) and the <strong>Delivery Charge ($)</strong> for orders within this zone.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/zone-wise-charge-toggle-and-add-new-1024x581.webp" alt="Zone Wise Charge Toggle And Add New" class="wp-image-10664" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/zone-wise-charge-toggle-and-add-new-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/zone-wise-charge-toggle-and-add-new-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/zone-wise-charge-toggle-and-add-new-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/zone-wise-charge-toggle-and-add-new-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/zone-wise-charge-toggle-and-add-new.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Next, choose your <strong>Zone Selection Type</strong> to define the boundary:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Option A: Circle</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the “Circle” radio button.</li><li>Enter a value in the <strong>Set Radius (km)</strong> field. The map will display a circular delivery zone around your restaurant’s location. This is a quick way to define a general service area.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-A-circle--1024x582.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-8246" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-A-circle--1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-A-circle--300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-A-circle--768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-A-circle--1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-A-circle-.webp 1900w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Option B: Custom Shape</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the “Custom Shape” radio button.</li><li>On the interactive map, click to place points and draw a custom polygon. This allows you to create a precise boundary that follows specific streets or neighborhoods.</li></ul></li></ul><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After defining your zone on the map, click the <strong>Create</strong> button to save it.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-B-custom-shape--1024x580.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-8247" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-B-custom-shape--1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-B-custom-shape--300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-B-custom-shape--768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-B-custom-shape--1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-delivery-zone-and-charges-option-B-custom-shape-.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:55.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:55.000000Z',
                ],
                8 => [
                    'id' => 9,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-apply-delivery-charges-to-a-specific-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Apply Delivery Charges to a Specific Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Once you set up global delivery rules (Kilometer Wise, Area Wise, or Zone Wise), you must apply them to individual branches. This ensures each branch can have unique delivery configurations.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-branch-delivery-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Branch Delivery Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Restaurant Management →Restaurant Setup → </strong> <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the branch you want to configure in the <strong>Branch List</strong>.</li><li>Click the <strong>Three-dot menu</strong> on the right-hand side of a specific branch.</li><li>Select <strong>Edit Delivery Area &amp; Charges</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/from-branch-list-navigate-to-edit-delivery-area-and-charges-1024x576.webp" alt="From Branch List Navigate To Edit Delivery Area &amp; Charges" class="wp-image-10667" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/from-branch-list-navigate-to-edit-delivery-area-and-charges-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/from-branch-list-navigate-to-edit-delivery-area-and-charges-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/from-branch-list-navigate-to-edit-delivery-area-and-charges-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/from-branch-list-navigate-to-edit-delivery-area-and-charges-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/from-branch-list-navigate-to-edit-delivery-area-and-charges.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-enable-and-select-the-delivery-charge-type" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enable and Select the Delivery Charge Type</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Zone &amp; Delivery Area &amp; Charges Setup</strong> page for the selected branch.</li><li>Toggle ON the switch to Enable <strong>Delivery Charges</strong>.</li><li>Select a <strong>Delivery Charge Type</strong> for the branch:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>KM Wise</strong> – Charge customers based on delivery distance.</li><li><strong>Area Wise</strong> – Use fixed charges for predefined areas or postal codes.</li><li><strong>Zone Wise</strong> – Apply flat rates for custom-drawn delivery zones.</li></ul></li></ul><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><em><strong>Note</strong></em></p><p><em><em>These charge types are based on the global settings from </em><strong><em>Delivery Area Setup</em></strong><em>. If not configured yet, </em><a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/restaurant-branch-setup/how-to-set-up-delivery-areas-and-charges/"><em>click here</em></a><em> to set up first.</em></em></p></div></div><h2 id="step-3-configure-branch-specific-settings" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 3: Configure Branch-Specific Settings</strong></h2><p><strong>For KM Wise Charges</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The system will display the global <strong>Per-Kilometer Delivery Charge</strong> (e.g., $5).</li><li>Configure optional limits:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Base Delivery Charge</strong> – Set a minimum charge applied to all deliveries.</li><li><strong>Maximum Delivery Charge</strong> – Cap the maximum fee, regardless of distance (e.g., if fee = $25 but cap = $15, customer pays $15).</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-km-wise-charge-1024x580.webp" alt="KM Wise Charge" class="wp-image-9732" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-km-wise-charge-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-km-wise-charge-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-km-wise-charge-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-km-wise-charge-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-km-wise-charge.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p><strong>For Area Wise Charges</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Open the <strong>Select Area</strong> dropdown.</li><li>Choose the area or postal code for this branch.</li><li>The system will display the fixed fee associated with the selected area.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-1024x581.webp" alt="Area Wise Charge" class="wp-image-8294" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/area-wise-charge.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p><strong>For Zone Wise Charges</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Open the <strong>Select Zone</strong> dropdown.</li><li>Select the delivery zone for this branch from the drop-down.</li><li>The system will display the flat fee for that zone.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-zone-wise-charge-1024x581.webp" alt="Zone Wise Charge" class="wp-image-9734" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-zone-wise-charge-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-zone-wise-charge-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-zone-wise-charge-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-zone-wise-charge-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-zone-wise-charge.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-save-your-configuration" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save Your Configuration</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all settings are defined, click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong> (top-right corner).</li><li>Your branch will now calculate delivery charges based on the rules you applied.</li></ul><p>With these steps, you can assign global delivery methods to specific branches, giving each location its own delivery pricing structure.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:55.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:55.000000Z',
                ],
                9 => [
                    'id' => 10,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-assign-a-menu-to-a-specific-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Assign a Menu to a Specific Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to assign menus to individual branches. This allows you to manage different menus for multiple locations from one dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-restaurant-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Restaurant Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-open-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under <strong>Restaurant Setup</strong>, click on <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li><li>A list of all your branches will be displayed.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-select-a-branch-and-assign-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select a Branch and Assign Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the branch you want to assign a menu to.</li><li>On the right-hand side of the branch entry, click the <strong>Assign Menu </strong>Icon near the <strong>Three-dot menu</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-1024x576.webp" alt="Assign Menu Icon" class="wp-image-9738" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-icon.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A new window will appear displaying all <strong>available menus</strong>.</li><li><strong>Choose</strong> the menu you want to assign to this branch.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-1024x577.webp" alt="Assign Menu to a Branch" class="wp-image-8211" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/assign-menu-to-a-branch.webp 1914w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You have now successfully assigned a menu to a branch, allowing each location to operate with its own tailored menu.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:56.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:56.000000Z',
                ],
                10 => [
                    'id' => 11,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-change-the-existing-menu-of-a-specific-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Change the Existing Menu of a Specific Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to replace an existing menu with a new one for any branch. Menumium makes it easy to manage and update menus across different locations.</p><h2 id="step-1-go-to-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Go to Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, navigate to the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The page will display all your branches and their details.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-locate-the-branch-select-the-new-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Locate the Branch &amp; Select the New Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the branch where you want to update the menu.</li><li>On the right-hand side of the branch entry, click the <strong>Assign Menu </strong>Icon near the <strong>Three-dot menu</strong>. Clicking on it will give you the option of <strong>Change Menu</strong>. Now, click on Change Menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-change-menu-option-1024x576.webp" alt="Change Menu Option" class="wp-image-9752" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-change-menu-option-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-change-menu-option-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-change-menu-option-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-change-menu-option-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-change-menu-option.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window will appear showing the list of available menus.</li><li>Choose the new menu you want to assign to the branch and click <strong>Save</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-menu-popup-1024x575.webp" alt="Change Menu Popup" class="wp-image-8323" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-menu-popup-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-menu-popup-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-menu-popup-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-menu-popup-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-menu-popup.webp 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can quickly update a branch’s menu, ensuring each location has the correct offerings.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:57.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:57.000000Z',
                ],
                11 => [
                    'id' => 12,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-configure-working-hours-for-a-restaurant-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Configure Working Hours for a Restaurant Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to set up or modify the operating hours for any branch. You can configure unique schedules for each day, add multiple time slots within a single day, or mark a branch as always open.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-side navigation menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-select-the-branch" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Branch</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>Branch List</strong> will display all available branches.</li><li>Locate the branch you want to configure.</li><li>Click the <strong>Three-dot action menu (â®)</strong> on the right-hand side of the branch.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-access-working-hour-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Access Working Hour Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the action menu, select <strong>Edit Working Hour</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-working-hour-settings-1024x576.webp" alt="Access Working Hour Settings" class="wp-image-10673" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-working-hour-settings-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-working-hour-settings-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-working-hour-settings-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-working-hour-settings-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-working-hour-settings.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-choose-time-configuration-type" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Choose Time Configuration Type</h2><p>On the <strong>Working Hours</strong> page, select one of the following:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Always Open</strong> – Choose this if the branch operates 24/7.</li><li><strong>Set Specific Time</strong> – Choose this to define custom working hours for each day of the week.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-configuration-type-1024x576.webp" alt="Choose Configuration Type" class="wp-image-9757" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-configuration-type-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-configuration-type-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-configuration-type-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-configuration-type-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-configuration-type.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p><em>(For this guide, we will use Set Specific Time.)</em></p><h2 id="step-5-set-the-daily-schedule" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set the Daily Schedule</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Activate a Day</strong> – Click the toggle beside a day to activate scheduling.</li><li><strong>Set Time Slots</strong> – Once activated, click the <strong>Plus (+) </strong>icon to add opening and closing hours.</li><li><strong>Add Multiple Slots – </strong>If the branch operates in shifts (e.g., lunch and dinner), click the<strong> Plus (+) </strong>icon again to add another slot for the same day.</li><li><strong>Remove a Slot </strong>– Click the<strong> Red (X) </strong>icon to delete a slot.</li><li><strong>Apply to All Days – T</strong>o set the same timing for all days, use the checkbox above the list.</li><li>A success notification will confirm: <em>“Working schedule was updated successfully.”</em></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-specific-time-1024x580.webp" alt="Set Specific Time" class="wp-image-10674" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-specific-time-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-specific-time-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-specific-time-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-specific-time-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-specific-time.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can easily configure working hours for each branch, ensuring accurate schedules for your restaurant operations.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:57.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:57.000000Z',
                ],
                12 => [
                    'id' => 13,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-branch-details-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit Branch Details in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to modify the basic details of an existing branch, including its address, contact person, logo, and customer support information.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-the-branch-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Branch to Edit</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch List</strong> page, review the list of existing branches.</li><li>Find the branch you want to edit.</li><li>Click the <strong>Three-dot action menu (â®)</strong> on the right-hand side of the branch.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-access-the-edit-details-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Access the Edit Details Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li><li>You will be redirected to the branch’s configuration page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-edit-details-of-branch-1024x576.webp" alt="Edit Details Of Branch" class="wp-image-9760" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-edit-details-of-branch-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-edit-details-of-branch-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-edit-details-of-branch-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-edit-details-of-branch-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-edit-details-of-branch.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-update-the-branch-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Update the Branch Information</h2><p>On the <strong>Setup Basic Information</strong> page, you can update:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Branch Info</strong> – Edit the <strong>Branch Name</strong> and <strong>Address</strong>.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>+ See More</strong> to reveal and update additional fields (Country, State, City, Zip Code).</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-1024x579.webp" alt="Setup Basic Info" class="wp-image-8360" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-1536x868.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Contact Person Info</strong> – Update the contact person’s <strong>Name</strong>, <strong>Designation</strong>, <strong>Phone Number</strong>, and <strong>Email</strong>.</li><li><strong>Branch Logo</strong> – Upload a new logo for the branch or use the existing business logo.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/contact-person-info-1024x580.webp" alt="Contact Person Info" class="wp-image-8369" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/contact-person-info-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/contact-person-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/contact-person-info-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/contact-person-info-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/contact-person-info.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Customer Support Contact Info</strong> – Toggle ON to enable separate customer-facing details.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Choose a <strong>Support Type</strong> (Phone Number, Telephone, or Hotline).</li><li>Enter the relevant contact details.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-support-1024x579.webp" alt="Customer Support" class="wp-image-8362" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-support-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-support-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-support-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-support-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-support.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-5-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 5: Save the Changes</strong></h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After making edits, click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong> (top-right corner).</li><li>A success confirmation will appear, and you will be directed to the next configuration tab.</li></ul><p>By following these steps, you can keep branch details updated. This will ensure accurate contact and location information for your branches.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:58.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:58.000000Z',
                ],
                13 => [
                    'id' => 14,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-activate-and-deactivate-a-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Activate and Deactivate a Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to manage the status of a restaurant branch, enabling or disabling its availability for services such as online ordering and POS transactions.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>Branch List</strong> page will display all your registered branches.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-access-branch-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access Branch Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch List</strong> page, locate the branch you want to manage.</li><li>Click the <strong>Quick View (eye icon)</strong> on the right side of the branch row.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-view-icon-navigation-1024x576.webp" alt="Quick View Icon Navigation" class="wp-image-10679" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-view-icon-navigation-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-view-icon-navigation-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-view-icon-navigation-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-view-icon-navigation-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-view-icon-navigation.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window will open, showing branch details.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-deactivate-the-branch" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Deactivate the Branch</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the pop-up window, locate the <strong>Status toggle</strong> (top-right).</li><li>Switch the toggle <strong>OFF</strong> to deactivate the branch.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, warning that deactivating will disable POS and online ordering for this branch.</li><li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong> to proceed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/deactive-branch-1024x580.webp" alt="Deactive Branch" class="wp-image-10684" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/deactive-branch-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/deactive-branch-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/deactive-branch-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/deactive-branch-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/deactive-branch.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A success message will appear: <em>“The branch was updated successfully.”</em></li><li>The branch will now show a <strong>red circle</strong> next to its name in the Branch List, indicating inactive status.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-deactive-indicator-1024x576.webp" alt="Branch Deactive Indicator" class="wp-image-10685" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-deactive-indicator-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-deactive-indicator-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-deactive-indicator-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-deactive-indicator-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-deactive-indicator.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-activate-the-branch" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Activate the Branch</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>To reactivate, repeat <strong>Step 1</strong> and <strong>Step 2</strong> to open the branch details.</li><li>In the pop-up, switch the <strong>Status toggle ON</strong>.</li><li>A success message will confirm that the branch has been updated and is now active.</li><li>The <strong>red circle</strong> next to the branch name will disappear, and a green circle will appear once it is active.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/active-1024x580.webp" alt="Active" class="wp-image-8385" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/active-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/active-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/active-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/active-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/active.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can quickly control whether a branch is live and available for orders, giving you full flexibility over branch operations.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 8,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:59.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:52:59.000000Z',
                ],
                14 => [
                    'id' => 15,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-an-inventory-model-for-a-branch-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up an Inventory Model for a Branch in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to activate and configure inventory management for a specific branch, helping you control stock levels and ingredient usage directly from the Menumium platform.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-branch-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Branch Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-a-branch" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select a Branch</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch List</strong> page, locate the branch you want to configure.</li><li>Click the <strong>Three-dot (â®) menu</strong> next to the branch name.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-edit-branch-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Edit Branch Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dropdown options, click <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li><li>This will open the settings page for the selected branch.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-list-edit-details-navigation-1024x576.webp" alt="Branch List Edit Details Navigation" class="wp-image-10688" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-list-edit-details-navigation-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-list-edit-details-navigation-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-list-edit-details-navigation-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-list-edit-details-navigation-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-list-edit-details-navigation.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-access-inventory-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Access Inventory Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the branch settings, navigate to the <strong>Inventory</strong> tab.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-enable-inventory-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Enable Inventory Management</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle ON the <strong>Inventory Management Model</strong> switch.</li><li>This will activate inventory tracking for the branch.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-navigation-1024x576.webp" alt="Inventory Model Navigation" class="wp-image-10689" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-navigation-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-navigation-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-navigation-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-navigation-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-navigation.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-choose-an-inventory-usage-model" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Choose an Inventory Usage Model</h2><p>Once enabled, select your preferred inventory deduction method:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Deduct inventory after order confirmation:</strong> This option automatically deducts items from your inventory as soon as a customerâs order is confirmed.</li><li><strong>Deduct inventory when prepare recipe wise food:</strong> This option deducts ingredients from your inventory based on the recipe when a dish is being prepared.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-toggle-1024x580.webp" alt="Inventory Model Toggle" class="wp-image-9764" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-toggle-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-toggle-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-toggle-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-toggle-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-model-toggle.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-save-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Save Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply your settings.</li><li>A success notification will confirm: <em>“Business settings were updated successfully.”</em></li></ul><p>With these steps, your branch will now manage stock accurately, ensuring better control over ingredients, waste reduction, and smoother operations.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 9,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:00.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:00.000000Z',
                ],
                15 => [
                    'id' => 16,
                    'doc_category_id' => 2,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-view-branch-details-and-order-information-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to View Branch Details and Order Information in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Menumium provides a complete overview of each restaurant branch, including details, contact information, performance metrics, and associated orders. This guide explains how to view branch details, check specific orders, and export order lists.</p><h2 id="step-1-view-branch-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: View Branch Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong> <strong>&gt; Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Restaurant Management to Restaurant Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12234" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/restaurant-management-to-restaurant-setup-navigation-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch List</strong> page, locate the desired branch.</li><li>Click the <strong>Three-dot menu (â®)</strong> next to the branch.</li><li>Select <strong>View Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-navigation-1024x576.webp" alt="View Details Navigation" class="wp-image-10692" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-navigation-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-navigation-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-navigation-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-navigation-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-navigation.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The screen will display complete information about the selected branch.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-1024x581.webp" alt="View Details" class="wp-image-8411" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-details.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-review-additional-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Review Additional Information</h2><p>Below the branch details, you will find the <strong>Additional Information</strong> section. This provides key performance insights for the branch:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Total Orders</strong> – Number of all orders processed.</li><li><strong>Default Menu</strong> – The menu currently assigned to the branch.</li><li><strong>Available Order Types</strong> – The types of orders enabled (e.g., dine-in, takeaway, delivery).</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-check-individual-order-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Check Individual Order Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch Details</strong> page, scroll down to the <strong>Order List</strong> section.</li><li>The list is shown in a table format with Order ID, date, and status.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column for the order you want to check, click the <strong>Eye icon</strong>.</li><li>A pop-up window will display:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Ordered items</li><li>Quantities</li><li>Customer notes or comments</li><li>Total bill</li><li>Invoice</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-details-1024x582.webp" alt="Order Details" class="wp-image-8410" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-details-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-details-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-details-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-details-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-details.webp 1900w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-export-the-order-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Export the Order List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the Order List section of the Branch Details page, go to the top-right corner of the table.</li><li>Click Export.</li><li>The file will be downloaded directly to your device.<br></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-export-1024x581.webp" alt="Export" class="wp-image-9767" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-export-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-export-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-export-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-export-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-export.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can view branch details, analyze performance, check individual orders, and export order lists for reporting or record-keeping.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 10,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:00.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:00.000000Z',
