                65 => [
                    'id' => 66,
                    'doc_category_id' => 7,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-the-website-storefront',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up the Website/Storefront',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Access the Dashboard:</strong> Begin by logging into your Menumium dashboard.</li><li><strong>Navigate to Website Setup:</strong> On the left-hand menu, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>Website Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10717" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Go to Website Layout:</strong> From the dropdown menu that appears, select <strong>Website Layout</strong>. This is where you will find all the customization options for your website’s appearance.</li></ul><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><p><em>Before setting up your restaurant website, make sure you have <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/food-management/how-to-filter-or-export-category-in-food-management-2/">added food items</a> and <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/menu-management/how-to-create-a-new-menu/">menus</a> in the Menumium admin dashboard. These items will appear on your website and be available for customers to order.</em></p><h2 id="how-to-customize-the-websites-main-sections" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Website’s Main Sections</h2><h3 id="how-to-change-website-layout" class="wp-block-heading">How to Change Website Layout</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Find Website Layout Section (Restaurant Management &gt; Website Setup &gt; Website Layout):</strong> This section allows you to define the main visual style of your website.</li><li><strong>Change Primary Color:</strong> Click on the <strong>color palette</strong> to open a color picker. Select a primary color that reflects your brand. This color will be used for key elements like buttons and highlights.</li><li><strong>Change Font:</strong> Click on the <strong>font dropdown menu</strong> to choose a new font style for your website from a list of available options.</li><li><strong>Save Changes:</strong> After selecting your preferred color and font, click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to apply them to your website.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-website-layout-0a.webp" alt="Change Website Layout" class="wp-image-10710" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-website-layout-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-website-layout-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/change-website-layout-0a-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="how-to-customize-the-header-section" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Header Section</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Find Header Section (Restaurant Management &gt; Website Setup &gt; Website Layout):</strong> This section controls the content and appearance of the top part of your website.</li><li><strong>Upload Logo:</strong> Click the <strong>upload file</strong> button to upload your business logo. This logo will appear in the header.</li><li><strong>Set Header Background Color:</strong> Click on the <strong>color palette</strong> to choose a background color for the header.</li><li><strong>Set Header Font Color:</strong> Click on the <strong>color palette</strong> to choose a font color for the header text.</li><li><strong>Enable Sticky Header:</strong> Toggle the <strong>Sticky Header</strong> option to on or off. When enabled, the header will remain fixed at the top of the page even as a user scrolls down.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enable-sticky-header-0b.webp" alt="Enable Sticky Header" class="wp-image-10709" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enable-sticky-header-0b.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enable-sticky-header-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enable-sticky-header-0b-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="how-to-manage-header-menu" class="wp-block-heading">How to Manage Header Menu</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Find Header Menu Section (Restaurant Management &gt; Website Setup &gt; Website Layout):</strong> This section allows you to organize the navigation links in your header.</li><li><strong>Reorder Menu Items:</strong> You can easily reorder the menu items by dragging and dropping them into your desired sequence.</li><li><strong>Add “Order Now” Button:</strong> To add a call-to-action button, toggle the <strong>Show Button</strong> option to on.</li><li><strong>Customize Button Text:</strong> Edit the content in the <strong>Button Text</strong> field to change the text displayed on the button (e.g., “Order Online,” “Order Now”).</li><li><strong>Save Changes:</strong> Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to save your menu layout and button settings.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-button-text-0c.webp" alt="Customize Button Text" class="wp-image-10708" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-button-text-0c.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-button-text-0c-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-button-text-0c-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="how-to-customize-the-footer-section" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Footer Section</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Find Footer Section (Restaurant Management &gt; Website Setup &gt; Website Layout):</strong> This section manages the content and appearance of the bottom part of your website.</li><li><strong>Upload Footer Background:</strong> Click on the <strong>upload file</strong> button to upload an image specifically for the footer.</li><li><strong>Reorder Footer Menus:</strong> You can reorder the items in the footer menu by dragging and dropping them.</li><li><strong>Update Contact Information:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the <strong>Contact Us</strong> section.</li><li>Enter your business phone number in the <strong>Phone Number</strong> field.</li><li>Enter your business location in the <strong>Location</strong> field.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Manage “My Account” Section:</strong> You can reorder the items listed under the “My Account” section.</li><li><strong>Add Copyright Information:</strong> Enter the copyright text (e.g., “© 2025 All Rights Reserved”) in the <strong>Copyright Text</strong> field.</li><li><strong>Save Changes:</strong> Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to apply all the changes to your footer.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-copyright-information-0d.webp" alt="Add Copyright Information" class="wp-image-10707" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-copyright-information-0d.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-copyright-information-0d-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-copyright-information-0d-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="how-to-add-a-favicon" class="wp-block-heading">How to Add a Favicon</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Find Favicon Section (Restaurant Management &gt; Website Setup &gt; Website Layout):</strong> The favicon section is within the <strong>Website Layout</strong> options.</li><li><strong>Upload Favicon:</strong> Click on the <strong>upload file</strong> button to upload your favicon. A favicon is a small, icon-like image that appears in the browser tab next to your website’s name. It helps to brand your website and makes it easily recognizable to users. Maximum file size is 1 MB.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-a-favicon-0e.webp" alt="Add A Favicon" class="wp-image-10706" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-a-favicon-0e.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-a-favicon-0e-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-a-favicon-0e-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="how-to-set-up-the-website-url" class="wp-block-heading">How to Set Up the Website URL</h2><p>This guide details how to set a URL for your website within the Menumium dashboard.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Access the Dashboard</strong> – Log in to your Menumium dashboard.</li><li><strong>Navigate to Website Setup</strong> – From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> Website Setup &gt; Website URL &amp; Availability.</li><li><strong>Manage Website Availability</strong> – Use the toggle to control when your website is live. You get two options here:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Make unavailable unless changed</strong> – Keeps the website offline until you switch it back on.</li><li><strong>Make available after a certain time </strong>– Set your site to go live automatically at a chosen time.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Create a Subdomain</strong> – Enter your preferred subdomain name.</li><li><strong>Preview Your Website</strong> – Use the URL Preview option to instantly view how your site looks.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-website-URL-1024x577.webp" alt="Website URL" class="wp-image-9031" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-website-URL-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-website-URL-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-website-URL-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-website-URL-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-website-URL.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="how-to-set-up-a-custom-domain-on-menumium" class="wp-block-heading">How to Set Up a Custom Domain on Menumium</h3><p>To connect a custom domain to your Menumium website, you must first initiate the connection within your Menumium dashboard and then configure your domain’s DNS settings. This process involves pointing your domain to Menumium’s servers by adding an A record.</p><h4 id="step-1-initiate-domain-connection-in-menumium" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Initiate Domain Connection in Menumium</h4><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Access the Custom Domain Section:</strong> From the <strong>Website URL</strong> page in your Menumium dashboard <strong>(Restaurant Management &gt; Website Setup &gt; Website URL)</strong>, click on <strong>Advanced Settings</strong> to reveal the custom domain options.</li><li><strong>Locate “Setup Custom Domain”:</strong> Find this section, which is specifically for users who want to use their own custom domain.</li><li><strong>Enter Custom URL:</strong> In the input field, type in your full custom URL (e.g., “quick-bites.com”).</li><li><strong>Connect Domain:</strong> Click the <strong>Connect</strong> button to initiate the domain connection process.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-setup-custom-domain-1024x580.webp" alt="Setup Custom Domain" class="wp-image-9032" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-setup-custom-domain-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-setup-custom-domain-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-setup-custom-domain-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-setup-custom-domain-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-setup-custom-domain.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>After this step, you must configure your domain’s DNS records to complete the setup.</p></div></div><h4 id="step-2-configure-your-domains-dns-records" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Configure Your Domain’s DNS Records</h4><h5 class="wp-block-heading">Method 1: Direct DNS Configuration</h5><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Access Your Domain Control Panel:</strong> Log in to the control panel of your domain registrar (e.g., GoDaddy, Namecheap, Google Domains).</li><li><strong>Navigate to DNS Settings:</strong> Find the DNS management or advanced DNS settings section. The name might vary depending on your registrar.</li><li><strong>Add an A Record:</strong> Create a new DNS record with the following details:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Type:</strong> Select <strong>A</strong> (Address Record).</li><li><strong>Host/Name:</strong> Enter <strong>@</strong> to configure the main domain, or a subdomain name if you want to use that (e.g., www).</li><li><strong>Value/IP Address:</strong> Enter the provided IP address: <strong>137.184.251.200</strong>.</li><li><strong>TTL (Time to Live):</strong> Set this to the lowest possible value, if available, for faster propagation.</li></ul></li></ol><h5 class="wp-block-heading">Method 2: Using Cloudflare (Alternative)</h5><p>If your domain registrar does not provide an option to set up DNS records directly, you can use Cloudflare as an intermediary to manage your DNS.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Connect Your Domain to Cloudflare:</strong> First, change your domain’s nameservers at your registrar to the nameservers provided by Cloudflare.</li><li><strong>Add the A Record in Cloudflare:</strong> Once your domain is connected to Cloudflare, navigate to the <strong>DNS</strong> tab in your Cloudflare dashboard.</li><li><strong>Create the A Record:</strong> Add the same A record as described in the previous section:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Type:</strong> <strong>A</strong></li><li><strong>Name:</strong> <strong>@</strong> or www</li><li><strong>IPv4 address:</strong> <strong>137.184.251.200</strong></li><li>Ensure the proxy status is set to <strong>DNS Only</strong> (the cloud icon should be gray).</li></ul></li></ol><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:38.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:38.000000Z',
                ],
                66 => [
                    'id' => 67,
                    'doc_category_id' => 7,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-customize-website-contents',
                    'title' => 'How to Customize Website Contents',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Easily update your website text, images, and layouts without coding. This feature lets you personalize content to match your brand, improve user experience, and keep your site fresh and relevant.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Access the Dashboard:</strong> Begin by logging into your Menumium dashboard.</li><li><strong>Navigate to Website Setup:</strong> On the left-hand menu, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong>  <strong>Website Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10717" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-setup-0f-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Go to Website Content:</strong> From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="how-to-customize-the-websites-home-page" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Website’s “Home” Page?</h2><p>This guide provides a detailed walkthrough for managing and editing the content on the <strong>Home Page</strong> of your website. The process includes accessing the editor and customizing each section individually.</p><h3 id="step-1-access-the-home-page-editor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Home Page Editor</h3><p>To begin editing, navigate to the correct section within the website’s administrative portal.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the main <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, select <strong>Website Setup</strong> from the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Home Page</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-access-home-page-editor-1024x576.webp" alt="Access Home Page Editor" class="wp-image-9068" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-access-home-page-editor-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-access-home-page-editor-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-access-home-page-editor-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-access-home-page-editor-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-access-home-page-editor.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-edit-the-home-page-content-sections" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit the Home Page Content Sections</h3><p>The editor is divided into several sections that correspond to different parts of the live homepage.</p><h4 id="intro-section" class="wp-block-heading">Intro Section</h4><p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Controls the main banner and introductory text of the homepage.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle the <em>Show on website?</em> option to display or hide the Intro section.</li><li><strong>Layout</strong>: Click the Pencil icon next to <strong><em>Intro Layout</em></strong><strong> </strong>to select your preferred layout.</li><li><strong>Banner Image</strong>: Upload a banner image.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Maximum size: 10 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: <strong>1440 × 590 px</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>Title and Sub-Title</strong>: Enter your desired heading and slogan.</li><li><strong>Call-to-Action Button</strong>:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle <em>Show Button?</em> to enable a button.</li><li>Edit the <em>Button. </em>You can edit the button text as you need.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Social Media Links</strong>:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle <em>Show Social Media?</em> to enable social icons.</li><li>Use the Pencil icon to add URLs for each platform.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-home-page-intro-1024x576.webp" alt="Home Page Intro
" class="wp-image-9069" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-home-page-intro-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-home-page-intro-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-home-page-intro-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-home-page-intro-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-home-page-intro.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="about-us-section" class="wp-block-heading">About Us Section</h4><p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Allows you to provide an overview of your business.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle the <strong><em>Show on website?</em></strong> option to display or hide the section.</li><li><strong>Layout</strong>: Click the Pencil icon next to <em>About Us Layout</em> to choose a design (e.g., Classic or Modern).</li><li><strong>Background Image</strong>: Upload an image for the section background.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Recommended ratio: <strong>755 × 550 px</strong><br></li></ul></li><li><strong>Text Fields</strong>: Edit the Title, Sub-Title, and Content.</li><li><strong>Phone Number:</strong> Optionally display your business phone number. Use the toggle to show or hide it.</li><li><strong>Save Changes</strong>: Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to apply edits.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-home-page-about-us-1-1024x576.webp" alt="Home Page About Us" class="wp-image-9070" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-home-page-about-us-1-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-home-page-about-us-1-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-home-page-about-us-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-home-page-about-us-1-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-home-page-about-us-1.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="trust-section" class="wp-block-heading">Trust Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Purpose</strong>: Highlight key achievements, stats, or values to build customer trust.</li><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle <em>Show on website?</em> to display or hide the section.</li><li><strong>Layout</strong>: Select a layout design for the trust section.</li><li><strong>Image/Banner</strong>: Upload a banner for the section.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Max size: 5 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: 1100 × 300 px</li></ul></li></ul><h5 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Section Details</strong></h5><p>Each trust item (up to four sections) can be customized individually:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Section Image/Icon</strong> – Upload an image or icon (1:1 ratio).</li><li><strong>Title</strong> – Add a short label (e.g., <em>Professional Chefs</em>, <em>Years of Experience</em>).</li><li><strong>Counting</strong> – Input the number or figure to display (e.g., <em>320 items</em>, <em>2+ years</em>, <em>5000+ happy customers</em>).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-home-page-trust-section-1-1024x576.webp" alt="Home Page Trust Section" class="wp-image-9071" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-home-page-trust-section-1-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-home-page-trust-section-1-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-home-page-trust-section-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-home-page-trust-section-1-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-home-page-trust-section-1.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="popular-dish-section" class="wp-block-heading">Popular Dish Section</h4><p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Highlights selected popular menu items.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle the <em>Show on website?</em> option to display or hide the section.</li><li>The <strong>Popular Dish Layout</strong> option lets you pick different styles, like Classic or Modern. This controls how your featured dishes look on the homepage.</li><li>The <strong>Popular Dish Background</strong> setting allows you to choose a background color for the section to match your website’s theme.</li><li>The <strong>Section Title</strong> field allows you to create a custom heading, like “Popular Dish.” This heading will show above the featured items on your homepage.</li><li><strong>Food Items</strong>: Click <strong>Add Item</strong> to select dishes from your existing menu.</li><li>The <strong>Button</strong> setting allows you to control the visibility of a call-to-action button and customize its label (e.g., “View All”) to guide visitors to more menu items.</li><li><strong>Save Changes</strong>: Finalize by clicking <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-home-page-popular-dish-1-1024x576.webp" alt="Home Page Popular Dish" class="wp-image-9072" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-home-page-popular-dish-1-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-home-page-popular-dish-1-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-home-page-popular-dish-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-home-page-popular-dish-1-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-home-page-popular-dish-1.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="menu-section" class="wp-block-heading">Menu Section</h4><p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Displays the full food menu directly on the homepage.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle the <em>Show on website?</em> option to display or hide the section.</li><li><strong>Layout</strong>: Click the Pencil icon next to <em>Menu Layout</em> to select a design (e.g., Classic or Modern).</li><li><strong>Background Color</strong>: Choose a background color for your menu section to match your website’s design.</li><li><strong>Background Overlay</strong>: Add a color overlay to the menu background to improve text readability and enhance the overall appearance.</li><li><strong>Background Image</strong>: Upload a custom image as the backdrop for your menu section to give it a more personalized look.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Recommended ratio of <strong>1:1</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>Section Title</strong>: Write a custom heading for your menu section (up to 40 characters) to help visitors easily identify the content.</li><li><strong>Show Food</strong>: Choose whether to display all menu categories or only selected ones in the menu section.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Select Categories</strong>: Pick specific food categories (e.g., Fries, Wraps) to highlight on the homepage while keeping all items available on the full menu page.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Button</strong>: Enable or disable a call-to-action button in the menu section, and customize the button text (up to 30 characters) to guide visitors (e.g., “View Full Menu” or “See All Dishes”).</li><li><strong>Save Changes</strong>: Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-home-page-menu-1024x577.webp" alt="Home Page Menu" class="wp-image-9074" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-home-page-menu-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-home-page-menu-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-home-page-menu-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-home-page-menu-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-home-page-menu.webp 1914w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="gallery-section" class="wp-block-heading">Gallery Section</h4><p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Showcases photos of your restaurant, food, or ambiance.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle the <em>Show on website?</em> option to display or hide the gallery.</li><li><strong>Gallery Section Layout</strong>: Choose a layout for your gallery section. You can pick Classic, Modern, or Slider. This will control how images show on the home page’s gallery.</li><li><strong>Section Title</strong>: Write a custom heading for your gallery section (up to 40 characters) to clearly label the content for visitors.</li><li><strong>Add Photos</strong>: Click the <strong>Pencil Icon</strong> and upload an image from your device.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Ratio: 755 x 550</li></ul></li><li><strong>Manage Gallery Section Images</strong>: Delete or view existing photos in the gallery.</li><li><strong>Save Changes</strong>: Click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to finalize updates.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-home-page-gallery-1024x576.webp" alt="Home Page Gallery" class="wp-image-9075" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-home-page-gallery-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-home-page-gallery-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-home-page-gallery-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-home-page-gallery-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-home-page-gallery.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-3-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Save the Changes</h3><p>After making edits to any section, scroll to the bottom of the page and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This ensures all modifications are applied to your live homepage.</p><h2 id="how-to-customize-the-websites-about-us-page" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Website’s ‘About Us’ Page?</h2><p>This guide provides a detailed walkthrough for managing and editing the content on the “About Us” page of your website. The process involves navigating to the content editor and customizing each section individually.</p><h3 id="step-1-access-the-about-us-editor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the ‘About Us’ Editor </h3><p>To begin editing, navigate to the correct section within the website’s administrative portal.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, select <strong>Website Setup</strong> from the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>About Us</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><h3 id="step-2-edit-the-page-content-sections" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit the Page Content Sections </h3><p>The editor is divided into several manageable sections that correspond to different parts of the live “About Us” page.</p><h4 id="page-visibility" class="wp-block-heading">Page Visibility</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Show About Us Page?</strong>: At the very top, use the toggle switch to make the entire “About Us” page visible or hidden from the public website.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-1024x577.webp" alt="About Us" class="wp-image-9076" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="intro-section" class="wp-block-heading">Intro Section</h4><p>This is the top-most part of the page.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title and Sub-Title</strong>: Enter the main heading and the subheading for the page.</li><li><strong>Intro Image/Banner</strong>: Upload a banner image.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Supported formats</strong>: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP.</li><li><strong>Maximum size</strong>: 5 MB.</li><li><strong>Ratio</strong>: 1:6.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Banner Overlay Color</strong>: Select a color to place over the banner image. This can improve the readability of the text on top of the image.</li></ul><h4 id="company-overview-section" class="wp-block-heading">Company Overview Section</h4><p>Provide core information about the business here.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Company Overview Image</strong>: Upload an image to represent the company.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Supported formats</strong>: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP.</li><li><strong>Maximum size</strong>: 5 MB.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Title and Description</strong>: Write a title and a detailed description for the company overview.</li></ul><h4 id="our-mission-our-vision-sections" class="wp-block-heading">Our Mission &amp; Our Vision Sections</h4><p>These two sections are structured identically.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Use the toggle to show or hide the “Our Mission” or “Our Vision” section.</li><li><strong>Image</strong>: Upload a relevant image for the section.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Supported formats</strong>: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP.</li><li><strong>Maximum size</strong>: 5 MB.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Description</strong>: Write the mission or vision statement in the text box provided.</li></ul><h4 id="gallery-section" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Gallery Section</strong></h4><p>Showcase a collection of images.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manage Visibility</strong>: Toggle this section on or off.</li><li><strong>Section Title</strong>: Enter a title for the gallery (e.g., “Our Delicious Food”).</li><li><strong>Gallery Images</strong>: Add, remove, rearrange, or replace multiple images to display in a photo gallery.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Supported formats</strong>: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP.</li><li><strong>Maximum size</strong>: 5 MB.</li><li><strong>Ratio</strong>: 755 x 550</li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>Step 3: Save the Changes</strong></p><p>After completing all edits, scroll to the bottom of any section and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This action will apply all the modifications made across the entire page to the live website.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-1024x577.webp" alt="About Us" class="wp-image-9076" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-about-us.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="how-to-manage-the-websites-contact-us-page" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How to Manage the Website’s ‘Contact Us’ Page?</strong></h2><p>This guide explains how to update the information on the “Contact Us” page, including contact details, titles, and banner images.</p><h3 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-contact-us-settings" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 1: Navigate to the ‘Contact Us’ Settings </strong></h3><p>To begin editing, access the “Contact Us” management area by following this path in the admin panel:</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, go to <strong>Website Setup</strong>.</li><li>In the side menu, click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Contact Us</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><h3 id="step-2-customize-the-page-sections" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 2: Customize the Page Sections </strong></h3><p>The editing interface allows for the modification of several distinct sections on the page.</p><h4 id="page-visibility" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Page Visibility</strong></h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Show Contact Us Page?</strong>: Use the primary toggle switch at the top to either display or hide the entire “Contact Us” page on the public website.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-conract-us-1024x578.webp" alt="Contact Us" class="wp-image-9077" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-conract-us-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-conract-us-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-conract-us-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-conract-us-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-conract-us.webp 1913w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="title-sub-title-section" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Title &amp; Sub-title Section</strong></h4><p>This section controls the main headings of the page.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title</strong>: Enter the main title for the page (e.g., “Contact Us”).</li><li><strong>Sub-title</strong>: Provide a brief, descriptive subtitle or message.</li></ul><h4 id="intro-image-banner" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Intro Image / Banner</strong></h4><p>This section manages the page’s main visual banner.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Upload Image</strong>: Click to upload an intro image or banner for the page.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Supported Formats</strong>: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP.</li><li><strong>Maximum Size</strong>: 5 MB.</li><li><strong>Ratio</strong>: 1:6.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Banner Overlay Color</strong>: Select a color to apply as a transparent layer over the banner image. This can help make the text on top of the banner more readable.</li></ul><h4 id="contact-section" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Contact Section</strong></h4><p>This is where the primary contact information is managed.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Support Number Type</strong>: Choose the type of contact number to display.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Phone Number</strong>: A standard contact number.</li><li><strong>Telephone:</strong> For showing phone number.</li><li><strong>Hotline</strong>: For a dedicated hotline number.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Email Address</strong>: Input the official contact email address.</li><li><strong>Location</strong>: Enter the physical address of the business.</li></ul><h3 id="contact-us-form" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Contact Us Form</strong></h3><p>The <strong>Contact Us Form</strong> section allows you to manage the visibility of the form on your website’s Contact Us page. Simply toggle the <strong>Show Form?</strong> Option on or off to display or hide the form. The form’s purpose is to let visitors easily reach out with inquiries, feedback, or service requests.</p><h3 id="step-3-save-all-changes" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 3: Save All Changes</strong></h3><p>After making the necessary updates to any of the fields, click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This will apply all modifications to the live website.</p><h2 id="how-to-update-the-websites-our-menu-page" class="wp-block-heading">How to Update the Website’s “Our Menu” Page?</h2><p>This guide will walk you through the process of updating the content on the “Our Menu” page of your website. You can change the title, subtitle, background image, and the layout of your menu items.</p><h3 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-our-menu-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the “Our Menu” Page</h3><p>To begin editing, access the “Our Menu” section area by following this path in the admin panel:</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, go to <strong>Website Setup</strong>.</li><li>In the side menu, click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Our Menu</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-our-menu-1024x576.webp" alt="Our Menu" class="wp-image-9078" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-our-menu-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-our-menu-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-our-menu-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-our-menu-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-our-menu.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-edit-text-and-image-content" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit Text and Image Content</h3><p>On this page, you can modify the following:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title &amp; Sub-title:</strong> Change the main title and subtitle of your menu page.</li><li><strong>Intro Image/Banner:</strong> Update the main background image of the page. The system supports PNG, JPG, JPEG, and WEBP formats, with a maximum size of 5MB and a recommended ratio of 1:6.</li><li><strong>Banner Overlay Color:</strong> Adjust the color overlay on the banner image using the color picker.</li><li><strong>Opening Hours:</strong> Use the toggle button to show or hide the restaurant’s opening hours on the menu page.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-change-the-item-card-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Change the Item Card Layout</h3><p>To change how your menu items are displayed:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the <strong>Item Card Layout</strong> section.</li><li>Click the layout selector to choose your preferred display style, such as <strong>Grid View</strong> or <strong>List View</strong>.</li><li>After selecting your desired layout, click the <strong>Select</strong> button.</li></ul><h3 id="step-4-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save Your Changes</h3><p>Once you’ve made all the desired updates, click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. A confirmation message will appear, indicating that the “Our Menu” page content has been successfully updated.</p><h2 id="how-to-change-the-wishlist-page-layout" class="wp-block-heading">How to Change the “Wishlist” Page Layout?</h2><p>The following steps outline how to update the layout for the item cards on your website’s wishlist page.</p><h3 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-wishlist-option" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Wishlist Option</h3><p>To begin editing, access the “Wishlist” page by following this path in the admin panel:</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, go to <strong>Website Setup</strong>.</li><li>In the side menu, click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Wishlist</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><h3 id="step-2-choose-your-item-card-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Choose Your Item Card Layout</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click on the pencil button beside <strong>Item Card Layout</strong>.</li><li>Choose between two options:<strong> Grid</strong> or <strong>List</strong>.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-select-and-save" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select and Save</h3><p>After selecting your desired layout, click the <strong>“Select”</strong> button to confirm your choice. Finally, click the <strong>“Save Changes”</strong> button to apply the new layout to your website’s wishlist page.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wishlist-1024x576.webp" alt="Wishlist" class="wp-image-9774" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wishlist-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wishlist-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wishlist-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wishlist-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wishlist.webp 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="how-to-customize-the-websites-terms-conditions-page" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Website’s “Terms &amp; Conditions” Page?</h2><p>This guide provides a detailed walkthrough for updating and managing the content on the <strong>Terms &amp; Conditions</strong> page of your website. The process includes adjusting visibility, editing text fields, uploading images, and saving changes.</p><h3 id="step-1-access-the-terms-conditions-editor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Terms &amp; Conditions Editor</h3><p>To begin editing, navigate to the correct section within the website’s administrative portal.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, select <strong>Website Setup</strong> from the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Terms &amp; Conditions</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-terms-conditions-1024x577.webp" alt="Terms &amp; Conditions" class="wp-image-9080" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-terms-conditions-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-terms-conditions-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-terms-conditions-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-terms-conditions-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-terms-conditions.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-edit-the-page-content-sections" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit the Page Content Sections</h3><p>The editor is divided into sections that correspond to different parts of the Terms &amp; Conditions page.</p><h4 id="page-visibility" class="wp-block-heading">Page Visibility</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Show Terms &amp; Conditions Page?</strong>: Use the toggle switch at the top to make the Terms &amp; Conditions page visible or hidden on your live website.</li></ul><h4 id="intro-section" class="wp-block-heading">Intro Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title and Sub-Title</strong>: Enter the main heading and subheading for the page.</li><li><strong>Intro Image/Banner</strong>: Upload a banner image.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Maximum size: 5 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: <strong>1:6</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>Banner Overlay Color</strong>: Optionally, select a color overlay to improve the readability of text placed over the banner image.</li></ul><h4 id="description-section" class="wp-block-heading">Description Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Content</strong>: Use the Description field to write or paste the full text of your Terms &amp; Conditions.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Save the Changes</h3><p>After completing your edits, scroll to the bottom of the page and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This action will publish the updates to your live website.</p><h2 id="how-to-customize-the-websites-privacy-policy-page" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Website’s “Privacy Policy” Page?</h2><p>This guide provides a detailed walkthrough for updating and managing the content on the <strong>Privacy Policy</strong> page of your website. The process includes adjusting visibility, editing text fields, uploading images, and saving changes.</p><h3 id="step-1-access-the-privacy-policy-editor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Privacy Policy Editor</h3><p>To begin editing, navigate to the correct section within the website’s administrative portal.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>, select <strong>Website Setup</strong> from the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Privacy Policy</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><h3 id="step-2-edit-the-page-content-sections" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit the Page Content Sections</h3><p>The editor is divided into sections that correspond to different parts of the Privacy Policy page.</p><h4 id="page-visibility" class="wp-block-heading">Page Visibility</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Show Privacy Policy Page?</strong>: Use the toggle switch at the top to make the Privacy Policy page visible or hidden on your live website.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-privacy-policy-1-1024x576.webp" alt="Privacy Policy" class="wp-image-9775" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-privacy-policy-1-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-privacy-policy-1-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-privacy-policy-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-privacy-policy-1-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-privacy-policy-1.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="intro-section" class="wp-block-heading">Intro Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title and Sub-Title</strong>: Enter the main heading and subheading for the page.</li><li><strong>Intro Image/Banner</strong>: Upload a banner image.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Maximum size: 5 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: <strong>1:6</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>Banner Overlay Color</strong>: Optionally, select a color overlay to improve the readability of text placed on top of the banner image.</li></ul><h4 id="description-section" class="wp-block-heading">Description Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Content</strong>: Use the Description field to write or paste the full text of your Privacy Policy.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Save the Changes</h3><p>After completing your edits, scroll to the bottom of the page and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This action will publish the updates to your live website.</p><h2 id="how-to-customize-the-websites-refund-policy-page" class="wp-block-heading">How to Customize the Website’s “Refund Policy” Page?</h2><p>This guide provides a detailed walkthrough for updating and managing the content on the <strong>Refund Policy</strong> page of your website. The process includes adjusting visibility, editing text fields, uploading images, and saving changes.</p><h3 id="step-1-access-the-refund-policy-editor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Refund Policy Editor</h3><p>To begin editing, navigate to the correct section within the website’s administrative portal.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong><strong>Restaurant Management</strong></strong>, select <strong>Website Setup</strong> from the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Website Content</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Refund Policy</strong> from the list to load the editing page.</li></ol><h3 id="step-2-edit-the-page-content-sections" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit the Page Content Sections</h3><p>The editor is divided into sections that correspond to different parts of the Refund Policy page.</p><h4 id="page-visibility" class="wp-block-heading">Page Visibility</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Show Refund Policy Page?</strong>: Use the toggle switch at the top to make the Refund Policy page visible or hidden on your live website.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-refund-policy-1024x577.webp" alt="Refund Policy" class="wp-image-9082" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-refund-policy-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-refund-policy-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-refund-policy-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-refund-policy-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-refund-policy.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h4 id="intro-section" class="wp-block-heading">Intro Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title and Sub-Title</strong>: Enter the main heading and subheading for the page.</li><li><strong>Intro Image/Banner</strong>: Upload a banner image.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Maximum size: 5 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: <strong>1:6</strong><strong><br></strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>Banner Overlay Color</strong>: Optionally, select a color overlay to improve readability of text placed over the banner image.<br></li></ul><h4 id="description-section" class="wp-block-heading">Description Section</h4><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Content</strong>: Use the Description field to write or paste the full text of your Refund Policy.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Save the Changes</h3><p>After completing your edits, scroll to the bottom of the page and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This action will publish the updates to your live website.</p><h2 id="seo-setting" class="wp-block-heading">SEO Setting</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Purpose</strong>: Manage SEO details for your website’s home page.</li><li><strong>Meta Title (Default)</strong>: Add a title that represents your brand.</li><li><strong>Meta Description (Default)</strong>: Write a short description for search engines.</li><li><strong>Meta Image</strong>: Upload an image to appear in search results and social shares.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li><li>Maximum size: 2 MB</li><li>Recommended ratio: 2:1</li></ul></li></ul><p>After completing your settings, click on <strong>Save Changes. </strong></p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-seo-settings-1024x576.webp" alt="SEO Settings" class="wp-image-9083" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-seo-settings-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-seo-settings-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-seo-settings-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-seo-settings-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-seo-settings.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p></p></div>',
