                67 => [
                    'id' => 68,
                    'doc_category_id' => 7,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-place-an-order-on-an-online-website-store-front',
                    'title' => 'How to Place an Order on an Online Website (Store Front)',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Menumium makes online ordering fast and convenient. With just a few clicks, customers can browse the menu, add their favorite dishes, and place orders for delivery or pickup.</p><h2 id="step-1-browse-the-menu-and-add-items" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Browse the Menu and Add Items</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Visit the restaurant’s website to access the full menu.</li><li>Browse categories such as <strong>Popular Dishes, Burgers &amp; Wraps, Pizzas,</strong> and more.</li><li>To add an item, click the <strong>Add</strong> button.</li><li>A pop-up window will appear with item details. Adjust the quantity using the <strong>(– / +)</strong> buttons.</li><li>Click <strong>Add to Cart</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/browse-the-menu-and-add-items-0a.webp" alt="Browse The Menu And Add Items
" class="wp-image-10842" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/browse-the-menu-and-add-items-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/browse-the-menu-and-add-items-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/browse-the-menu-and-add-items-0a-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-proceed-to-checkout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Proceed to Checkout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all items are in your cart, look at the <strong>Cart Summary</strong> on the right-hand side.</li><li>Click the <strong>Checkout</strong> button to continue.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-1024x579.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10164" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-1536x868.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-enter-personal-and-delivery-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Enter Personal and Delivery Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the checkout page, fill in your <strong>Name, Email, and Phone Number.</strong></li><li>Select a <strong>Delivery Type:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Home Delivery:</strong> Enter your delivery address.</li><li><strong>Take Away:</strong> Choose this option if you plan to pick up your order.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-personal-details-1024x581.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10166" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-personal-details-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-personal-details-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-personal-details-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-personal-details-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-personal-details.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-review-and-place-your-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Review and Place Your Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Check the <strong>Cart Summary</strong> to ensure all items and quantities are correct.</li><li>Apply a <strong>coupon code</strong> if available.</li><li>Click the <strong>Place Order</strong> button to complete your purchase.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-order-confirmation-invoice" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Order Confirmation &amp; Invoice</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After successful submission, a confirmation screen will display:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Your <strong>Order ID</strong></li><li>Expected <strong>delivery or pickup time</strong></li></ul></li><li>You can also download a <strong>PDF invoice</strong> by clicking <strong>Download Invoice.</strong></li></ul><p>Placing an online order with Menumium is simple—browse, customize, and checkout in just a few steps.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:40.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:40.000000Z',
                ],
                68 => [
                    'id' => 69,
                    'doc_category_id' => 7,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-apply-a-coupon-when-ordering-from-the-website',
                    'title' => 'How to Apply a Coupon When Ordering from the Website',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Customers can easily apply a coupon code during checkout to enjoy discounts on their orders. Follow the steps below to use a coupon when placing an order.</p><h2 id="step-1-add-items-to-your-cart" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Add Items to Your Cart</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Browse the restaurant’s menu.</li><li>Click the <strong>Add</strong> button next to the food item you want.</li><li>A pop-up will appear to adjust the <strong>quantity</strong>.</li><li>After selecting the quantity, click <strong>Add to Cart</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-proceed-to-checkout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Proceed to Checkout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all items are added, go to the <strong>Cart Summary</strong> (on the right side of the page).</li><li>Click the <strong>Checkout</strong> button to continue.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-1024x579.webp" alt="Website Order Online Cart Summary
" class="wp-image-10164" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary-1536x868.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-order-online-cart-summary.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-apply-the-coupon-code" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply the Coupon Code</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the checkout page, scroll to the <strong>Order Summary</strong> section.</li><li>Below it, click the <strong>Apply Coupon</strong> link.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-on-the-apply-coupon-from-checkout-1024x580.webp" alt="Click On The Apply Coupon From Checkout
" class="wp-image-10846" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-on-the-apply-coupon-from-checkout-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-on-the-apply-coupon-from-checkout-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-on-the-apply-coupon-from-checkout-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-on-the-apply-coupon-from-checkout-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-on-the-apply-coupon-from-checkout.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-enter-the-coupon-code" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Enter the Coupon Code</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up titled <strong>Available Coupon</strong> will appear.</li><li>Enter your coupon code in the text box.</li><li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li><li>If valid, the discount will be applied, and you will see the reduced total amount.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-online-order-apply-coupon-1024x576.webp" alt="Website Online Order Apply Coupon" class="wp-image-10170" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-online-order-apply-coupon-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-online-order-apply-coupon-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-online-order-apply-coupon-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-online-order-apply-coupon-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/website-online-order-apply-coupon.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-place-your-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Place Your Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Review your order details, including delivery type and personal information.</li><li>Once confirmed, click the <strong>Place Order</strong> button to finalize your purchase.</li></ul><p>The coupon is now successfully applied, and your discount is included in the final bill.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:41.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:41.000000Z',
                ],
                69 => [
                    'id' => 70,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-select-a-qr-menu-template-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Select a QR Menu Template in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of selecting a QR menu template within the Menumium dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium account.</li><li>From the main dashboard, go to <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong> in the left-hand navigation menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>This will open the QR Menu setup page.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-choose-qr-code-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Choose QR Code Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the QR Menu Setup page, scroll down to the <strong>Choose QR Code Layout</strong> section.</li><li>You will see a selection of available templates.</li><li>The options include <strong>Default, Medium, and Standard</strong>, each with its own design and description.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-qr-code-layout-1024x579.webp" alt="Choose QR Code Layout" class="wp-image-9608" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-qr-code-layout-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-qr-code-layout-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-qr-code-layout-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-qr-code-layout-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-choose-qr-code-layout.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-preview-and-select-a-template" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Preview and Select a Template</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Hover over the template you want to preview and click <strong>Preview</strong> to see a larger view.</li><li>Once you have chosen the template you prefer, click <strong>Use This Layout</strong> under the template image.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, and your selected template will be applied.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hover-over-qr-template-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Hover Over QR Template" class="wp-image-10936" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hover-over-qr-template-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hover-over-qr-template-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hover-over-qr-template-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hover-over-qr-template-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/hover-over-qr-template-0a.webp 1900w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your QR menu template is now selected and ready to customize with your restaurant branding.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:42.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:42.000000Z',
                ],
                70 => [
                    'id' => 71,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-the-front-layout-of-qr-menu',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit the Front Layout of QR Menu',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of editing the front design of your Menumium QR menu. You can customize the background, colors, logo, and text to align with your restaurant’s branding.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium dashboard.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-a-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select a Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>You will see available layout options: <strong>Default, Medium, and Standard</strong>.</li><li>Review the options and click <strong>Use This Layout</strong> under your preferred design.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-use-this-layout-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Click Use This Layout" class="wp-image-10940" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-use-this-layout-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-use-this-layout-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-use-this-layout-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-use-this-layout-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/click-use-this-layout-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-customize-the-front-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Customize the Front Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After selecting a layout, the <strong>QR Card Design editor</strong> will open.</li><li>Click on the <strong>Front Layout</strong> tab to begin editing.</li><li>Customize the following elements (This is for the Standard Layout):</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Front Layout Customize" class="wp-image-10966" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="background-image" class="wp-block-heading">Background Image</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Upload an image (PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP | Max 10 MB).</li></ul><h3 id="color-style" class="wp-block-heading">Color Style</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Background Color: Choose a background color.</li><li>Top Section Color: Adjust the top section color.</li><li>Font Color: Change the font color.</li></ul><h3 id="logo" class="wp-block-heading">Logo</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle <strong>Show Logo</strong> on or off.</li><li>Select <strong>Use Business Logo</strong> or upload a new one (PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP | Max 2 MB | Ratio 4:1).</li></ul><h3 id="title-sub-title" class="wp-block-heading">Title &amp; Sub-Title</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle <strong>Show Title &amp; Sub-Title</strong> on or off.</li><li>Enter your menu title and subtitle text.</li></ul><h3 id="contact-section" class="wp-block-heading">Contact Section</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle <strong>Show Contact Section</strong> on or off.</li><li>Choose the <strong>Support Number Type</strong> (Phone, Telephone, Hotline).</li><li>Enter your <strong>contact number</strong> and <strong>email address</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save Your Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>When you finish customizing, click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation message, <strong>“Data saved successfully!”</strong> will appear.</li><li>Your QR menu front layout is now updated.</li></ul><p>You’ve successfully customized the front layout of your QR menu. You can see the preview on the right side of the window</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:42.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:42.000000Z',
                ],
                71 => [
                    'id' => 72,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-the-back-layout-of-a-qr-menu',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit the Back Layout of a QR Menu',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will help you customize the back layout of your QR menu in Menumium. The back layout appears when users scan your QR code, allowing you to add branding and extra details.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium dashboard.</li><li>From the left-hand navigation menu, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-qr-card-design" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the QR Card Design</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the QR Menu Setup page, locate the layout you previously selected for editing your front layout.</li><li>Click <strong>Edit Layout</strong> to open the QR Card Design editor.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Edit Layout Button Click" class="wp-image-10948" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-go-to-the-back-layout-tab" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Go to the Back Layout Tab</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the QR Card Design editor, you will see multiple tabs.</li><li>Click on <strong>Back Layout</strong> to start customizing the reverse side of your QR menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Back Layout Customize" class="wp-image-10967" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-customize-the-background" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Customize the Background</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Background Image</strong>: Upload an image (PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP | Max 10 MB). Drag and drop or browse your computer.</li><li><strong>Background Color</strong>: Alternatively, select a solid color using the color picker.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-edit-text-and-logo" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Edit Text and Logo</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Font Color</strong>: Adjust the font color to ensure visibility against your chosen background.</li><li><strong>Logo</strong>: Toggle the option to show or hide your business logo. You can upload a new logo or use your saved business logo.</li><li><strong>Title</strong>: Enter or update the back layout title (e.g., <em>Order Now</em>).</li></ul><h2 id="step-6-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save Your Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After customizing, click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong> at the bottom of the page.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, and your back layout will be updated.</li></ul><p>Your QR menu back layout is now customized. Customers will see your branding and message when they scan your QR code.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:43.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:43.000000Z',
                ],
                72 => [
                    'id' => 73,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-add-your-menu-to-a-qr-code',
                    'title' => 'How to Add Your Menu to a QR Code',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will help you add your restaurant’s menu to a QR code in Menumium, so customers can instantly view it by scanning the code.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium dashboard.</li><li>From the left-hand navigation menu, click on  <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will open the QR code configuration page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-choose-your-qr-code-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Choose Your QR Code Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the QR Menu Setup page, you will see pre-designed layout options such as <strong>Default, Medium, and Standard</strong>.</li><li>Select the layout that fits your brand style.</li><li>Click <strong>Edit Layout</strong> to open the customization editor.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Edit Layout Button Click" class="wp-image-10948" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-add-your-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Add Your Menu</h2><p>Within the layout editor, click on the <strong>Menu</strong> tab. You have three options for how your menu will appear:</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-menu-customize-1024x580.webp" alt="Menu Customize" class="wp-image-9611" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-menu-customize-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-menu-customize-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-menu-customize-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-menu-customize-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-menu-customize.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="option-1-upload-your-own-pdf" class="wp-block-heading">Option 1: Upload Your Own PDF</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Upload Your PDF</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>Browse</strong> to upload your pre-designed PDF menu.</li><li>Customers scanning the QR code will see this PDF.</li></ul><h3 id="option-2-use-system-pdf" class="wp-block-heading">Option 2: Use System PDF</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Use System PDF</strong> to automatically generate a digital PDF menu from the food items you set up in Menumium.</li><li>Choose your preferred <strong>Menu Layout</strong>.</li><li>Toggle the <strong>Contact Section</strong> (Phone, Telephone, Hotlines, Email) on or off as needed.</li></ul><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>Food items must already be set up in the system for this option to work. See the tutorial here: <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/food-management/">How to Set Up Food in Menumium</a>.</p></div></div><h3 id="option-3-open-as-website" class="wp-block-heading">Option 3: Open as Website</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Open in Website</strong> to show your interactive menu as a webpage.</li><li>Upload your business logo (or use an existing one).</li><li>Choose a <strong>website theme color</strong> that matches your branding.</li></ul><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>Food items must already be set up in the system for this option to work. See the tutorial here: <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/food-management/">How to Set Up Food in Menumium</a>.</p></div></div><h2 id="step-4-preview-and-save" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Preview and Save</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the right-hand side, you will see a live <strong>preview</strong> of your QR menu.</li><li>Review the design and layout.</li><li>Once satisfied, click <strong>Save</strong> to finalize your changes.</li></ul><p>Your QR code is now linked to your menu. Customers can scan it to view your PDF, digital system menu, or interactive website menu instantly.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:44.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:44.000000Z',
                ],
                73 => [
                    'id' => 74,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-customize-your-qr-menu-url',
                    'title' => 'How to Customize Your QR Menu URL',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Menumium allows you to personalize the URL of your digital menu. This makes it easier for customers to remember and strengthens your restaurant’s branding.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your Menumium dashboard, click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>This will open the QR Menu Setup page, where you can manage the design and functionality of your QR code.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-choose-your-qr-code-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Choose Your QR Code Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the QR Menu Setup page, scroll to the <strong>Choose QR Code Layout</strong> section.</li><li>Select your preferred layout (Default, Medium, or Standard).</li><li>Click <strong>Edit Layout</strong> to proceed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Edit Layout Button Click" class="wp-image-10948" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-layout-button-click-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-open-the-qr-url-tab" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Open the QR URL Tab</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After clicking <strong>Edit Layout</strong>, you will see four tabs: <strong>Front Layout, Back Layout, Menu,</strong> and <strong>QR URL</strong>.</li><li>Click on the <strong>QR URL</strong> tab to access your menu’s web address settings.</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-edit-your-subdomain" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Edit Your Subdomain</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the QR URL tab, locate the section <strong>Edit Sub Domain for Your Website</strong>.</li><li>The first field shows the fixed part of your URL:<br>https://qr.menumium.com/</li><li>In the second field, type your desired subdomain (e.g., restaurant-name).</li><li>The <strong>URL Preview</strong> below will update automatically to show the full link.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="QR URL Customize" class="wp-image-10969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-and-finalize" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save and Finalize</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once you are happy with your custom URL, click the green <strong>Save</strong> button.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear: <em>“Data was created successfully.”</em></li><li>Your QR code is now updated and will direct customers to your new personalized URL.</li></ul><p>With your custom subdomain set, customers can easily access your digital menu with a branded and memorable link.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:45.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:45.000000Z',
                ],
                74 => [
                    'id' => 75,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-preview-the-qr-menu',
                    'title' => 'How to Preview the QR Menu',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to preview your QR menu in Menumium before finalizing or printing it. The preview lets you see exactly how the design will appear to customers, ensuring everything matches your brand.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A registered Menumium account.</li><li>An active menu set up on your account.</li><li>A QR menu already created and customized.</li></ul><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your Menumium dashboard, look at the left-hand navigation panel.</li><li>Click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong> to open the configuration page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-preview-option" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Preview Option</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>At the top of the QR Menu Setup page, you’ll see the layout you selected for your QR menu.</li><li>Click the <strong>Preview</strong> button to open a preview window.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-preview-qr-1024x581.webp" alt="Preview QR" class="wp-image-9613" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-preview-qr-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-preview-qr-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-preview-qr-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-preview-qr-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-preview-qr.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-review-the-qr-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Review the QR Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A new pop-up window will display the QR menu design.</li><li>The preview shows two sections:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Front Layout</strong>: Displays the QR code and restaurant name.</li><li><strong>Back Layout</strong>: Typically shows a tagline, contact info, or brand message.</li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="step-4-finalize-or-edit-the-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Finalize or Edit the Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After reviewing, you can:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Print</strong> (top-right corner) to print your QR code card.</li><li>Or click <strong>Edit Layout</strong> (bottom of the pop-up) to return and make design changes.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-print-or-edit-from-qr-preview-1024x582.webp" alt="Print Or Edit From QR Preview" class="wp-image-9614" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-print-or-edit-from-qr-preview-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-print-or-edit-from-qr-preview-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-print-or-edit-from-qr-preview-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-print-or-edit-from-qr-preview-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-print-or-edit-from-qr-preview.webp 1898w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Previewing ensures your QR menu is polished and customer-ready before you share or print it.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:46.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:46.000000Z',
                ],
                75 => [
                    'id' => 76,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-view-the-qr-menu-website',
                    'title' => 'How to View the QR Menu Website',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to access your live QR menu website directly from the Menumium dashboard. Viewing the live menu allows you to confirm that your categories, food items, and design appear correctly to customers.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A registered Menumium account.</li><li>An active menu set up on your account.</li><li>A QR menu already created and customized.</li></ul><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your Menumium dashboard, open the left-hand navigation panel.</li><li>Click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong> to open the QR menu configuration page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-qr-menu-website" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the QR Menu Website</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>At the top of the QR Menu Setup page, locate the <strong>Visit QR Menu</strong> button (beside the <strong>Print</strong> and <strong>Preview</strong> buttons).</li><li>Click <strong>Visit QR Menu</strong>. Your live QR menu website will open in a new browser tab.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-visit-qr-menu-button-1024x579.webp" alt="Visit QR Menu Button" class="wp-image-9615" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-visit-qr-menu-button-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-visit-qr-menu-button-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-visit-qr-menu-button-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-visit-qr-menu-button-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-visit-qr-menu-button.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-a-branch-if-applicable" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select a Branch (If Applicable)</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>If your restaurant has multiple branches, a pop-up window titled <strong>Select a Branch to Continue</strong> will appear.</li><li>Choose the branch you want to view from the list.</li><li>Click <strong>Continue</strong> to proceed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-visit-qr-menu-select-a-branch-1024x576.webp" alt="Visit QR Menu Select A Branch" class="wp-image-9616" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-visit-qr-menu-select-a-branch-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-visit-qr-menu-select-a-branch-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-visit-qr-menu-select-a-branch-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-visit-qr-menu-select-a-branch-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-visit-qr-menu-select-a-branch.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-view-your-live-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View Your Live Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Your digital menu will now load in the browser.</li><li>You can browse categories, food items, descriptions, and prices exactly as a customer would.</li><li>Use this view to confirm that everything is displayed correctly and professionally.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-visit-qr-menu-view-1024x582.webp" alt="Visit QR Menu View" class="wp-image-9617" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-visit-qr-menu-view-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-visit-qr-menu-view-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-visit-qr-menu-view-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-visit-qr-menu-view-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-visit-qr-menu-view.webp 1900w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By following these steps, you can quickly access and verify your live QR menu website, ensuring a smooth customer experience.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:47.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:47.000000Z',
                ],
                76 => [
                    'id' => 77,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-print-a-qr-menu',
                    'title' => 'How to Print a QR Menu',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to print your QR menu directly from the Menumium dashboard. Printed QR menus can be placed on tables, entrances, or included with takeout orders, giving customers quick access to your digital menu.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A registered Menumium account.</li><li>An active menu set up on your account.</li><li>A QR menu already created and customized.</li></ul><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-qr-menu-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to QR Menu Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your Menumium dashboard, open the left-hand navigation panel.</li><li>Click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup</strong> to open the QR menu configuration page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-print-button" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Print Button</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>At the top of the QR Menu Setup page, locate the <strong>Print</strong> button (beside the <strong>Visit QR Menu</strong> button).</li><li>Click on <strong>Print</strong>. A print preview window will open, displaying your QR menu design.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-qr-menu-print-1024x580.webp" alt="QR Menu Print" class="wp-image-9618" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-qr-menu-print-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-qr-menu-print-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-qr-menu-print-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-qr-menu-print-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-qr-menu-print.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-adjust-print-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Adjust Print Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the print dialog, adjust settings such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Destination</strong> (printer or Save as PDF)</li><li><strong>Paper Size</strong></li><li><strong>Pages</strong></li><li><strong>Color Options</strong></li></ul></li><li>Review the preview to ensure the layout looks correct.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-menu-print-popup-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="QR Menu Print Popup" class="wp-image-10962" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-menu-print-popup-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-menu-print-popup-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-menu-print-popup-0a-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-menu-print-popup-0a-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-menu-print-popup-0a.webp 1908w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-finalize-printing" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Finalize Printing</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After adjusting the settings, click <strong>Print</strong>.</li><li>Your QR menu will be sent to the selected printer or saved as a PDF file.</li><li>The menu is now ready to be displayed at your restaurant.</li></ul><p>By following these steps, you can easily print professional QR menus that enhance customer convenience and your restaurant’s branding.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 8,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:48.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:48.000000Z',
                ],
                77 => [
                    'id' => 78,
                    'doc_category_id' => 8,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-turn-a-pdf-menu-into-a-qr-menu',
                    'title' => 'How to Turn a PDF Menu into a QR Menu',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through converting a PDF menu into a scannable QR menu using the Menumium platform. Customers can then instantly access your digital menu by scanning the QR code with their smartphone.</p><h2 id="step-1-set-up-your-qr-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Set Up Your QR Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log into your Menumium dashboard.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Restaurant Management &gt;</strong> <strong>QR Menu Setup.</strong></li><li>This will take you to the QR Menu setup page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate To QR Menu Section" class="wp-image-10935" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-qr-menu-section-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-choose-a-qr-code-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Choose a QR Code Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the QR Menu Setup page, scroll down to the available templates.</li><li>Choose a layout that fits your branding (e.g., Default, Medium, Standard).</li><li>Click <strong>Use This Layout</strong> to apply it.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-customize-the-front-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Customize the Front Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the edit page, select the <strong>Front Layout</strong> tab.</li><li>Configure the following:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Background Image</strong> – Upload a PNG, JPG, JPEG, or WEBP (Max 10 MB).</li><li><strong>Color Style</strong> – Set background, top section, and font colors.</li><li><strong>Logo</strong> – Upload your restaurant logo (PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP | Max 2 MB | Ratio 4:1).</li><li><strong>Title &amp; Sub-Title</strong> – Enter your restaurant name and tagline.</li><li><strong>Contact Section</strong> – Toggle ON and add contact number and/or email.</li></ul></li><li>Click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong> when done.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Front Layout Customize" class="wp-image-10966" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/front-layout-customize-0a.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-customize-the-back-layout" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Customize the Back Layout</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the <strong>Back Layout</strong> tab.</li><li>Configure the following:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Background Image</strong> – Upload a supporting image.</li><li><strong>Color Style</strong> – Adjust font and background colors.</li><li><strong>Logo</strong> – Upload or toggle the business logo.</li><li><strong>Title</strong> – Toggle ON and add text (e.g., “Order Now”).</li></ul></li><li>Click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Back Layout Customize" class="wp-image-10967" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/back-layout-customize-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-5-upload-the-pdf-menu" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 5: Upload the PDF Menu</strong></h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Menu</strong> tab.</li><li>You will get three options to choose from:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Upload Your PDF</strong> – Drag and drop or browse to upload your existing menu file.</li><li><strong>Use System PDF</strong> – Generate a menu from Menumium’s food setup.</li><li><strong>Open Menu as Website</strong> – Display an interactive menu webpage.</li></ul></li><li>Select <strong>Upload Your PDF</strong>, preview it on the right, then click <strong>Save</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/turn-pdf-menu-into-qr-menu-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Turn PDF Menu Into QR Menu" class="wp-image-10968" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/turn-pdf-menu-into-qr-menu-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/turn-pdf-menu-into-qr-menu-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/turn-pdf-menu-into-qr-menu-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/turn-pdf-menu-into-qr-menu-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/turn-pdf-menu-into-qr-menu-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-customize-the-qr-url" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Customize the QR URL</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Open the <strong>QR URL</strong> tab.</li><li>Edit the subdomain to create a personalized link (e.g., https://qr.menumium.com/munchbox).</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="QR URL Customize" class="wp-image-10969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/qr-url-customize-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-finalize-and-distribute" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Finalize and Distribute</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the QR Menu Setup page, click <strong>Print</strong> to generate a printable version of your QR code.</li><li>Place the printed QR menus on tables, entrances, or packaging.</li><li>Customers can scan the QR or visit the custom URL to access your PDF menu.</li></ul><p>Your QR menu is now live! This makes it easier for customers to access your restaurant’s menu digitally, while giving your brand a professional and modern touch.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 9,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:49.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:49.000000Z',
                ],
                78 => [
                    'id' => 79,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-a-new-coupon-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Create a New Coupon in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to set up a new coupon in Menumium, from entering basic details to configuring discounts and advanced rules.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-coupon-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Coupon Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Promotion Management, </strong>then <strong>Coupon</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The Coupon Section" class="wp-image-11053" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-add-new-coupon-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Add New Coupon Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under the Coupon menu, click <strong>Add New Coupon</strong>.</li><li>The system will load the coupon creation form.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-the-add-new-coupon-page-0a.webp" alt="Access The Add New Coupon Page" class="wp-image-11058" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-the-add-new-coupon-page-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-the-add-new-coupon-page-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-the-add-new-coupon-page-0a-768x437.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-in-basic-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill in Basic Information</h2><p>In the <strong>Setup Basic Info</strong> section:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Coupon Title</strong> – Enter a descriptive name (e.g., Summer Sale, Winter Special).</li><li><strong>Coupon Code</strong> – The system generates one automatically. Click <strong>Generate Code</strong> to create a new one. You can also use manual code.</li><li><strong>Maximum Usage</strong> – Specify the number of times a coupon can be used per customer, or tick <strong>Unlimited Usage</strong> for no restrictions.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-add-new-coupon-1024x581.webp" alt="Add New Coupon" class="wp-image-9423" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-add-new-coupon-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-add-new-coupon-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-add-new-coupon-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-add-new-coupon-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-add-new-coupon.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-the-discount" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure the Discount</h2><p>In the <strong>Discount Setup</strong> section:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Discount Type</strong> – Select from:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Discount on Purchase</li><li>First Order</li><li>Free Item with Purchase</li><li>Free Delivery</li></ul></li><li><strong>Discount Amount %</strong> – Enter the percentage discount.</li><li><strong>Max. Amount</strong> – Set the maximum discount allowed.</li><li><strong>Validity</strong> – Define start and end dates using the calendar or tick <strong>Assign this offer permanently</strong> for no expiry.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-coupon-discount-type-1024x579.webp" alt="Coupon Discount Type" class="wp-image-9424" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-coupon-discount-type-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-coupon-discount-type-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-coupon-discount-type-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-coupon-discount-type-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-coupon-discount-type.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-define-advanced-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Define Advanced Settings</h2><p>Expand the <strong>Advance Settings</strong> section for more rules:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Targeted Customers</strong> –<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Default: Applies to all customers.</li><li>Toggle ON to limit by customer, then select specific users by <strong>name, ID, or phone number</strong>.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Minimum Order Value</strong> – Toggle ON and set the minimum amount required to apply the coupon.</li><li><strong>Order Type</strong> – Choose where the coupon applies: Dine-In, Takeaway, or Home Delivery (multiple can be selected).</li><li><strong>Specific Branch</strong> – Toggle ON to restrict coupon availability to selected branches. By default, promotions apply to <strong>all branches</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-coupon-advanced-setting-1024x580.webp" alt="Coupon Advanced Setting" class="wp-image-9425" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-coupon-advanced-setting-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-coupon-advanced-setting-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-coupon-advanced-setting-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-coupon-advanced-setting-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-coupon-advanced-setting.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-the-coupon" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save the Coupon</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all settings are configured, click <strong>Save</strong> (top-right).</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, and your coupon will be activated.</li></ul><p>With these steps, you can create customized coupons in Menumium to attract customers, drive sales, and reward loyalty.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:51.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:51.000000Z',
                ],
                79 => [
                    'id' => 80,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-a-coupon-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit a Coupon in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to update the details of an existing coupon in the Menumium dashboard, including discount setup, validity, and advanced settings.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-coupon-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Coupon Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Promotion Management </strong>&gt; <strong>Coupon</strong> to access the main coupon management page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The Coupon Section" class="wp-image-11053" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-coupon-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Coupon List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>Coupon List</strong> page will display all active and inactive coupons.</li><li>Each entry includes coupon details and available actions.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-select-and-edit-a-coupon" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select and Edit a Coupon</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column of the desired coupon, click the <strong>Three-dot menu (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-coupon-edit-dropdown-1024x577.webp" alt="Coupon Edit Dropdown" class="wp-image-9426" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-coupon-edit-dropdown-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-coupon-edit-dropdown-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-coupon-edit-dropdown-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-coupon-edit-dropdown-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-coupon-edit-dropdown.webp 1914w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-modify-coupon-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Modify Coupon Details</h2><p>On the <strong>Update Coupon</strong> page, update the following fields as needed:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Coupon Title &amp; Code</strong> – Edit the name or coupon code.</li><li><strong>Discount Setup</strong> – Adjust discount type, amount (percentage or fixed), and maximum value.</li><li><strong>Validity</strong> – Change the start and end dates or set it as permanent.</li><li><strong>Advanced Settings</strong> – Update targeted customers, minimum order value, order types, or branch availability.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-coupon-details-0a.webp" alt="Modify Coupon Details" class="wp-image-11063" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-coupon-details-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-coupon-details-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-coupon-details-0a-768x434.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save Your Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once edits are complete, click <strong>Save</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, and you will be redirected back to the <strong>Coupon List</strong>.</li></ul><p>With these steps, you can efficiently modify coupons in Menumium to keep your promotions accurate and up to date.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:52.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:52.000000Z',
                ],
                80 => [
                    'id' => 81,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-turn-a-coupon-on-or-off-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Turn a Coupon On or Off in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to instantly activate or deactivate a coupon in Menumium. Turning a coupon <strong>On</strong> makes it available for customer use, while turning it <strong>Off</strong> disables it without deleting it.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-coupon-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Coupon List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Promotion Management</strong> → <strong>Coupon</strong>.</li><li>The <strong>Coupon List</strong> page will display all available coupons.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The Coupon Section" class="wp-image-11053" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-change-the-coupon-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Change the Coupon Status</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Coupon List</strong> table, locate the coupon you want to manage.</li><li>Find the <strong>Status</strong> column for that coupon.</li><li>Use the <strong>toggle switch</strong> to update the status:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>On</strong> → Coupon is <strong>active</strong> and redeemable by customers.</li><li><strong>Off</strong> → Coupon is <strong>inactive</strong> and cannot be used.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-coupon-status-1024x576.webp" alt="Coupon Status" class="wp-image-9427" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-coupon-status-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-coupon-status-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-coupon-status-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-coupon-status-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-coupon-status.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-confirm-the-action" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Confirm the Action</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After toggling the status, a confirmation pop-up will appear.</li><li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong> to finalize the change.</li><li>A success message will appear at the bottom of your screen:<br><em>“Coupon status was updated successfully.”</em></li></ul><p>You can repeat this process anytime to quickly enable or disable coupons as needed, without permanently removing them.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:52.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:52.000000Z',
                ],
                81 => [
                    'id' => 82,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-delete-a-coupon-from-promotion-management',
                    'title' => 'How to Delete a Coupon from Promotion Management',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This documentation outlines the steps to delete an existing coupon from the promotion management section of the dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-promotion-management" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 1: Navigate to Promotion Management</strong></h2><p>From the main dashboard, go to the <strong>Promotion Management</strong> section on the left-hand sidebar.</p><h2 id="step-2-access-coupon-list" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 2: Access Coupon List</strong></h2><p>In the Promotion Management submenu, click on <strong>Coupon</strong> and then select <strong>Coupon List</strong>. This will display a list of all existing coupons.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The Coupon Section" class="wp-image-11053" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-coupon-section-0a-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-find-the-coupon-to-delete" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 3: Find the Coupon to Delete</strong></h2><p>Scroll through the list to find the coupon you wish to delete.</p><h2 id="step-4-delete-the-coupon" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 4: Delete the Coupon</strong></h2><p>Locate the three-dot menu on the right side of the coupon’s entry. Click on it, and a dropdown menu will appear. Select <strong>Move to Trash</strong>.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-coupon-delete-1024x576.webp" alt="Coupon Delete" class="wp-image-9428" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-coupon-delete-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-coupon-delete-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-coupon-delete-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-coupon-delete-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-coupon-delete.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-confirm-deletion" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 5: Confirm Deletion</strong></h2><p>A confirmation window will pop up. Click <strong>Trash</strong> to confirm that you want to delete the coupon. The coupon will now be inactive and removed from the active list.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:53.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:53.000000Z',
                ],
                82 => [
                    'id' => 83,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-a-bogo-offer-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Create a BOGO Offer in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>A <strong>Buy One, Get One (BOGO)</strong> offer allows you to set up promotions where a customer receives a free item when they purchase a specific item.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><p><em>Before creating a BOGO offer, ensure that all food items you plan to include are already added to your system under </em><strong><em>Food Management</em></strong><em>. This ensures they are available for selection during setup.</em></p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the BOGO Offer Section</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>dashboard</strong>, click <strong>Promotion Management</strong> &gt; <strong>BOGO Offer</strong> in the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click <strong>Add New BOGO Offer</strong> to begin creating a new promotion.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/image-5-1024x579.png" alt="" class="wp-image-11074"></figure><h2 id="step-2-fill-out-the-offer-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Fill Out the Offer Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>BOGO Offer Title</strong> – Enter a descriptive name (e.g., <em>Buy 1 Get 1 Burger</em>).</li><li><strong>BOGO Offer Type</strong> – Select the type of deal (e.g., <em>Buy X Get Y Free Deal</em>).</li><li><strong>Validation Date</strong> – Set the start and end dates for the offer, or select <strong>Assign this offer permanently</strong> for no expiry.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-add-BOGO-offer-1024x581.webp" alt="Add BOGO Offer" class="wp-image-9429" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-add-BOGO-offer-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-add-BOGO-offer-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-add-BOGO-offer-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-add-BOGO-offer-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-add-BOGO-offer.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-define-the-buy-food-items" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Define the “Buy” Food Items</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Buy Food</strong> section, choose the item(s) customers must purchase.</li><li>Search for items by name or keyword.</li><li>Use the <strong>+ / –</strong> buttons to set the required quantity.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Example: <em>1 × Classic Cheeseburger</em></li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-BOGO-Buy-food-1024x583.webp" alt="BOGO Buy Food" class="wp-image-9430" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-BOGO-Buy-food-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-BOGO-Buy-food-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-BOGO-Buy-food-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-BOGO-Buy-food-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-BOGO-Buy-food.webp 1895w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-define-the-get-food-items" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Define the “Get” Food Items</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Get Food</strong> section, choose the free item(s) customers will receive.</li><li>Search for items by name or keyword.</li><li>Adjust the free item’s quantity.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Example: <em>1 × Choco Lava Shake</em>.</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-BOGO-Get-food-1024x581.webp" alt="BOGO Get Food" class="wp-image-9431" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-BOGO-Get-food-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-BOGO-Get-food-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-BOGO-Get-food-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-BOGO-Get-food-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-BOGO-Get-food.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-set-offer-availability" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set Offer Availability</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Order Type</strong> – Select where the offer applies:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Dine-In</li><li>Take Away</li><li>Home Delivery</li></ul></li><li><strong>Specific Branch</strong> – Toggle ON if the offer should apply only to certain branches.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the desired branches from the list.</li><li>By default, this promotion applies to <strong>all branches</strong></li></ul></li><li>Click the green <strong>Save</strong> button to activate the BOGO offer.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-BOGO-offer-availability-1024x581.webp" alt="BOGO Offer Availability" class="wp-image-9432" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-BOGO-offer-availability-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-BOGO-offer-availability-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-BOGO-offer-availability-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-BOGO-offer-availability-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-BOGO-offer-availability.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your BOGO promotion is now live, and customers can redeem it according to your configured rules.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:54.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:54.000000Z',
                ],
                83 => [
                    'id' => 84,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-and-manage-a-bogo-offer',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up and Manage a BOGO Offer',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p><strong>BOGO</strong> stands for <strong>Buy One, Get One</strong>, a common promotional offer used to attract customers and increase sales. This guide explains how to view, edit, and manage BOGO offers within the Menumium platform.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-bogo-offer-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the BOGO Offer Section</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>Promotion Management</strong>.</li><li>Under this section, select <strong>BOGO Offer</strong>.</li><li>Then, click <strong>BOGO Offer List</strong> to see all existing BOGO offers.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The BOGO Offer Section" class="wp-image-11075" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a-768x434.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-view-an-existing-bogo-offer" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: View an Existing BOGO Offer</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>BOGO Offer List</strong> page, locate the offer you want to review.</li><li>Click the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong> on the right-hand side of the entry.</li><li>Select <strong>View Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-BOGO-offer-view-details-1024x578.webp" alt="BOGO Offer View Details" class="wp-image-9433" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-BOGO-offer-view-details-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-BOGO-offer-view-details-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-BOGO-offer-view-details-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-BOGO-offer-view-details-1536x867.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-BOGO-offer-view-details.webp 1912w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The next page will display the full setup of the offer, including:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Offer Title</li><li>Offer Type</li><li>Validity</li><li>Food Items and other configurations</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-view-details-page-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="BOGO Offer View Details Page" class="wp-image-11079" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-view-details-page-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-view-details-page-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-view-details-page-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-view-details-page-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-view-details-page-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-edit-an-existing-bogo-offer" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Edit an Existing BOGO Offer</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>BOGO Offer List</strong> page, locate the offer you want to review.</li><li>Click the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong> on the right-hand side of the entry.</li><li>Select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-BOGO-offer-edit-details-drop-down-1024x576.webp" alt="BOGO Offer Edit Details Dropdown" class="wp-image-9434" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-BOGO-offer-edit-details-drop-down-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-BOGO-offer-edit-details-drop-down-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-BOGO-offer-edit-details-drop-down-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-BOGO-offer-edit-details-drop-down-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-BOGO-offer-edit-details-drop-down.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Edit Details</strong> page, adjust the necessary fields (e.g., title, type, items, or availability)</li><li>Scroll up the page and click the <strong>Update</strong> button.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, confirming that the offer has been updated successfully.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-edit-details-page-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="BOGO Edit Details Page" class="wp-image-11081" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-edit-details-page-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-edit-details-page-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-edit-details-page-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-edit-details-page-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-edit-details-page-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:55.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:55.000000Z',
