                84 => [
                    'id' => 85,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-enable-or-disable-a-bogo-offer',
                    'title' => 'How to Enable or Disable a BOGO Offer',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to quickly activate or deactivate an existing <strong>Buy One, Get One (BOGO)</strong> offer in Menumium. Turning an offer <strong>On</strong> makes it available to customers, while turning it <strong>Off</strong> pauses the promotion without deleting it.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the BOGO Offer Section</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>dashboard</strong>, click on <strong>Promotion Management</strong> in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Select <strong>BOGO Offer</strong> from the dropdown.</li><li>Click on <strong>BOGO Offer List</strong> to view all active and inactive BOGO offers.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The BOGO Offer Section" class="wp-image-11075" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a-768x434.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-locate-the-desired-bogo-offer" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Locate the Desired BOGO Offer</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>BOGO Offer List</strong> page, find the specific offer you want to manage.</li><li>Offers are displayed in a table format with details such as title, type, and status.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-toggle-the-bogo-offer-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Toggle the BOGO Offer Status</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Status</strong> column, locate the toggle switch for the chosen offer.</li><li><strong>Blue toggle</strong> → The offer is <strong>Active</strong>.</li><li><strong>Grey toggle</strong> → The offer is <strong>Inactive</strong>.</li><li>Click the toggle to change the status.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-BOGO-offer-status-1024x576.webp" alt="BOGO Offer Status" class="wp-image-9435" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-BOGO-offer-status-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-BOGO-offer-status-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-BOGO-offer-status-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-BOGO-offer-status-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-BOGO-offer-status.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-confirm-the-change" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Confirm the Change</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation pop-up will appear, asking if you want to enable or disable the offer.</li><li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong> to proceed.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-verification" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Verification</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A success message will appear at the bottom of the screen:<br><em>“BOGO Offer Status Updated Successfully.”</em></li><li>The toggle switch will update to reflect the new status (blue for active, grey for inactive).</li></ul><p>With these steps, you can easily manage the availability of your BOGO offers, turning promotions on or off as needed without permanently removing them.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:55.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:55.000000Z',
                ],
                85 => [
                    'id' => 86,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-delete-a-bogo-offer-from-promotion-management',
                    'title' => 'How to Delete a BOGO Offer from Promotion Management',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to delete a âBuy One, Get Oneâ (BOGO) offer from your Menumium promotion management section.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-promotions-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Promotions Management</h2><p>From your Menumium dashboard, go to the left-hand menu and click on <strong>Promotion Management</strong>.</p><h2 id="step-2-access-the-bogo-offer-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the BOGO Offer List</h2><p>In the Promotion Management menu, select <strong>BOGO Offer</strong>.<br>This will open the <strong>BOGO Offer List</strong> page, showing all active BOGO promotions.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a.webp" alt="Navigate To The BOGO Offer Section" class="wp-image-11075" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-the-bogo-offer-section-0a-768x434.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-find-the-bogo-offer-to-delete" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Find the BOGO Offer to Delete</h2><p>Browse the list and locate the BOGO offer you want to remove.</p><h2 id="step-4-delete-the-offer" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Delete the Offer</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the right-hand side of the offer row, click the <strong>three-dot (â®) Action menu</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Move to Trash</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-confirm-deletion" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Confirm Deletion</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation pop-up will appear.</li><li>Click <strong>Move to Trash</strong> again to confirm.</li><li>The selected BOGO offer will now be deleted from your active promotions.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-delete-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-11089" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-delete-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-delete-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-delete-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-delete-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bogo-offer-delete-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your BOGO offer has been successfully removed from Promotion Management.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 8,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:56.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:56.000000Z',
                ],
                86 => [
                    'id' => 87,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-a-happy-hour-discount',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up a Happy Hour Discount',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Happy Hour</strong> feature in Menumium allows you to create time-based promotions that automatically apply discounts during off-peak hours. This helps attract more customers and increase sales during slower periods.</p><h2 id="step-1-activate-the-happy-hour-promotion" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Activate the Happy Hour Promotion</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click <strong>Promotion Management </strong>&gt;<strong>  Happy Hour</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Happy Hour Navigation" class="wp-image-11097" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>At the top of the page, find the toggle switch labeled <strong>“Do you want to activate the happy hour promotion?”</strong></li><li>Switch it <strong>On</strong>. The toggle will change color to confirm activation.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-add-Happy-Hour-1024x580.webp" alt="Add Happy Hour" class="wp-image-9437" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-add-Happy-Hour-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-add-Happy-Hour-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-add-Happy-Hour-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-add-Happy-Hour-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.-add-Happy-Hour.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-add-a-promotion-title" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Add a Promotion Title</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Happy Hour Title</strong> field, enter a descriptive name for your promotion.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Examples: <em>“Happy Hour Specials,” “Daily Happy Hour,” or “Afternoon Delight”</em>.</li></ul></li></ol><h2 id="step-3-define-the-offers-active-time" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Define the Offer’s Active Time</h2><p>You can schedule when the happy hour applies:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Daily in a Specific Time</strong> – Runs every day within the chosen time window.</li><li><strong>Specific Day in a Week</strong> – Runs only on selected days of the week.</li><li><strong>Custom Day</strong> – Runs for a specific date range (ideal for seasonal or one-time events).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-Happy-Hour-offer-active-time-1024x581.webp" alt="Happy Hour Offer Active Time" class="wp-image-9438" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-Happy-Hour-offer-active-time-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-Happy-Hour-offer-active-time-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-Happy-Hour-offer-active-time-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-Happy-Hour-offer-active-time-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-Happy-Hour-offer-active-time.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Select the option that fits your promotion and set the timing.</p><h2 id="step-4-configure-the-discount" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure the Discount</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Scroll to the <strong>Discount Setup</strong> section.</li><li>Choose the discount type. (<em>Percentage</em> is most common for happy hour deals.)</li><li>Enter the discount value (e.g., <em>20</em> → 20%).</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-the-discount-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Configure The Discount" class="wp-image-11095" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-the-discount-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-the-discount-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-the-discount-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-the-discount-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-the-discount-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-select-applicable-food-and-categories-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Select Applicable Food and Categories <em>(Optional)</em></h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>By default, discounts apply to the <strong>entire menu</strong>.</li><li>To limit the promotion, toggle <strong>Offer on Specific Food / Category</strong> to <strong>On</strong>.</li><li>Choose either <strong>Specific Food</strong> or <strong>Specific Category</strong>.</li><li>Select items or categories from the list.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Happy-Hour-food-selection-1024x580.webp" alt="Happy Hour Food Selection" class="wp-image-9439" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Happy-Hour-food-selection-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Happy-Hour-food-selection-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Happy-Hour-food-selection-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Happy-Hour-food-selection-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Happy-Hour-food-selection.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-choose-applicable-order-types" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Choose Applicable Order Types</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Order Type</strong> section, select which order methods are eligible.</li><li>Options include:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Dine In</strong></li><li><strong>Take Away</strong></li><li><strong>Home Delivery</strong></li></ul></li></ol><h2 id="step-7-select-specific-branches-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Select Specific Branches <em>(Optional)</em></h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>By default, discounts apply to the <strong>All Branches</strong></li><li>If your business has multiple locations, toggle <strong>Specific Branch</strong> to <strong>On</strong>.</li><li>Select the branches where the happy hour should apply.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Happy-Hour-order-type-and-branch-selection-1024x580.webp" alt="Happy Hour Order Type And Branch Selection" class="wp-image-9440" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Happy-Hour-order-type-and-branch-selection-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Happy-Hour-order-type-and-branch-selection-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Happy-Hour-order-type-and-branch-selection-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Happy-Hour-order-type-and-branch-selection-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Happy-Hour-order-type-and-branch-selection.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-8-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 8: Save Your Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all details are set, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the top right.</li><li>A success message will confirm: <em>“Happy Hour promotion saved successfully.”</em></li></ol><p>Your happy hour promotion is now live. Customers ordering during the configured times will automatically receive the discount.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 9,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:57.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:57.000000Z',
                ],
                87 => [
                    'id' => 88,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-update-happy-hour-settings',
                    'title' => 'How to Update Happy Hour Settings',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to modify an existing <strong>Happy Hour</strong> promotion in Menumium. You can update the discount, timing, applicable items, order types, or branches.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-happy-hour-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Happy Hour Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand navigation menu, click <strong>Promotion Management</strong> &gt; <strong>Happy Hour</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Happy Hour Navigation" class="wp-image-11097" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-navigation-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The page will display your current <strong>active Happy Hour configuration</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-modify-the-promotion-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Modify the Promotion Details</h2><p>You can update any of the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Title</strong>: Change the text in the <strong>Happy Hour Title</strong> field to rename your promotion.</li><li><strong>Schedule</strong>: Adjust the <strong>Offer Active Time</strong> to a new daily time, specific day(s) of the week, or a custom date range.</li><li><strong>Discount</strong>: Update the percentage in the <strong>Discount Setup</strong> section (e.g., change from <em>20%</em> to <em>25%</em>).</li><li><strong>Applicable Items</strong>: Under <strong>Offer on Specific Food / Category</strong>, add or remove items or categories by checking/unchecking boxes.</li><li><strong>Order Types</strong>: Modify which order methods the discount applies to by checking/unchecking options such as <strong>Dine In</strong>, <strong>Take Away</strong>, or <strong>Home Delivery</strong>.</li><li><strong>Branches</strong>: In the <strong>Specific Branch</strong> section, select or deselect branches where the promotion should apply.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-modify-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Happy Hour Modify" class="wp-image-11100" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-modify-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-modify-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-modify-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-modify-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-hour-modify-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-save-your-updates" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Save Your Updates</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After making changes, click the <strong>Save</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>A success message will appear at the bottom of the screen:<br><em>“Happy Hour settings updated successfully.”</em></li><li>The updated promotion will reflect immediately on your digital menus.</li></ol><p>With these steps, you can keep your Happy Hour promotions flexible, ensuring they align with your business needs at any time.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 10,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:58.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:58.000000Z',
                ],
                88 => [
                    'id' => 89,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-apply-a-coupon-to-an-order',
                    'title' => 'How to Apply a Coupon to an Order',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Applying a coupon to an order in the Menumium POS system is simple and efficient. This feature allows you to give discounts, run promotions, and reward customer loyalty directly at checkout.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-pos-dashboard" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the POS Dashboard</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your Menumium main dashboard, click <strong>POS Management &gt; New Sale </strong>in the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Point of Sale (POS)</strong> interface.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-add-items-to-the-cart" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Add Items to the Cart</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Browse and select the items the customer wishes to purchase.</li><li>Each selected item will appear in the <strong>Cart List</strong> on the right side of the screen.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-view-order-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: View Order Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all items are added, scroll down the right-hand panel.</li><li>In the <strong>Order Information</strong> section, click on the <strong>Billings</strong> tab to expand billing details.</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-access-the-coupon-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Access the Coupon Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the billing breakdown, locate the <strong>Coupon Discount</strong> field.</li><li>Click the small button next to it to open the <strong>Available Coupon</strong> window.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Add-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-1024x580.webp" alt="Add Coupon To POS - Coupon Selection" class="wp-image-9441" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Add-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Add-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Add-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Add-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Add-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-apply-a-coupon" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Apply a Coupon</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the pop-up window, you can:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Select an existing coupon</strong> → Click on the coupon from the list to apply<br>Or,</li><li><strong>Enter a coupon code manually</strong> → Type the code into the <strong>Coupon Code</strong> field and click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Apply-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-from-list-1024x580.webp" alt="Apply Coupon To POS - Coupon Selection From List" class="wp-image-9442" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Apply-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-from-list-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Apply-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-from-list-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Apply-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-from-list-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Apply-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-from-list-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Apply-Coupon-to-POS-coupon-selection-from-list.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-confirm-the-discount" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Confirm the Discount</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once applied, the coupon discount will appear in the billing summary.</li><li>The reduced amount will be shown next to the <strong>Coupon Discount</strong> field.</li></ul><h2 id="step-7-complete-the-transaction" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Complete the Transaction</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Proceed with the order as usual.</li><li>Select the <strong>payment method</strong> (Cash, Card, Mobile Banking, etc.).</li><li>Click <strong>Place Order</strong> to finalize the transaction.</li></ul><p>The order is now completed with the coupon successfully applied, and the discount reflected in the bill.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 11,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:59.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:59.000000Z',
                ],
                89 => [
                    'id' => 90,
                    'doc_category_id' => 9,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-a-food-specific-discount',
                    'title' => 'How to Set a Food-Specific Discount',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through applying a discount to a single food item in Menumium. This feature is perfect for promotions, limited-time offers, or special deals on selected menu items.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-food-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Food List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dashboard, go to <strong>Menu Setup Management &gt; Food Management</strong>.</li><li>The Food List page will display all available menu items.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-management-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="Food Management Navigation" class="wp-image-11107" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-management-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-management-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-management-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-management-navigation-0a-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-management-navigation-0a.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-setup-food-list-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Food Setup Food List" class="wp-image-11108" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-setup-food-list-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-setup-food-list-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-setup-food-list-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-setup-food-list-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-setup-food-list-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-edit-a-food-item" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Edit a Food Item</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the food item you want to discount.</li><li>On the right side, click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Edit Details</strong> from the dropdown.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-three-dot-menu-edit-details-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Food Item Three Dot Menu Edit Details" class="wp-image-11109" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-three-dot-menu-edit-details-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-three-dot-menu-edit-details-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-three-dot-menu-edit-details-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-three-dot-menu-edit-details-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-three-dot-menu-edit-details-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-access-discount-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Access Discount Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Food Setup</strong> window, go to the <strong>Variation &amp; Prices</strong> tab.</li><li>Scroll down and click <strong>Advance Settings</strong>.</li><li>Find the <strong>Setup Discount</strong> section and toggle it <strong>ON</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-view-advanced-settings-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Food Item View Advanced Settings" class="wp-image-11111" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-view-advanced-settings-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-view-advanced-settings-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-view-advanced-settings-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-view-advanced-settings-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-item-view-advanced-settings-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-the-discount" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure the Discount</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the <strong>Discount Amount</strong> (either a flat value or percentage).</li><li>Set the <strong>Validity Period</strong>:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the calendar to choose a start and end date.</li><li>Or check the <strong>Permanent Discount</strong> box to keep it active indefinitely.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-configure-the-discount.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-9831" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-configure-the-discount.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-configure-the-discount-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/food-configure-the-discount-768x435.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong> at the bottom.</li><li>A success message will confirm the discount is applied to the food item.</li></ul><p>The selected food item now has a specific discount, helping you run promotions smoothly and boost customer engagement.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 12,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:59.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:53:59.000000Z',
                ],
                90 => [
                    'id' => 91,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-add-a-new-floor-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Add a New Floor in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to create a new floor for a specific restaurant branch in <strong>Menumium</strong>. By first selecting the correct branch, you can ensure the floor setup applies to the intended location.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-floor-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Floor Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the sidebar, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management &gt; Floor Setup</strong>.</li><li>At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown.</li><li>Select the branch you want to manage.</li><li>The system will load the <strong>Floor List</strong> for that branch, showing a <strong>default floor</strong> already created.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Access Floor Setup" class="wp-image-11744" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-create-a-new-floor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Create a New Floor</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>+ Add New Floor</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>A <strong>Create New Floor</strong> pop-up form will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-floor-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Add New Floor Button" class="wp-image-11745" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-floor-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-floor-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-floor-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-floor-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-floor-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the following details:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Name</strong>: Floor name (e.g., <em>2nd Floor</em>).</li><li><strong>Max. Table Capacity</strong>: The maximum number of tables allowed on this floor.</li><li><strong>Max. Person Capacity</strong>: The maximum number of people the floor can accommodate.</li><li><strong>No. of Windows</strong>: Total number of windows on the floor.</li><li><strong>Area (Sqft)</strong>: Total area of the floor. You may also specify width and length separately.</li><li><strong>Short Description</strong>: (Optional) Add a brief description of the floor.</li><li><strong>Floor Image</strong>: Upload an image of the floor (PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP formats supported).</li></ul></li><li>After filling in the details, click <strong>Save</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-floor-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Create Floor" class="wp-image-11746" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-floor-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-floor-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-floor-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-floor-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-floor-0b.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-verify-the-new-floor" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Verify the New Floor</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A success message will appear: <strong>“Resource created successfully.”</strong></li><li>The floor will now appear in the <strong>Floor List</strong>, along with details like:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Floor Info</li><li>Table Info</li><li>Person Capacity</li><li>Status (default: <strong>Full Available</strong>)</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Verify New Floor" class="wp-image-11747" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-0a-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-0a.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You have successfully added a new floor to a branch. You can now assign tables and manage seating capacity within this floor setup.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:01.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:01.000000Z',
                ],
                91 => [
                    'id' => 92,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-update-floor-information-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Update Floor Information in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to edit and update the floor layout and capacity information within the Menumium dashboard. Updating floor details is useful after renovations, layout changes, or for setting up special events.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-floor-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Floor Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the sidebar, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management &gt; Floor Setup</strong>.</li><li>At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown.</li><li>Select the branch you want to manage.</li><li>The system will load the <strong>Floor List</strong> for that branch, showing a <strong>default floor</strong> already created.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Access Floor Setup" class="wp-image-11744" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-a-floor-to-update" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select a Floor to Update</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>Floor List</strong> page will display all floors for the selected branch.</li><li>Locate the floor you want to edit.</li><li>Click the <strong>three-dot menu icon</strong> (â®) on the right-hand side of the floor’s row.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-marked.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-9815" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-marked.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-marked-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/verify-new-floor-marked-768x433.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-update-floor-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Update Floor Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Update Floor</strong> will appear.</li><li>Modify any of the following fields as needed:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Name:</strong> Change the floor name (e.g., <em>2nd Floor</em>, <em>Terrace Seating</em>).</li><li><strong>Max. Table Capacity:</strong> Adjust the maximum number of tables allowed.</li><li><strong>Max. Person Capacity:</strong> Update the total number of people the floor can accommodate.</li><li><strong>Area (SqFt):</strong> Enter or update the floor area in square feet.</li><li><strong>Short Description:</strong> Add or update a brief description.</li></ul></li><li>After making the changes, click the <strong>Update</strong> button to save.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-update-0b-1024x579.webp" alt="Floor Update" class="wp-image-11749" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-update-0b-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-update-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-update-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-update-0b-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-update-0b.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-confirmation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Confirmation</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A notification will appear at the bottom of your screen: <strong>“Floor updated successfully.”</strong></li><li>The updated floor details will now be visible in the <strong>Floor List</strong>.</li></ul><p>You have now successfully updated the floor information for the selected branch.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:01.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:01.000000Z',
                ],
                92 => [
                    'id' => 93,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-manage-floor-status-off-on-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Manage Floor Status (Off/On) in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This feature allows you to control the availability of a specific floor, preventing new dine-in orders or reservations from being created for that area. This is useful for maintenance, private events, or when a section of your restaurant is temporarily closed.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-floor-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Floor Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the sidebar, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management &gt; Floor Setup</strong>.</li><li>At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown.</li><li>Select the branch you want to manage.</li><li>The system will load the <strong>Floor List</strong> for that branch, showing a <strong>default floor</strong> already created.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Access Floor Setup" class="wp-image-11744" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-manage-floor-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Manage Floor Status</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Floor List</strong> page, locate the floor you want to manage.</li><li>Under the <strong>Status</strong> column, click the toggle button:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Blue Toggle (On):</strong> The floor is currently active</li><li><strong>Gray Toggle (Off):</strong> The floor is inactive </li></ul></li><li>To deactivate the floor, click the blue toggle. A confirmation pop-up will appear.</li><li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong>. The toggle will turn gray, and the status will change to <strong>Unavailable</strong>.</li><li>To reactivate the floor, click the gray toggle. Confirm the action again, and the floor will switch back to <strong>Full Available</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-status-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Floor Status" class="wp-image-11750" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-status-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-status-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-status-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-status-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-status-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You have now successfully managed the availability of a floor for the selected branch.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:02.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:02.000000Z',
                ],
                93 => [
                    'id' => 94,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-filter-your-floor-list',
                    'title' => 'How to Filter Your Floor List',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This documentation will guide you through the process of filtering your floor list in the Menumium dashboard. Filters help you quickly find specific floors based on criteria like status, table capacity, and current floor status.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-floor-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Floor Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the sidebar, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management &gt; Floor Setup</strong>.</li><li>At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown.</li><li>Select the branch you want to manage.</li><li>The system will load the <strong>Floor List</strong> for that branch, showing a <strong>default floor</strong> already created.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Access Floor Setup" class="wp-image-11744" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-floor-setup-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-filter" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Filter</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Floor List page, locate the <strong>Filter</strong> button in the top-right. Click this button to open the filter menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-filter-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Floor Filter Button" class="wp-image-11751" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-filter-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-filter-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-filter-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-filter-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/floor-filter-button-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-apply-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply Filters</h2><p>The filter menu provides several options to refine your floor list:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All</strong> – Shows all floors.</li><li><strong>Active</strong> – Displays only active floors.</li><li><strong>Inactive</strong> – Displays only inactive floors.<br></li></ul></li><li><strong>Max. Table Capacity:</strong><strong><br></strong> Enter a number to filter for floors with a maximum table capacity up to that value.</li><li><strong>Max. Person Capacity:</strong><strong><br></strong> Enter a number to filter for floors that can accommodate up to that many people.</li><li><strong>Current Status:</strong><strong><br></strong> Use the checkboxes to filter by floor availability:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Full Available</strong> – Floors are completely available.</li><li><strong>Partial Available</strong> – Floors with some tables available.</li><li><strong>Fully Engaged</strong> – Floors where all tables are occupied.</li><li><strong>Full Reserved</strong> – Floors fully reserved.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-filter-floor-list-1024x577.webp" alt="Filter Floor List" class="wp-image-9286" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-filter-floor-list-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-filter-floor-list-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-filter-floor-list-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-filter-floor-list-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-filter-floor-list.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-apply-the-filter" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Apply the Filter</h2><p>Once you’ve selected your filters, click the <strong>Apply</strong> button at the bottom of the menu. The floor list will refresh and display only the matching floors.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:03.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:03.000000Z',
                ],
                94 => [
                    'id' => 95,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-a-new-table',
                    'title' => 'How to Create a New Table',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will show you how to create a new table in Menumium. Creating new tables allows you to organize your restaurant’s floor plan and manage reservations efficiently.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-table-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Table List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the Menumium dashboard, click on <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong> in the left-hand navigation panel.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Table Setup Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11768" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Next, go to <strong>Table Setup &gt; Table List</strong>. At the top of the page, open the <strong>branch dropdown</strong>. Select the branch you want to manage. The system will load the Table List for that branch, showing a default table already created.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Table List Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11770" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-create-new-table-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the “Create New Table” Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Table List</strong> page, click the <strong>+ Create New Table</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>A form titled <strong>Create New Table</strong> will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Create New Table Button" class="wp-image-11771" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-out-the-table-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill Out the Table Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Table Name:</strong> Enter a unique and descriptive name (e.g., <em>Table 10</em>, <em>Window Seat 2</em>).</li><li><strong>Max. Person Capacity:</strong> Specify the maximum number of people the table can accommodate.</li><li><strong>Floor:</strong> Select the floor where this table will be placed (e.g., <em>1st Floor</em>, <em>2nd Floor</em>).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Create New Table" class="wp-image-11772" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-add-advanced-details-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Add Advanced Details (Optional)</h2><p>Click <strong>+ Advance Field</strong> to expand more customization options:</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-field-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Create New Table Advanced Field Button" class="wp-image-11773" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-field-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-field-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-field-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-field-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-field-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Position:</strong> Choose a position from the dropdown (e.g., <em>East Side with window</em>).</li><li><strong>Table Shape:</strong> Select the table shape (e.g., <em>Rectangular</em>, <em>Circular</em>).</li><li><strong>Short Description:</strong> Add notes about the table for easier identification.</li><li><strong>Table Image:</strong> Upload a table image (PNG, JPG, JPEG, or WEBP supported).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-options-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="Create New Table Advanced Options" class="wp-image-11774" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-options-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-options-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-options-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-options-0b-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-new-table-advanced-options-0b.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-the-new-table" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save the New Table</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After completing the form, click <strong>Save</strong> at the bottom.</li><li>A confirmation message, <strong>“Table Successfully Added,”</strong> will appear at the bottom-left of your screen.</li></ol><p>Your new table will now be listed in the <strong>Table List</strong>, ready for reservations and management.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-table-list-1024x576.webp" alt="Table List" class="wp-image-9295" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-table-list-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-table-list-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-table-list-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-table-list-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-table-list.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:04.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:04.000000Z',
                ],
                95 => [
                    'id' => 96,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-table-information',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit Table Information',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of editing existing table information, such as table number, maximum capacity, and floor location.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-table-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Table List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Table Setup Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11768" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click on <strong>Table Setup &gt; Table List</strong>. A list of all tables for the selected branch will appear. At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown. Select the branch you want to manage.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Table List Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11770" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-edit-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Edit Options</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the table you wish to edit.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> (â®).</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="Edit Table Details" class="wp-image-11779" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-0b-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-0b.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-update-table-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Update Table Details</h2><p>A pop-up window titled <strong>Update Table</strong> will open. Here, you can edit the following:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Table Name:</strong> Change the name or number of the table.</li><li><strong>Max. Person Capacity:</strong> Adjust the maximum number of guests the table can accommodate.</li><li><strong>Floor:</strong> Reassign the table to another floor if needed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0d-1024x576.webp" alt="Edit Table Details" class="wp-image-11780" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0d-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0d-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0d-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0d-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0d.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Advanced Fields (Optional):</strong> Expand to edit fields such as <strong>Position</strong>, <strong>Table Shape</strong>, <strong>Short Description</strong>, and upload/update a <strong>Table Image</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0f-1024x581.webp" alt="Edit Table Details" class="wp-image-11781" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0f-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0f-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0f-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0f-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-table-details-2-0f.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save the Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After updating the details, click the <strong>Update</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up window.</li><li>A confirmation message — <strong>“Table Info Status Updated Successfully”</strong> — will appear at the bottom left of your screen.</li></ol><p>Your table information is now updated and will reflect immediately in the Table List and across the reservation system.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:04.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:04.000000Z',
                ],
                96 => [
                    'id' => 97,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-manage-table-statuses',
                    'title' => 'How to Manage Table Statuses',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through how to monitor and change the status of your tables within the Menumium platform, which is crucial for efficient restaurant management and seating.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-table-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Table List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the Menumium dashboard, click on <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong> in the left-hand menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Table Setup Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11768" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Then, select <strong>Table Setup &gt; Table List</strong> to view all tables in the chosen branch. At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown. Select the branch you want to manage. The system will load the Table List for that branch, showing a default table already created.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Table List Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11770" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-understand-table-statuses" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Understand Table Statuses</h2><p>The <strong>Table List</strong> provides a quick overview of the current status of each table in your restaurant. The possible statuses include:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Available:</strong> The table is ready to be seated (default status for new tables).</li><li><strong>Active:</strong> The table is currently occupied, and an order has been placed.</li><li><strong>Engaged:</strong> The table is occupied, but no order has been placed yet (e.g., guests just seated).</li><li><strong>Reserved:</strong> The table is reserved for a future booking.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/understand-table-statuses-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Understand Table Statuses" class="wp-image-11787" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/understand-table-statuses-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/understand-table-statuses-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/understand-table-statuses-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/understand-table-statuses-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/understand-table-statuses-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-change-a-tables-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Change a Table’s Status</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the table you want to update in the list.</li><li>In the<strong> Status</strong> column, click the <strong>slider toggle</strong> to adjust availability:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Turn Off:</strong> Switch from <strong>Available</strong> to <strong>Off</strong> to make the table unavailable. A confirmation pop-up will appear. Click <strong>Confirm</strong>.</li><li><strong>Turn On:</strong> Switch from <strong>Off</strong> to <strong>Available</strong> to make the table ready for seating again.</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-status-slider-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Table Status Slider" class="wp-image-11788" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-status-slider-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-status-slider-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-status-slider-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-status-slider-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-status-slider-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="notes" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Notes</strong></h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation message will always appear when changing a table’s status, helping prevent accidental updates.</li><li>Keeping statuses accurate ensures smooth seating, order management, and reservation handling.</li></ul></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:05.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:05.000000Z',
                ],
                97 => [
                    'id' => 98,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-filter-the-table-list',
                    'title' => 'How to Filter the Table List',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to use the filter feature to quickly find specific tables in the table list based on their status, capacity, and current state.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-table-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Table List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Table Setup Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11768" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-setup-button-navigation-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click on <strong>Table Setup &gt; Table List</strong> to view all tables for the selected branch. At the top of the page, open the branch dropdown. Select the branch you want to manage. The system will load the Table List for that branch.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Table List Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11770" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-button-navigation-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-the-filter-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Filter Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the right side of the screen, locate the <strong>View Filter</strong> button.</li><li>Click it to open the filter panel.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-filter-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Table List Filter Button" class="wp-image-11792" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-filter-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-filter-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-filter-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-filter-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/table-list-filter-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-apply-filter-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply Filter Options</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Filter by Status:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All</strong>: Displays both active and inactive tables.</li><li><strong>Active</strong>: Shows only tables that are currently active.</li><li><strong>Inactive</strong>: Shows tables that are not active.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Filter by Person Capacity:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter a value in the <strong>Max. Person Capacity</strong> field to find tables that can accommodate a specific number of people.</li><li>Example: Enter <strong>10</strong> to find tables with a maximum capacity of 10 people.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Filter by Current Status:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Available</strong>: Shows tables that are currently free and ready for use.</li><li><strong>Dine-in (Currently Busy)</strong>: Shows tables occupied by dine-in customers.</li><li><strong>Reserved</strong>: Shows tables that are already booked.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-filter-1024x576.webp" alt="Filter" class="wp-image-9298" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-filter-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-filter-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-filter-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-filter-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-filter.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-apply-or-reset-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Apply or Reset Filters</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After selecting your desired filters, click the <strong>Apply</strong> button at the bottom of the filter panel. The table list will instantly refresh to show only the tables that match your criteria.</li><li>To clear all filters and view the full list again, click the <strong>Reset</strong> button.</li></ul><p>With this feature, you can quickly locate and manage tables based on real-time availability, status, or seating capacity.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 8,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:06.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:06.000000Z',
                ],
                98 => [
                    'id' => 99,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-a-reservation',
                    'title' => 'How to Create a Reservation',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Creating a new reservation in <strong>Menumium</strong> is a simple process. Follow these steps to book a table for a customer, including their details and billing information.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-reservation-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Reservation Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Manage Reservation</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Manage Reservation Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11797" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-the-reservation-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Reservation Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Manage Reservation</strong> page, click the green <strong>+ Create Reservation</strong> button in the top right corner.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Make Reservation</strong> form.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-reservation-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Create Reservation" class="wp-image-11798" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-reservation-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-reservation-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-reservation-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-reservation-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-reservation-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-in-reservation-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill in Reservation Details</h2><p>Under the <strong>Reservation Information</strong> section:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Reservation Date:</strong> Select the desired date from the calendar.</li><li><strong>Reservation Time:</strong> Choose the start and end times for the reservation.</li><li><strong>No of Person:</strong> Enter the number of guests.</li><li><strong>Floor:</strong> Select the floor where the table will be located.</li><li><strong>Choose Table:</strong> Select either <strong>Full Floor</strong> (system auto-assigns a table) or <strong>Specific Table</strong> (manually select from available tables).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-reservation-information-1024x580.webp" alt="Reservation Information" class="wp-image-9305" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-reservation-information-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-reservation-information-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-reservation-information-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-reservation-information-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-reservation-information.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-add-customer-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Add Customer Information</h2><p>In the <strong>Customer Info</strong> section, you can:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Walk-in Customer</strong> for new/unlisted guests.</li><li>Use <strong>Add Contact Person Info</strong> to search and select an existing customer.</li><li>Or, click <strong>+ Add New Customer</strong> to create a new profile with <strong>Name, Phone, and Email</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-add-customer-info-1024x580.webp" alt="Add Customer Info" class="wp-image-9306" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-add-customer-info-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-add-customer-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-add-customer-info-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-add-customer-info-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-add-customer-info.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-enter-billing-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Enter Billing Information</h2><p>Expand the <strong>Billings</strong> section to configure payments:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Advance Booking Fee / Specific Table:</strong> Enter the applicable amount (tax auto-calculated).</li><li><strong>Payment Method:</strong> Choose the method.</li><li><strong>Paid Amount:</strong> Enter the amount received in advance. The system will automatically update the <strong>Due</strong> amount.</li><li><strong>Add a comment</strong> if needed, and also click on the checkbox if you want to show the comment on the receipt.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-billing-1024x581.webp" alt="Billing" class="wp-image-9307" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-billing-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-billing-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-billing-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-billing-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-billing.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-finalize-the-reservation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Finalize the Reservation</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Review all details entered.</li><li>Click the green <strong>Create Reservation</strong> button at the bottom of the form.</li><li>A confirmation message — <strong>“Reservation Successfully Added”</strong> — will appear.</li></ol><p>The reservation is now active and visible in your reservation list for the selected branch.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-reservation-list-1024x576.webp" alt="Reservation List" class="wp-image-9308" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-reservation-list-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-reservation-list-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-reservation-list-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-reservation-list-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-reservation-list.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p><strong>Note:</strong><strong><br></strong>In addition to creating a reservation through the main Reservation form, there are other ways to create one:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>From a Specific Table:</strong> When viewing a table in the Table List, you can directly reserve it.</li><li><strong>From the POS:</strong> Reservations can also be made directly while processing orders in the POS.<br></li></ul></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 9,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:07.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:07.000000Z',
                ],
                99 => [
                    'id' => 100,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-update-a-reservation-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Update a Reservation in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to modify an existing reservation, such as changing the date, time, floor, or table for a customer.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-manage-reservation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Manage Reservation</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong> section in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Manage Reservation</strong>. This will display a list of all reservations for the selected branch.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-list-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="Reservation List Navigation" class="wp-image-11801" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-list-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-list-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-list-navigation-0a-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-list-navigation-0a-1536x868.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-list-navigation-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-reservation-actions" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Reservation Actions</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the reservation you want to update in the list.</li><li>On the right-hand side of the row, click the <strong>three-dot action menu</strong> (â®).</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-edit-details-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Reservation Edit Details" class="wp-image-11802" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-edit-details-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-edit-details-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-edit-details-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-edit-details-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-edit-details-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-update-reservation-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Update Reservation Information</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up titled <strong>Edit Reservation</strong> will appear.</li><li>Modify the details as needed:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Reservation Date</strong></li><li><strong>Reservation Time</strong></li><li><strong>Number of Persons</strong></li><li><strong>Floor</strong></li><li><strong>Table</strong></li><li><strong>Customer Info</strong></li><li><strong>Billing</strong></li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-update-reservation-1024x580.webp" alt="Update Reservation" class="wp-image-9310" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-update-reservation-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-update-reservation-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-update-reservation-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-update-reservation-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-update-reservation.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-save-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once the edits are complete, click the <strong>Update Reservation</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up.</li><li>A success message will appear:<br><br><em>âReservation info status updated successfully.â</em></li></ol></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 10,
