                101 => [
                    'id' => 102,
                    'doc_category_id' => 10,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-link-an-order-to-a-reservation-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Link an Order to a Reservation in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to link a customer’s order to their existing reservation in Menumium. Linking ensures that all food and billing details are correctly associated with the reserved table.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-reservation-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Reservation Management</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Manage Reservation</strong>.</li><li>This will open the list of all reservations for the selected branch.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1-1024x575.webp" alt="Manage Reservation Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11811" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-reservation-button-navigation-0a-1.webp 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-locate-the-reservation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Locate the Reservation</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the search bar or scroll through the list to find the reservation by <strong>Customer Name</strong> or <strong>Reservation ID</strong>.</li><li>Verify the reservation details to ensure you’re linking the order to the correct booking.</li></ol><h2 id="step-3-open-the-action-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Open the Action Menu</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the far right of the reservation row, click the <strong>three-dot action menu</strong> (â®).</li><li>From the dropdown options, select <strong>Link Order</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-three-dot-menu-for-link-order-1024x576.webp" alt="Three Dot Menu for Link Order" class="wp-image-9321" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-three-dot-menu-for-link-order-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-three-dot-menu-for-link-order-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-three-dot-menu-for-link-order-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-three-dot-menu-for-link-order-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-three-dot-menu-for-link-order.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-enter-order-id" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Enter Order ID</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Link Order</strong> will appear.</li><li>In the <strong>Enter Order ID</strong> field, type or paste the unique ID of the customer’s order.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-enter-order-id-1024x578.webp" alt="Enter Order ID" class="wp-image-9322" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-enter-order-id-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-enter-order-id-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-enter-order-id-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-enter-order-id-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.-enter-order-id.webp 1913w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-confirm-the-link" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Confirm the Link</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After entering the ID, click the <strong>Link Order</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up.</li><li>A success message will appear:<br><br><em>âOrder linked to reservation successfully.â</em></li></ol></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 12,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:09.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:09.000000Z',
                ],
                102 => [
                    'id' => 103,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-get-branch-specific-order-reports',
                    'title' => 'How to Get Branch-Specific Order Reports?',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Menumium allows you to manage your business by branch. You can switch between locations to view branch-specific order reports.</p><h2 id="view-reports-for-a-specific-branch" class="wp-block-heading">View Reports for a Specific Branch</h2><p>From your dashboard, open the <strong>left-hand sidebar</strong> and click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-management-navigation-0a-1024x585.webp" alt="Order Management Navigation" class="wp-image-11815" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-management-navigation-0a-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-management-navigation-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-management-navigation-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-management-navigation-0a-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-management-navigation-0a.webp 1888w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-1-locate-the-branch-switcher" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Locate the Branch Switcher</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>At the top of your dashboard, find the button displaying the name of your current branch (e.g., <strong>Main Branch</strong>).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/current-branch-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Current Branch" class="wp-image-11816" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/current-branch-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/current-branch-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/current-branch-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/current-branch-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/current-branch-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-switch-branches" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Switch Branches</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the branch name button to open a dropdown list of all registered branches.</li><li>Select the branch you want to view.</li><li>The dashboard will automatically refresh to display reports for the selected location.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-3-1024x582.webp" alt="Switch Branches" class="wp-image-9355" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-3-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-3-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-3-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-3-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-3.webp 1887w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>In this process, you can switch to any branch within the system. Once switched, the order management module will display and operate only on the data specific to that selected branch. This ensures each branch has a clear, isolated view of its order information.<br></p><h2 id="how-to-filter-any-branch-specific-orders" class="wp-block-heading">How to Filter Any Branch-Specific Orders?</h2><p>After selecting a branch, you can filter its orders by order source, status, date range, and payment type.</p><h2 id="step-1-specify-the-branch" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Specify The Branch </h2><p>Select the branch you want to filter data for. At the top of your dashboard, you’ll find the drop-down box to choose the branch.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/switch-branch-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Switch Branch" class="wp-image-11817" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/switch-branch-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/switch-branch-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/switch-branch-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/switch-branch-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/switch-branch-0a.webp 1887w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-navigate-to-order-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Navigate to Order Management</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-hand navigation menu, click <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li><li>Choose the type of orders to view:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>POS Orders</strong>: Orders created in your POS system (Dine In, Take Away, Home Delivery, Refund Request).</li><li><strong>Online Orders</strong>: Orders placed via the online ordering platform (Take Away, Home Delivery, and Refund Request).</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-order-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate To Order" class="wp-image-11818" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-order-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-order-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-order-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-order-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-order-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-access-the-filter-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Access the Filter Menu</h2><p>Suppose you want to filter any specific POS data-</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the POS order &gt; All Order List<strong>,</strong> click the <strong>Filter</strong> button at the top right of the order list.</li><li>A filter panel will slide out on the right side of the screen.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-filter-menu-0a-1024x586.webp" alt="Access Filter Menu" class="wp-image-11819" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-filter-menu-0a-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-filter-menu-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-filter-menu-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-filter-menu-0a-1536x878.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-filter-menu-0a.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-apply-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Apply Filters</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>By Order Date</strong>: Use the calendar to select a specific date or custom date range.</li><li><strong>By Payment Status</strong>: Choose <strong>Paid</strong> (completed payments) or <strong>Unpaid</strong> (pending payments).</li><li><strong>By Order Status</strong>: Select one or more statuses, such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Pending</strong>: Order placed but not confirmed.</li><li><strong>Confirmed</strong>: Accepted, awaiting preparation.</li><li><strong>Cooking</strong>: Currently being prepared in the kitchen.</li><li><strong>Eating</strong>: (For dine-in orders) Customer is consuming their meal.</li><li><strong>Ready to Serve</strong>: Meal is ready to be served at the table.</li><li><strong>Ready to Handover</strong>: Order is ready for pickup or delivery.</li><li><strong>On The Way</strong>: Delivery person is en route.</li><li><strong>Delivered</strong>: Order has been successfully delivered.</li><li><strong>Completed</strong>: Order fulfilled and closed.</li><li><strong>Refunded</strong>: Payment has been returned to the customer.</li><li><strong>Canceled</strong>: Order was canceled.</li><li><strong>Failed</strong>: Payment or delivery failed.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="570" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-page-0a-1024x570.webp" alt="Filter Page" class="wp-image-11940" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-page-0a-1024x570.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-page-0a-300x167.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-page-0a-768x427.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-page-0a-1536x854.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-page-0a.webp 1895w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-apply-or-reset" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Apply or Reset</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Apply</strong> to update the list based on your selected filters.</li><li>Click <strong>Reset</strong> to clear all filters and return to the full order list.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="592" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-0a-1024x592.webp" alt="Apply Filters" class="wp-image-11941" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-0a-1024x592.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-0a-768x444.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-0a-1536x888.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-0a.webp 1864w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With branch-specific reports and advanced filtering, you can efficiently analyze order trends and manage operations for each restaurant location.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:10.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:10.000000Z',
                ],
                103 => [
                    'id' => 104,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-view-and-manage-point-of-sale-pos-orders',
                    'title' => 'How to View and Manage Point of Sale (POS) Orders',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to navigate and manage all POS orders in Menumium. From dine-in to takeaway and delivery, the POS Orders section gives you complete visibility over your transactions.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-pos-orders-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the POS Orders Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>main dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>POS Orders</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-4-1024x583.webp" alt="Access the POS Orders Menu" class="wp-image-9358" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-4-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-4-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-4-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-4-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-4.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-navigate-the-order-lists" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Navigate the Order Lists</h2><p>The POS Orders section is divided into multiple lists to help you manage different types of orders:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All Order List:</strong> View all orders placed through the POS system, including details such as Order ID, Customer Info, Total Amount, Order Info, and Order Status.</li><li><strong>Dine In:</strong> Filter and view only dine-in orders.</li><li><strong>Take Away:</strong> See all takeaway orders placed by customers.</li><li><strong>Home Delivery:</strong> Monitor orders scheduled for delivery.</li><li><strong>Refund Request:</strong> Review all refund-related orders, including requested, approved, denied, and refunded. You can sort them by status using the tabs at the top.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-pos-order-list-0a-1024x585.webp" alt="Navigate Pos Order List" class="wp-image-11945" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-pos-order-list-0a-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-pos-order-list-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-pos-order-list-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-pos-order-list-0a-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-pos-order-list-0a.webp 1888w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-exporting-order-data" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Exporting Order Data</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From <strong>All Order List</strong> (or any filtered list), locate the <strong>Export</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>Click <strong>Export</strong> to download your order data in spreadsheet format for reporting or record-keeping.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-pos-data-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Export Pos Data" class="wp-image-11946" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-pos-data-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-pos-data-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-pos-data-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-pos-data-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-pos-data-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-using-search-and-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Using Search and Filters</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Search:</strong> Enter an <strong>Order ID</strong> or keyword in the search bar to quickly find specific orders.</li><li><strong>Filter:</strong> Click the <strong>Filter</strong> button to apply advanced filters by <strong>date, order status, or payment method</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-or-filter-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Search Or Filter" class="wp-image-11947" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-or-filter-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-or-filter-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-or-filter-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-or-filter-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-or-filter-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By using the <strong>POS Orders menu</strong>, you can efficiently monitor, filter, and export order data. This ensures smooth daily operations and accurate record management for all customer orders.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:11.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:11.000000Z',
                ],
                104 => [
                    'id' => 105,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-update-pos-order-status',
                    'title' => 'How to Update POS Order Status',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will show you how to update the status of a POS order within the Menumium platform. Updating order statuses keeps your workflow organized and ensures customers are informed of their order progress.</p><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p><em>You can also <strong>update order statuses <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/pos/how-to-manage-ongoing-orders-from-pos/">directly from the POS interface</a></strong>, making it convenient for on-floor staff to manage orders in real-time.</em></p></div></div><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-order-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Order Management</h2><p>From your dashboard, open the <strong>left-hand sidebar</strong> and click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</p><p>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>POS Orders</strong>. This will display a list of all orders placed through the POS system.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-pos-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Access Pos" class="wp-image-11950" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-pos-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-pos-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-pos-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-pos-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-pos-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-locate-the-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Locate the Order</h2><p>On the <strong>All Order List</strong> page, find the order you wish to update.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Order Status</strong> button in that row.</li><li>A dropdown menu will appear with various status options.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-status-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Order Status" class="wp-image-11952" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-status-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-status-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-status-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-status-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-status-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-update-the-order-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Update the Order Status</h2><p>Select the new status from the dropdown. The available options are:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Cooking</strong> → A pop-up will ask you to provide the <strong>estimated processing time</strong>.</li><li><strong>Ready to Serve</strong></li><li><strong>Eating</strong></li><li><strong>Completed</strong></li><li><strong>Failed</strong></li><li><strong>Canceled</strong> → A pop-up will ask you to confirm the <strong>refund amount</strong> and provide a <strong>reason for cancellation</strong>.</li></ul><p>You can also update the order status by clicking the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> under the <strong>Action</strong> column. Here you’ll also find details about the <strong>order status</strong> and <strong>payment status</strong> (e.g., paid or unpaid).</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-order-status-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="Update Order Status" class="wp-image-11953" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-order-status-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-order-status-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-order-status-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-order-status-0a-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-order-status-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-confirmation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Confirmation</h2><p>Once you update the order, the system will automatically save the change.<br>A <strong>success message</strong> will appear at the bottom of your screen confirming the update.</p><p>Updating POS order statuses ensures smooth operations, accurate tracking, and clear communication with both your team and customers.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:12.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:12.000000Z',
                ],
                105 => [
                    'id' => 106,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-view-manage-online-orders',
                    'title' => 'How to View & Manage Online Orders',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Managing online orders is a crucial part of running your restaurant. Menumium provides a dedicated interface to help you track, update, and fulfill orders efficiently.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-online-orders-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Online Orders Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>main dashboard</strong>, navigate to the <strong>left-hand menu</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Online Orders</strong>.</li><li>A sub-menu will appear with multiple order types.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate To Online Orders" class="wp-image-11969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-view-orders-by-type" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: View Orders by Type</h2><p>Menumium organizes online orders into categories for easier tracking:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All Order List</strong> → Displays all orders, including Order ID, date, customer, total amount, items, type, and status.</li><li><strong>Take Away</strong> → Shows pickup orders. Use status tabs at the top (Cooking, Ready to Handover, Completed, etc.) to filter.</li><li><strong>Home Delivery</strong> → Displays delivery orders with status tabs (Cooking, On the Way, Delivered, etc.).</li><li><strong>Refund Request</strong> → View and manage refund cases. Sub-categories include <strong>Requested, Approved, Denied, and Refunded</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-all-order-type-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Online All Order Type" class="wp-image-11971" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-all-order-type-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-all-order-type-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-all-order-type-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-all-order-type-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-all-order-type-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-filter-orders" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Filter Orders</h2><p>To quickly find specific orders:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Filter</strong> button on the right side of the order list.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-button-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Filter Button" class="wp-image-11973" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-button-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-button-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-button-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-button-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-button-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A filter panel will appear with the following options:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Order Date</strong> → Select a date range.</li><li><strong>Payment Status</strong> → Filter by Paid or Unpaid.</li><li><strong>Order Type</strong> → Narrow results by Take Away, Home Delivery, etc.</li><li><strong>Order Status</strong> → Filter by stages such as Cooking, Completed, Canceled.</li></ul></li><li>Click <strong>Apply</strong> to update the list.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="592" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-details-and-apply-0a-1024x592.webp" alt="Filter Details &amp; Apply" class="wp-image-11975" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-details-and-apply-0a-1024x592.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-details-and-apply-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-details-and-apply-0a-768x444.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-details-and-apply-0a-1536x887.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-details-and-apply-0a.webp 1866w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-manage-order-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Manage Order Status</h2><p>To manage an order:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the order in the list and click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> under the <strong>Action</strong> column.</li><li>Choose from the following options:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>View Details</strong> → Full breakdown (items, customer, payment info).</li><li><strong>Edit Food</strong> → Modify food items in the order.</li><li><strong>Update Status</strong> → Manually update the order’s progress.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-order-status-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Online Order Status" class="wp-image-11976" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-order-status-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-order-status-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-order-status-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-order-status-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/online-order-status-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By using Menumium’s online order management tools, you can <strong>track, filter, <strong>export data,</strong> and update orders seamlessly</strong>. It ensures smooth operations from the moment an order is placed until it is delivered or picked up.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:13.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:13.000000Z',
                ],
                106 => [
                    'id' => 107,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-update-an-online-order-status',
                    'title' => 'How to Update an Online Order Status',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Updating the status of an online order is a crucial part of managing your restaurantâs workflow. Menumium makes it easy to change both order and payment statuses directly from the dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-online-orders-dashboard" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Online Orders Dashboard</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>main menu</strong> on the left side of your dashboard, click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Online Orders</strong> to view a list of all current and past online orders.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate To Online Orders" class="wp-image-11969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-locate-and-update-the-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Locate and Update the Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the order you want to update.</li><li>On the right-hand side of the order’s row, locate the <strong>Action</strong> column.</li><li>Click the <strong>three-dot icon (â®)</strong> to open the dropdown menu.</li><li>Select <strong>Update Status</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-3-1024x581.webp" alt="Locate and Update the Order" class="wp-image-9362" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-3-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-3-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-3-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-3-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-3.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-change-the-order-and-payment-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Change the Order and Payment Status</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Update Order Status</strong> will appear.</li><li>Under <strong>Order Status</strong>, choose from options such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Cooking</li><li>Ready to Handover</li><li>Delivered</li><li>Canceled</li></ul></li><li>Under <strong>Payment Status</strong>, select either:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Paid</li><li>Unpaid</li></ul></li><li>Once finished, click <strong>Update</strong>.</li></ul><p>A confirmation message, <strong>“Order Status Updated Successfully”</strong>, will appear at the bottom-left of the screen. The order status will now be updated in the main list.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="589" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-2-1024x589.webp" alt="Change the Order and Payment Status" class="wp-image-9363" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-2-1024x589.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-2-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-2-768x442.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-2-1536x884.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-2.webp 1873w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>You can also update an order’s <strong>status directly</strong> from the <strong>Order Status column</strong> in the order list, but <strong>payment status cannot be changed there</strong>.</p></div></div><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-status-change-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Quick Status Change" class="wp-image-11983" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-status-change-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-status-change-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-status-change-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-status-change-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/quick-status-change-0a.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By keeping order statuses updated, you ensure smooth coordination between staff, kitchen, and customers.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:14.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:14.000000Z',
                ],
                107 => [
                    'id' => 108,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-can-staff-download-the-invoice-of-online-orders',
                    'title' => 'How Can Staff Download the Invoice of Online Orders',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to download an invoice for POS or online orders directly from the Menumium dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-order-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Order Management</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the main dashboard, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li><li>A sub-menu will appear — select <strong>Online Orders</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate To Online Orders" class="wp-image-11969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-and-view-order-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select and View Order Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the order list, find the order you want to download an invoice for.</li><li>Under the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>three-dot (â®) icon</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>View Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-2-1024x582.webp" alt="Order Statuses Updated" class="wp-image-9364" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-2-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-2-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-2-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-2.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-download-the-invoice" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Download the Invoice</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>View Details</strong> page, locate the green <strong>Invoice</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-2-1024x583.webp" alt="Download the Invoice" class="wp-image-9365" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-2-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-2-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-2-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11-2.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Invoice</strong> button — this will open a new window with the invoice.</li><li>From this screen, you can:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Print</strong> the invoice.</li><li><strong>Download</strong> the invoice by clicking the <strong>Download icon</strong>.</li></ul></li></ul><p>The invoice will now be saved to your device or printed for record-keeping.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:14.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:14.000000Z',
                ],
                108 => [
                    'id' => 109,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-the-food-of-an-order',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit the Food of an Order',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of editing the food items in an existing order within your Menumium dashboard. This feature allows you to adjust quantities and update the order details easily.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-order-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Order Management</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-access-the-all-order-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the All Order List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A sub-menu will appear under <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>All Order List</strong> to view all online orders.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate To Online Orders" class="wp-image-11969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-locate-the-order-and-open-the-edit-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Locate the Order and Open the Edit Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>All Order List</strong> page, find the order you want to edit.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column (on the right side of the table), click the <strong>three vertical dots (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Edit Food</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-the-online-order-details-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Edit The Online Order Details" class="wp-image-11990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-the-online-order-details-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-the-online-order-details-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-the-online-order-details-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-the-online-order-details-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-the-online-order-details-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-edit-the-order-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Edit the Order Details</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Edit Food</strong> will open, showing the order’s details.</li><li>Adjust the quantity of items using the <strong>plus (+)</strong> or <strong>minus (–)</strong> buttons next to each product.</li><li>You can also add items by searching foods from the search bar.</li><li>As you make changes, the <strong>total price</strong> will automatically update.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-2-1024x586.webp" alt="Edit the Order Details" class="wp-image-9366" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-2-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-2-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-2-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-2-1536x879.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-2.webp 1886w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-confirm-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Confirm Your Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once you’ve made the necessary adjustments, click the <strong>Update Cart</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up.</li><li>A confirmation message, <strong>“Order Item Updated Successfully,”</strong> will appear at the bottom of the screen.</li></ol><p>By following these steps, you can quickly edit food items in an order, ensuring accuracy in customer requests and billing.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:15.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:15.000000Z',
                ],
                109 => [
                    'id' => 110,
                    'doc_category_id' => 11,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-assign-a-delivery-man-to-an-order',
                    'title' => 'How to Assign a Delivery Man to an Order',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to assign a delivery man to a home delivery order in Menumium. Assigning ensures proper tracking and management of deliveries.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-online-orders" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Online Orders</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Order Management</strong>.</li><li>Under it, select <strong>Online Orders</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate To Online Orders" class="wp-image-11969" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-online-orders-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-home-delivery-orders" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Home Delivery Orders</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Inside the Online Orders section, click on <strong>Home Delivery</strong>.</li><li>A list of all home delivery orders will be displayed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-home-delivery-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Open Home Delivery" class="wp-image-11993" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-home-delivery-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-home-delivery-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-home-delivery-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-home-delivery-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-home-delivery-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-access-order-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Access Order Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the order you want to assign.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>three-dot icon (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>View Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1-1024x583.webp" alt="Access Order Details" class="wp-image-9368" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-assign-a-delivery-man" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Assign a Delivery Man</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Order Details</strong> page, scroll to the <strong>Delivery Man</strong> section (right-hand side).</li><li>Click the <strong>Assign Delivery Man</strong> button.</li><li>A modal window will open, showing all available delivery men.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14-1-1024x586.webp" alt="Assign a Delivery Man" class="wp-image-9369" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14-1-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14-1-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14-1-768x440.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14-1-1536x879.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14-1.webp 1876w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-select-and-confirm" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Select and Confirm</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Choose a delivery man from the list.</li><li>(Optional) Add a note in the <strong>Comments</strong> box</li><li>Click the <strong>Assign</strong> button to confirm.</li></ul><h2 id="step-6-confirmation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Confirmation</h2><p>A success message will appear at the bottom-left corner of your screen, confirming that the delivery man has been successfully assigned to the order.</p><p>Following these steps ensures smooth assignment of delivery staff and timely delivery management.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 8,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:16.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:16.000000Z',
                ],
                110 => [
                    'id' => 111,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-employee-and-role-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up Employee and Role in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of creating new employee roles and assigning access permissions. Setting up roles ensures your team members have the right level of access to different modules, keeping your operations secure and organized.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-user-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to User Management</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the main dashboard, open the <strong>left-hand navigation menu</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>User Management</strong> to expand the dropdown menu.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-2-1024x580.webp" alt="Navigate to User Management" class="wp-image-9338" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-2-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-2-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-2-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-2-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-2.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-employee-role-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access Employee &amp; Role Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the dropdown, select <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Employee Role List</strong> page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-employee-role-setup-0b.webp-1024x585.webp" alt="Access Employee &amp; Role Setup" class="wp-image-11351" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-employee-role-setup-0b.webp-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-employee-role-setup-0b.webp-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-employee-role-setup-0b.webp-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-employee-role-setup-0b.webp-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-employee-role-setup-0b.webp.webp 1888w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-create-a-new-role" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Create a New Role</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Employee Role List page, click the <strong>+ Create New Role</strong> button (top-right corner).</li><li>This will open the <strong>Create New Role</strong> page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-2-1024x584.webp" alt="Create a New Role" class="wp-image-9339" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-2-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-2-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-2-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-2.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-define-the-new-role" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Define the New Role</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Availability Status: </strong>Toggle the switch to On to make the role active.</li><li><strong>Role Name</strong>: Enter a descriptive name (e.g., <em>Manager</em>, <em>Executive</em>, <em>Cashier</em>).</li><li><strong>Select Module</strong>: Use the dropdown menu to choose which modules the role should have access to.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Multiple modules can be selected, like order management, customer management, table &amp; reservation, etc.</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-3-1024x576.webp" alt="Define the New Role" class="wp-image-9340" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-3-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-3-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-3-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-3-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-3.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-configure-module-permissions" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Configure Module Permissions</h2><p>After selecting modules, permission options for each module will appear. Assign access levels by checking the relevant boxes:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Based on the module criteria, you can set employee access to View, Edit, Add, Print, Delete, and so on.</li></ul><p>You can fine-tune each role by enabling only the permissions needed.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-module-permissions-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Configure Module Permissions" class="wp-image-11352" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-module-permissions-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-module-permissions-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-module-permissions-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-module-permissions-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-module-permissions-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-the-new-role" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save the New Role</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once permissions are set, click the <strong>Create</strong> button at the top-right corner.</li><li>A confirmation message — <strong>“Role created successfully”</strong> — will appear at the bottom of the screen.</li><li>If required, the “<strong>Reset</strong>” button can be used to correct any mistakes before finalizing.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-new-role-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Save the New Role" class="wp-image-11354" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-new-role-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-new-role-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-new-role-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-new-role-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-new-role-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By setting up roles and assigning permissions, you can streamline employee responsibilities, safeguard sensitive information, and maintain better control over your restaurant’s operations.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:17.000000Z',
                ],
                111 => [
                    'id' => 112,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-employee-roles-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit Employee Roles in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of editing existing employee roles and permissions. Adjusting roles ensures your team members always have the correct level of access.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-employee-role-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Employee Role Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the main dashboard, open the <strong>left-hand navigation menu</strong>.</li><li>Under <strong>User Management</strong>, click on <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11357" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Employee Role List</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11359" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-the-role-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Role to Edit</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Employee Role List, find the role you want to edit.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column (far right), click the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Edit Role</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-the-role-to-edit-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="Select the Role to Edit" class="wp-image-11360" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-the-role-to-edit-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-the-role-to-edit-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-the-role-to-edit-0a-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-the-role-to-edit-0a-1536x868.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/select-the-role-to-edit-0a.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-adjust-permissions" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Adjust Permissions</h2><p>On the <strong>Edit Role</strong> page, you can update the role’s modules and access levels:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Remove Modules</strong> → Click the â next to any module to remove it from this role.</li><li><strong>Modify Module Access</strong> → For each module, set specific permissions:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>View</strong> → Allows the user to see module data.</li><li><strong>Edit</strong> → Allows the user to update information.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Mark All</strong> → Use the checkboxes to quickly enable or disable all <strong>View</strong> or <strong>Edit</strong> permissions for a module.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/adjust-permissions-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Adjust Permissions" class="wp-image-11362" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/adjust-permissions-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/adjust-permissions-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/adjust-permissions-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/adjust-permissions-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/adjust-permissions-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-save-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After making the required adjustments, click the green <strong>Update</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>A success message — <strong>âRole updated successfullyâ</strong> — will appear at the bottom-left of your screen.</li><li>All employees assigned to this role will automatically inherit the updated permissions.</li></ol><p>Editing employee roles ensures your staff always have the right access to perform their duties while maintaining system security.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/editing-employee-roles-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Editing Employee Roles" class="wp-image-11363" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/editing-employee-roles-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/editing-employee-roles-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/editing-employee-roles-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/editing-employee-roles-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/editing-employee-roles-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:17.000000Z',
                ],
                112 => [
                    'id' => 113,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-disable-or-enable-a-user-role-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Disable or Enable a User Role in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to disable or enable a user role, and how to reassign employees to a new role when a role is turned off.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-employee-role-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Employee Role Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>dashboard</strong>, open the <strong>left-hand navigation panel</strong>.</li><li>Under <strong>User Management</strong>, click on <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11357" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select <strong>Employee Role List</strong> from the submenu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11359" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0b.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-disable-a-role" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Disable a Role</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Employee Role List</strong> page, locate the role you want to disable.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>toggle switch</strong> to move it to the <strong>off</strong> position.</li><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>“By turning OFF this role?”</strong> will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disable-a-role-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Disable a Role" class="wp-image-11366" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disable-a-role-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disable-a-role-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disable-a-role-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disable-a-role-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disable-a-role-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-reassign-employees-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Reassign Employees (Optional)</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the pop-up window, you can reassign employees linked to other roles.</li><li>Click the <strong>Select Role</strong> dropdown menu and choose a new role.</li><li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong> to save the changes.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The selected role will be <strong>disabled</strong>.</li><li>Any employees assigned to it will automatically be reassigned to the new role.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reassign-employees-0a-1024x585.webp" alt="Reassign Employees" class="wp-image-11368" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reassign-employees-0a-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reassign-employees-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reassign-employees-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reassign-employees-0a-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reassign-employees-0a.webp 1888w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-enable-a-role" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Enable a Role</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Employee Role List</strong> page, find the disabled role you want to reactivate.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>toggle switch</strong> to the <strong>on</strong> position.</li><li>The role’s status will update, and it will become <strong>active</strong> again.</li></ol><p>Using the enable/disable toggle helps you manage user roles efficiently, temporarily pausing roles or reassigning employees without permanently deleting role settings.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:18.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:18.000000Z',
                ],
                113 => [
                    'id' => 114,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-invite-an-employee-for-a-role-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Invite an Employee for a Role in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to invite an employee to join your Menumium account by assigning them a role and branch.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-employee-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Employee List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>dashboard</strong>, open the <strong>left-hand navigation menu</strong>.</li><li>Under <strong>User Management</strong>, click on <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Employee List</strong> page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11357" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-initiate-an-invitation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Initiate an Invitation</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Employee List</strong> page, click the <strong>+Invite Employee</strong> button.</li><li>This button is located at the <strong>top-right corner</strong> of the page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="613" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-3-1024x613.webp" alt="Invite an Employee" class="wp-image-9342" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-3-1024x613.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-3-300x180.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-3-768x460.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-3-1536x919.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-3.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-out-the-invitation-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill Out the Invitation Form</h2><p>A pop-up form will appear. Enter the required details:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Email:</strong> Type the employee’s valid email address.</li><li><strong>Role:</strong> Select the role for the employee from the dropdown menu (e.g., Manager, Executive).</li><li><strong>Branch:</strong> Choose the branch/location where the employee will be assigned.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-invitation-form-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Fill Out the Invitation Form" class="wp-image-11371" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-invitation-form-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-invitation-form-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-invitation-form-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-invitation-form-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-invitation-form-0a.webp 1895w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-send-the-invitation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Send the Invitation</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all fields are completed, click the <strong>Send Invitation</strong> button.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, confirming that the invitation has been sent.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/send-the-invitation-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Send the Invitation" class="wp-image-11372" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/send-the-invitation-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/send-the-invitation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/send-the-invitation-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/send-the-invitation-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/send-the-invitation-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-employee-confirmation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Employee Confirmation</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The invited employee will receive an <strong>email with a unique link</strong> to join.</li><li>The link is <strong>time-sensitive</strong> and must be used within the given validity period.</li><li>Once accepted and completed, the employee will appear in your <strong>active Employee List</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-confirmation-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Employee Confirmation" class="wp-image-11373" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-confirmation-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-confirmation-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-confirmation-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-confirmation-0a-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-confirmation-0a.webp 1892w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Inviting employees through roles ensures they are assigned the right access and branch from the start, streamlining onboarding and team management.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:19.000000Z',
                ],
                114 => [
                    'id' => 115,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-complete-the-employee-registration-form',
                    'title' => 'How to Complete the Employee Registration Form',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to complete your registration as an employee after receiving an invitation email from Menumium.</p><h2 id="step-1-open-the-invitation-email" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Open the Invitation Email</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to your <strong>email inbox</strong>.</li><li>Look for an email from <strong>Menumium</strong> with the subject line: <em>“Employee Invitation for Registration.”</em></li><li>Click the email to open it.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-access-the-registration-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Registration Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Inside the email, you will see a welcome message from your manager.</li><li>Click the green <strong>Go to Employee Form</strong> button.</li><li>This will redirect you to the <strong>Employee Registration page</strong> in your browser.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Employee Setup" class="wp-image-11376" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-complete-the-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Complete the Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the registration page, fill in all the required fields.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Personal details</li><li>Contact information</li><li>Job-related data (e.g., role, branch)</li></ul></li><li>Double-check your entries to ensure they are correct and complete.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Employee Setup" class="wp-image-11378" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0b.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-submit-the-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Submit the Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After reviewing your information, scroll down and click the <strong>Submit</strong> button.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, verifying that your registration was successful.</li><li>Your manager will automatically be notified that you’ve completed the registration.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0c-1024x576.webp" alt="Employee Setup" class="wp-image-11379" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0c-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0c-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0c-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0c-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/employee-setup-0c.webp 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By following these steps, you can quickly complete your employee registration and gain access to the Menumium system with your assigned role and permissions.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:19.000000Z',
                ],
                115 => [
                    'id' => 116,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'where-can-i-find-the-employee-list',
                    'title' => 'Where Can I Find the Employee List?',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The Employee List provides a complete overview of all your employees, including their personal details and assigned roles.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-employee-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Employee List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>main dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>User Management</strong>.</li><li>Under the User Management menu, select <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11357" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>This will take you directly to the <strong>Employee List</strong> page.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-view-employee-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: View Employee Information</h2><p>On the <strong>Employee List</strong> page, you will see a table containing key details for each employee, including:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Employee Name</strong></li><li><strong>Employee Info</strong> (phone number, email)</li><li><strong>Role</strong> (assigned role within the system)</li><li><strong>Action</strong> (options to manage the employee profile)</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-3-1024x577.webp" alt="Find the Employee List" class="wp-image-9343" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-3-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-3-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-3-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-3-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-3.webp 1912w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You can also use the <strong>search bar</strong> at the top of the page to quickly find a specific employee.</p><p>The Employee List acts as a centralized directory, giving you quick access to all employee details and management actions in one place.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:20.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:20.000000Z',
                ],
                116 => [
                    'id' => 117,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-manage-employee-lists',
                    'title' => 'How to Manage Employee Lists',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to view, manage, and update employees within the Menumium dashboard. The Employee List allows you to control staff information, roles, and access levels.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-employee-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Employee List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>main dashboard</strong>, navigate to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>User Management</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Employee List</strong>.</li></ol><h2 id="step-2-view-employee-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: View Employee Information</h2><p>The <strong>Employee List</strong> page displays a table showing:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Employee Name</strong></li><li><strong>Contact Info</strong> (phone/email)</li><li><strong>Role</strong> (assigned role)</li><li><strong>Action</strong> (management options)</li></ul><p>A <strong>search bar</strong> is available at the top to quickly find specific employees.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-employee-information-0a-1024x578.webp" alt="View Employee Information" class="wp-image-11384" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-employee-information-0a-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-employee-information-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-employee-information-0a-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-employee-information-0a-1536x867.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-employee-information-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-manage-existing-employees" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Manage Existing Employees</h2><p>To manage an employee, click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> in the <strong>Action</strong> column. A dropdown will appear with these options:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status:</strong> Toggle the employee’s account status (active/inactive).</li><li><strong>View Details:</strong> Open a detailed profile of the employee.</li><li><strong>Edit Employee:</strong> Update employee details such as name or contact info.</li><li><strong>Edit Access:</strong> Modify the employee’s assigned role and permissions.</li><li><strong>Delete:</strong> Permanently remove the employee from the list.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-existing-employees-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Manage Existing Employees" class="wp-image-11385" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-existing-employees-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-existing-employees-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-existing-employees-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-existing-employees-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-existing-employees-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The Employee List gives you full control to view, edit, or remove employees, ensuring proper access and accurate staff records at all times.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:21.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:21.000000Z',
                ],
                117 => [
                    'id' => 118,
                    'doc_category_id' => 12,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-view-the-invited-employee-list-and-manage-it',
                    'title' => 'How to View the Invited Employee List and Manage It',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to view all invited employees in Menumium, check their invitation status, and manage actions like resending, copying, or deleting invitations.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-2-1024x576.webp" alt="View the Invited Employee List" class="wp-image-9344" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-2-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-2-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-2-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-2-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-2.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-employee-role-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Employee &amp; Role Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, click on <strong>User Management</strong> in the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>A sub-menu will appear. Select <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Navigate to Employee Role Setup" class="wp-image-11357" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-employee-role-setup-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-the-invited-employees-tab" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Invited Employees Tab</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Employee &amp; Role Setup</strong> page, you will see two tabs:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Employees</strong></li><li><strong>Invited Employees</strong></li></ul></li><li>Click on the <strong>Invited Employees</strong> tab to view all pending and past invitations.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-invited-employees-tab-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Open the Invited Employees Tab" class="wp-image-11388" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-invited-employees-tab-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-invited-employees-tab-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-invited-employees-tab-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-invited-employees-tab-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-invited-employees-tab-0a.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-view-the-invited-employee-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: View the Invited Employee List</h2><p>The <strong>Invited Employees</strong> tab displays:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Employee <strong>Email</strong></li><li>Assigned <strong>Role</strong></li><li>Assigned <strong>Branch</strong></li><li><strong>Invitation Date</strong></li><li><strong>Status</strong> (Pending / Accepted / Expired)</li></ul><p>At the top of the page, you will also see a summary:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Total Invitations Sent</strong></li><li><strong>Pending Invitations</strong></li><li><strong>Expired Invitations</strong></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-invited-employee-list-0b.webp" alt="View the Invited Employee List" class="wp-image-11395" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-invited-employee-list-0b.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-invited-employee-list-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-invited-employee-list-0b-768x436.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-manage-invitations" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Manage Invitations</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>To manage an invitation, click on the <strong>Action menu</strong> (three vertical dots) on the far right of the row.</li><li>Available options include:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Resend Invitation:</strong> Sends the invitation email again to the employee.</li><li><strong>Copy Invitation Link:</strong> Copies the unique invite link so you can share it manually.</li><li><strong>Delete:</strong> Permanently removes the invitation. A confirmation pop-up will appear before deletion.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-invitations-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Manage Invitations" class="wp-image-11390" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-invitations-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-invitations-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-invitations-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-invitations-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/manage-invitations-0a.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>For a quick look at invitation details, you can also click the <strong>Eye (👁) button</strong> next to the employee’s name.</p><p>The <strong>Invited Employees</strong> tab allows you to track pending invitations and manage them with ease, ensuring your team members can quickly join your Menumium account.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 8,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:22.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:22.000000Z',
                ],
                118 => [
                    'id' => 119,
                    'doc_category_id' => 13,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-a-new-delivery-man',
                    'title' => 'How to Create a New Delivery Man',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of adding a new delivery person in <strong>Menumium</strong>. By setting up delivery personnel, you can assign orders and manage delivery operations more effectively.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-delivery-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Delivery Management</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>User Management</strong> to expand the menu.</li><li>Select <strong>Delivery Management</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-1024x579.webp" alt="Navigation" class="wp-image-11525" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d.webp 1908w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-add-a-new-delivery-man" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Add a New Delivery Man</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Delivery Management page, click the <strong>+ Add New Delivery Man</strong> button.</li><li>A creation page will appear.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-creation-page-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="DM Creation Page" class="wp-image-11526" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-creation-page-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-creation-page-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-creation-page-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-creation-page-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-creation-page-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-enter-basic-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Enter Basic Information</h2><p>Fill in the required details:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>First Name &amp; Last Name</strong> – Enter the delivery person’s full name.</li><li><strong>Phone Number &amp; Email</strong> – Provide valid contact details.</li><li><strong>Maximum Assign Order</strong> – Set the maximum number of orders this delivery person can handle at one time.</li><li><strong>Branch Assignment</strong> – Choose the branch where the delivery person will be assigned from the dropdown list.</li><li><strong>Address </strong>– Enter the delivery person’s residential address.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Setup Basic Info" class="wp-image-11527" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-basic-info-0a.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-upload-delivery-man-image" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Upload Delivery Man Image</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Click on the image upload section to add a profile picture.</li><li>Supported formats: <strong>PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-dm-image-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Add DM Image" class="wp-image-11528" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-dm-image-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-dm-image-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-dm-image-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-dm-image-0a-1536x862.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-dm-image-0a.webp 1914w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-provide-identity-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Provide Identity Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under the <strong>Identity Type</strong> field, select the type of identification:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Passport</li><li>National ID</li><li>Driving License</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/identity-info-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Identity Info" class="wp-image-11529" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/identity-info-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/identity-info-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/identity-info-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/identity-info-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/identity-info-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the <strong>Identity Number</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="ID Number" class="wp-image-11530" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Upload an image of the document by dragging and dropping it into the upload area or by browsing files.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="ID Number" class="wp-image-11531" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0b-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-number-0b.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-the-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save the Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all fields are completed, click the <strong>Save &amp; Continue</strong> button.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Save &amp; Continue" class="wp-image-11533" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-0a.webp 1911w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A success message will appear confirming that the <strong>Delivery Man was added successfully</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="574" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-delivery-information-0a.webp" alt="Save the Delivery Information" class="wp-image-11535" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-delivery-information-0a.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-delivery-information-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-the-delivery-information-0a-768x431.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your new delivery person is now added to the system and can be assigned to orders.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:23.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:23.000000Z',
                ],
                119 => [
                    'id' => 120,
                    'doc_category_id' => 13,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-quickly-access-deliveryman-details',
                    'title' => 'How to Quickly Access Deliveryman Details',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to quickly view a deliveryman’s details in Menumium from Delivery Man List, including basic info, joining date, address, and assigned orders.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-user-management-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the User Management Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>User Management</strong> to expand the menu.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-select-the-eye-icon-to-view-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Eye Icon to view details.</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under Action, click on the Eye button.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="Eye Icon" class="wp-image-11582" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-0b-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-0b.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A form will appear with the deliveryman’s details including basic info, joining date, address, assigned orders, and ongoing orders.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-details-0c-1024x577.webp" alt="Eye Icon Details" class="wp-image-11586" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-details-0c-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-details-0c-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-details-0c-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-details-0c-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-icon-details-0c.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:23.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:23.000000Z',
                ],
                120 => [
                    'id' => 121,
                    'doc_category_id' => 13,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-update-a-deliverymans-account-details',
                    'title' => 'How to Update a Deliveryman’s Account Details',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to update or edit a deliveryman’s personal, vehicle, and document details in <strong>Menumium</strong> through the admin dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-user-management-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the User Management Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>User Management</strong> to expand the menu.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-go-to-the-deliveryman-management-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Go to the Deliveryman Management Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under <strong>User Management</strong>, click on <strong>Deliveryman Management</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-1024x579.webp" alt="Navigation" class="wp-image-11525" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigation-0d.webp 1908w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Navigate to the <strong>Deliveryman List</strong>, where all registered delivery personnel are displayed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-list-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="DM List" class="wp-image-11532" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-list-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-list-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-list-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-list-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-list-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-view-a-delivery-mans-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: View a Delivery Man’s Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the delivery man whose performance you want to check.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column on the right side, click the <strong>three-dot menu (⋮)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown options, select <strong>View Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-dm-details-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="View DM Details" class="wp-image-11537" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-dm-details-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-dm-details-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-dm-details-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-dm-details-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-dm-details-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>This will open the delivery man’s details page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="572" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-details-page-0a-1024x572.webp" alt="DM Details Page" class="wp-image-11538" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-details-page-0a-1024x572.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-details-page-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-details-page-0a-768x429.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-details-page-0a-1536x858.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-details-page-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>Delivery Man Details</strong> page displays basic information such as name, phone number, email, and address, along with details like assigned orders, working hours, assigned branch, and joining date.</li><li>On the profile page, scroll down to the <strong>Order Analytics</strong> section.</li><li>Here, you can see a detailed summary of the delivery man’s work, including:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Total Assigned Orders</strong></li><li><strong>Ongoing Orders</strong></li><li><strong>Delivered Orders</strong></li><li><strong>Returned Orders</strong></li></ul></li></ul><p>These numbers provide a quick and clear overview of the delivery man’s performance and workload.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-analytics-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="Order Analytics" class="wp-image-11590" style="width:1178px;height:auto" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-analytics-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-analytics-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-analytics-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-analytics-0b-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-analytics-0b.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Order List</strong> (with detailed order and invoice. You can also download invoice from there)</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-list-and-invoice-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="Order List &amp; Invoice" class="wp-image-11821" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-list-and-invoice-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-list-and-invoice-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-list-and-invoice-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-list-and-invoice-0b-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-list-and-invoice-0b.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>eye button</strong> under <strong>Action</strong> shows order details—quantity, price, comments, discount, coupon, VAT/Tax, and delivery charge. You can also access <strong>View Details</strong> and download the invoice from this section.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="574" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-0e-1024x574.webp" alt="Eye Button" class="wp-image-11593" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-0e-1024x574.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-0e-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-0e-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-0e-1536x861.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-0e.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-details-0c-1024x578.webp" alt="Eye Button Details" class="wp-image-11594" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-details-0c-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-details-0c-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-details-0c-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-details-0c-1536x866.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/eye-button-details-0c.webp 1913w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-select-the-deliveryman-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Select the Deliveryman to Edit</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the deliveryman whose details you want to update.</li><li>On the right side of their row, under the <strong>3 dots </strong>menu, click the <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="568" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-details-button-0a-1-1024x568.webp" alt="Edit Details Button" class="wp-image-11539" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-details-button-0a-1-1024x568.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-details-button-0a-1-300x166.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-details-button-0a-1-768x426.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-details-button-0a-1-1536x852.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-details-button-0a-1.webp 1914w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>This will open the Edit Deliveryman page.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-update-personal-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Update Personal Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>General Info</strong> – Update the deliveryman’s name, phone number, or email address.</li><li><strong>Maximum assign order</strong> – The number of orders a deliveryman can be assigned.</li><li><strong>Branch</strong> – Under which branch the deliveryman works.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="570" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-dm-details-page-0b-1024x570.webp" alt="Edit DM Details Page" class="wp-image-11541" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-dm-details-page-0b-1024x570.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-dm-details-page-0b-300x167.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-dm-details-page-0b-768x428.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-dm-details-page-0b-1536x856.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-dm-details-page-0b.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-upload-or-update-required-documents" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Upload or Update Required Documents</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Scroll down to the <strong>Documents Section</strong>.</li><li>Upload or replace verification files such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Driver’s License</li><li>National ID Card</li><li>Passport (if applicable)</li></ul></li><li>Ensure all files are clear and valid for compliance.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="572" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-information-0a-1024x572.webp" alt="ID Information" class="wp-image-11542" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-information-0a-1024x572.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-information-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-information-0a-768x429.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-information-0a-1536x858.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/id-information-0a.webp 1911w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-confirm-and-save-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Confirm and Save Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After making the updates, click “Save &amp; Continue”.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-edit-dm-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Save &amp; Continue Edit DM" class="wp-image-11543" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-edit-dm-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-edit-dm-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-edit-dm-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-edit-dm-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/save-and-continue-edit-dm-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation message will appear:<br><em>“Deliveryman details updated successfully.”</em></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="574" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-updated-confirmation-notification-0a-1024x574.webp" alt="DM Updated Confirmation Notification" class="wp-image-11599" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-updated-confirmation-notification-0a-1024x574.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-updated-confirmation-notification-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-updated-confirmation-notification-0a-768x430.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-updated-confirmation-notification-0a-1536x860.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/dm-updated-confirmation-notification-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The deliveryman’s profile is now updated with the latest information.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:24.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:54:24.000000Z',
