                192 => [
                    'id' => 193,
                    'doc_category_id' => 22,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-delete-a-menu',
                    'title' => 'How to Delete a Menu',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains the process of deleting an existing menu in Menumium.</p><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>This action is irreversible. Once deleted, the menu cannot be restored.</p></div></div><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-menu-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Menu Management</h2><p>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Menu Setup Management</strong> and click on <strong>Menu Management</strong>.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-setup-navigation-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Menu Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-11400" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-setup-navigation-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-setup-navigation-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-setup-navigation-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-setup-navigation-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-setup-navigation-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-management-nav-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Menu Management Nav" class="wp-image-11401" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-management-nav-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-management-nav-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-management-nav-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-management-nav-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/menu-management-nav-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-the-menu-to-delete" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Menu to Delete</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Menu List</strong> page, locate the menu you want to remove.</li><li>Click the <strong>three dots (â®)</strong> on the right side of the menu entry.</li><li>From the dropdown options, select <strong>Delete</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="574" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-button-menu-0a-1024x574.webp" alt="Delete Button Menu" class="wp-image-11453" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-button-menu-0a-1024x574.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-button-menu-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-button-menu-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-button-menu-0a-1536x861.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-button-menu-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-confirm-deletion" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Confirm Deletion</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up will appear. If the menu is currently assigned to any branches, the system will ask you to select an <strong>alternative menu</strong> for those branches.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-popup-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Delete Popup" class="wp-image-11454" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-popup-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-popup-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-popup-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-popup-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/delete-popup-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-deletion-0e.webp" alt="Confirm Deletion" class="wp-image-11470" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-deletion-0e.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-deletion-0e-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-deletion-0e-768x432.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Choose a replacement menu from the dropdown list.</li><li>Click <strong>Choose &amp; Delete</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/choose-and-delete-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Choose &amp; Delete" class="wp-image-11455" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/choose-and-delete-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/choose-and-delete-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/choose-and-delete-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/choose-and-delete-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/choose-and-delete-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The menu will now be permanently deleted, and if necessary, branches will be reassigned to the selected alternative menu.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:16.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:16.000000Z',
                ],
                193 => [
                    'id' => 194,
                    'doc_category_id' => 23,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-an-ingredient-category',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up an Ingredient Category',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Menumium allows you to organize your ingredients into categories for better inventory management. Categories make it easier to group, search, and manage ingredients efficiently.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-recipe-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-hand sidebar of your dashboard, click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong>.</li><li>A dropdown menu will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Inventory &amp; Recipe Management" class="wp-image-9127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-category-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Category Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Inventory Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Category Setup</strong>.</li><li>The system will open the <strong>Category List</strong> page, displaying all existing ingredient categories.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1024x581.webp" alt="Category Setup" class="wp-image-9128" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-create-a-new-category" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Create a New Category</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Category List</strong> page, click the <strong>+ Create Category</strong> button located in the top-right corner.</li><li>A <strong>Create Category</strong> pop-up window will appear.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1-1024x582.webp" alt="New Category" class="wp-image-9129" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1.webp 1896w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-fill-in-category-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Fill in Category Details</h2><p>In the pop-up, complete the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Category Name:</strong> Enter a descriptive name (e.g., <em>Green Vegetables</em>).</li><li><strong>Description (Optional):</strong> Add a short description of the category.</li><li><strong>Category Image:</strong> Click <strong>Browse</strong> to upload an image representing the category.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="587" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-category-detail-0a-1024x587.webp" alt="New (Create Category Detail)" class="wp-image-12008" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-category-detail-0a-1024x587.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-category-detail-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-category-detail-0a-768x440.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-category-detail-0a-1536x880.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-category-detail-0a.webp 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-the-category" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save the Category</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After filling out the details, click the <strong>Create</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up.</li><li>A success message will appear confirming the category creation:<br><br>â <em>âCategory created successfully.â</em><br></li><li>The new category will now be visible in the <strong>Category List</strong>.<em><br></em></li></ul></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:16.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:16.000000Z',
                ],
                194 => [
                    'id' => 195,
                    'doc_category_id' => 23,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-an-ingredient-category-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit an Ingredient Category in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to edit an existing ingredient category in <strong>Menumium</strong>. Updating a category allows you to change its name, description, or image to keep your inventory organized and up to date.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><p>Before setting up<strong> Ingredient,</strong> make sure you have set the “<strong>Category”</strong></p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dashboard, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Under <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong>, click on <strong>Inventory Setup</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Inventory &amp; Recipe Management" class="wp-image-9127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-category-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Category Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After clicking <strong>Inventory Setup</strong>, a new menu will appear.</li><li>Select <strong>Category Setup</strong> to view the list of all existing ingredient categories.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1024x581.webp" alt="Category Setup" class="wp-image-9128" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-a-category-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select a Category to Edit</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Category List</strong> page, locate the category you want to update.</li><li>Click the <strong>Edit (pencil) icon</strong> next to that category.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1-1024x582.webp" alt="Category to Edit" class="wp-image-9130" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-update-category-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Update Category Details</h2><p>A pop-up window titled <strong>Update Category</strong> will appear. Here you can modify:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Category Name</strong> – Update the name of the category.</li><li><strong>Description</strong> – Add or edit the description (optional).</li><li><strong>Category Image</strong> – Update the image if needed.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-change-the-category-image" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Change the Category Image</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>To upload a new image, click the <strong>Browse</strong> button or drag and drop a file into the upload area.</li><li>Supported formats: <strong>PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP</strong>.</li></ol><h2 id="step-6-save-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once you’ve made all the updates, click the <strong>Update</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up.</li><li>A success notification will appear at the bottom-left of the screen<br><br>â <em>“Category updated successfully.”</em></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="589" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-1-1024x589.webp" alt="Save Changes" class="wp-image-9131" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-1-1024x589.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-1-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-1-768x442.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-1-1536x883.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-1.webp 1871w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your category will now reflect the updated details in the <strong>Category List</strong>.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                195 => [
                    'id' => 196,
                    'doc_category_id' => 23,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-filter-ingredients-categories-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Filter Ingredients Categories in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to filter your ingredients categories in <strong>Menumium</strong> to quickly find and organize specific information within your inventory.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-ingredients-category-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Ingredients Category Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-hand navigation panel go to <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong>.</li><li>Under <strong>Inventory Setup</strong>, click on <strong>Category Setup</strong>.</li><li>The <strong>Category List</strong> page will open, displaying all your existing ingredient categories.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1024x581.webp" alt="Category Setup" class="wp-image-9128" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-the-filter-panel" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Filter Panel</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the top-right corner of the <strong>Category List</strong> page, locate the <strong>Filter icon</strong>.</li><li>Click the icon to open the <strong>Filter panel</strong>, which will slide in from the right side of the screen.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-1-1024x583.webp" alt="Filter Pane" class="wp-image-9132" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-1-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-1-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-1-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-1.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-your-filter-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select Your Filter Options</h2><p>The filter panel provides multiple options to refine your search:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All</strong> – View all categories.</li><li><strong>Active</strong> – Show only currently active categories.</li><li><strong>Inactive</strong> – Show only inactive categories.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Creation Date Range</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Filter categories based on when they were first created.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Modified Date Range</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Filter categories based on the last time they were updated.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Sort By</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Default (Newest to Oldest):</strong> Displays the most recently created categories first.</li><li><strong><strong>Oldest</strong> to Newest:</strong> Displays items starting from the earliest entries.</li><li><strong>Has Most Ingredients:</strong> Orders categories from those with the most ingredients to the fewest.</li><li><strong>Last Updates:</strong> Lists items based on the most recent changes or edits.</li></ul></li></ul><div class="wp-block-group doc-info"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><em><strong>Example</strong></em></p><p>To view only active categories, select <strong>Active</strong> under the <strong>Status</strong> filter.</p></div></div><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Reset Filters" class="wp-image-9133" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-1.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-apply-or-reset-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Apply or Reset Filters</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After selecting your filters, click the green <strong>Apply</strong> button at the bottom of the filter pane.</li><li>The category list will automatically refresh to show only the results that match your criteria.</li><li>To clear all filters and return to the full list, click the <strong>Reset</strong> button.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="587" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0a-1024x587.webp" alt="New (Filter Apply)" class="wp-image-12022" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0a-1024x587.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0a-768x440.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0a-1536x880.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0a.webp 1882w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can easily organize and locate categories based on their status, creation date, modification date, or ingredient count.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                196 => [
                    'id' => 197,
                    'doc_category_id' => 23,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-restore-deleted-inventory-categories',
                    'title' => 'How to Restore Deleted Inventory Categories',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will show you how to restore categories that have been deleted and are now stored in the <strong>Trash List</strong>. This feature is especially useful if a category was deleted by mistake and needs to be reactivated in your inventory.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the main dashboard, go to the left-hand navigation panel.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt; Inventory Setup</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Inventory &amp; Recipe Management" class="wp-image-9127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-category-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Category List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Under <strong>Inventory Setup</strong>, select <strong>Category Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Category List</strong> page, where all your active categories are displayed.</li></ol><h2 id="step-3-view-the-trash-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: View the Trash List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the top-right corner of the <strong>Category List</strong> page, click the <strong>View Trash</strong> button.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Category Trash List</strong>, which contains all deleted categories.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1024x583.webp" alt="Trash List" class="wp-image-9134" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-return-to-the-category-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Return to the Category List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Back to Category List</strong> button in the top-right corner of the card.</li><li>The restored category will now appear in your <strong>active category list</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-1024x576.webp" alt="Category List" class="wp-image-9135" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your category is now fully restored and active in the inventory again.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                197 => [
                    'id' => 198,
                    'doc_category_id' => 23,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-ingredients-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up Ingredients in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of setting up ingredients in the Menumium system. This is an essential step for managing your inventory and ensuring your recipes are accurately costed.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the Menumium dashboard, look at the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt; Inventory Setup</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Inventory &amp; Recipe Management" class="wp-image-9127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-ingredient-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select Ingredient Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under the <strong>Inventory Setup</strong> sub-menu, click on <strong>Ingredient Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will take you to the <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="New (Ingredient List)" class="wp-image-12028" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-add-a-new-ingredient" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Add a New Ingredient</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page, click the <strong>+ Create New Ingredients</strong> button located at the top right.</li><li>A <strong>Create Ingredient</strong> pop-up window will appear.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-1024x582.webp" alt="Add A New Ingredient" class="wp-image-9136" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.webp 1896w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-fill-out-ingredient-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Fill Out Ingredient Details</h2><p>In the pop-up, complete the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Ingredient Name:</strong> Enter the name of the ingredient (e.g., <em>Capsicum</em>).</li><li><strong>Select Category:</strong> Choose the appropriate category (e.g., <em>Green Vegetables</em>).</li><li><strong>Unit Type Category:</strong> Select the measurement unit — <strong>Weight, Volume, or Quantity</strong>.</li><li><strong>Low Stock Level:</strong> Set a minimum stock level to receive notifications when the ingredient runs low.</li><li><strong>Note:</strong> (Optional) Add a description or notes about the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Availability:</strong> Use the toggle to set the ingredient as <strong>Available</strong> or <strong>Unavailable</strong>.</li><li><strong>Ingredient Image:</strong> Upload an image of the ingredient by clicking <strong>Browse</strong> or dragging and dropping a file (formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="591" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0a-1024x591.webp" alt="Create Ingredient Details" class="wp-image-12029" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0a-1024x591.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0a-768x443.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0a-1536x886.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0a.webp 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-set-initial-stock-and-cost" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set Initial Stock and Cost</h2><p>If you want to add initial stock, toggle the <strong>Has Initial Stock</strong> option. Additional fields will appear:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Ingredient Type:</strong> Select <strong>Disposal</strong> (single-use) or <strong>Non-Disposal</strong> (reusable).</li><li><strong>Unit Price:</strong> Enter the cost per unit.</li><li><strong>Quantity:</strong> Specify the initial stock quantity.</li><li><strong>Expiry Date:</strong> (Visible if <em>Disposal</em> is selected) Set the expiration date.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="593" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0b-1024x593.webp" alt="Create Ingredient Details" class="wp-image-12031" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0b-1024x593.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0b-300x174.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0b-768x444.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0b-1536x889.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-ingredient-details-0b.webp 1863w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-the-new-ingredient" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save the New Ingredient</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After filling in all the details, click the <strong>Create</strong> button.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear — <strong>“Ingredient created successfully.”</strong></li><li>The new ingredient will now be listed in your <strong>Ingredients List</strong>, ready for stock and recipe management.</li></ol><p>You have now successfully added an ingredient, and it can be managed in recipes and inventory tracking across your Menumium system.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                198 => [
                    'id' => 199,
                    'doc_category_id' => 23,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-edit-an-ingredient',
                    'title' => 'How to Edit an Ingredient',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to update the details of an existing ingredient in Menumium. You can edit information such as the name, category, low stock level, notes, or image.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt;  Inventory Setup</strong> to expand the options.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Inventory &amp; Recipe Management" class="wp-image-9127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-ingredients-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Ingredients List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the expanded menu, click on <strong>Ingredient Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will take you to the <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page, where all existing ingredients are displayed.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="New (Ingredient List)" class="wp-image-12028" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-the-ingredient-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select the Ingredient to Edit</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page, find the ingredient you want to edit.</li><li>You can use the <strong>search bar</strong> at the top of the page to locate it quickly.</li><li>Once found, click the <strong>three-dot icon (â®)</strong> in the <strong>Action</strong> column for that ingredient.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-1024x586.webp" alt="New (Action Column)" class="wp-image-12035" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-1536x878.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-open-the-edit-panel" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Open the Edit Panel</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Update Ingredient [ID]</strong> will open, allowing you to modify the ingredient’s details.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-1024x583.webp" alt="Edit Panel" class="wp-image-9138" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-modify-ingredient-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Modify Ingredient Details</h2><p>In the <strong>Update Ingredient</strong> panel, you can update the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Ingredient Name:</strong> Edit the name of the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Category:</strong> Choose a new category from the dropdown. You can also click <strong>+ Add Category</strong> to create a new one.</li><li><strong>Unit Type Category:</strong> View or change the unit type (e.g., Weight, Volume, Quantity).</li><li><strong>Low Stock Level:</strong> Adjust the threshold to trigger low-stock alerts.</li><li><strong>Note:</strong> Add or update notes about the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Ingredient Image:</strong> Replace the existing image by uploading a new one (supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="591" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-1024x591.png" alt="Update Ingredients" class="wp-image-12036" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-1024x591.png 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-300x173.png 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-768x443.png 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-1536x886.png 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c.png 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save Your Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After making the desired updates, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom right of the panel.</li><li>A success notification — <strong>“Ingredient updated successfully”</strong> — will appear in the bottom left corner.</li><li>The updated details will now be reflected in the <strong>Ingredients List</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1024x580.webp" alt="Modify Ingredient Details" class="wp-image-9139" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.webp 1878w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You’ve successfully edited an ingredient in Menumium.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
