                295 => [
                    'id' => 296,
                    'doc_category_id' => 34,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-check-order-reports',
                    'title' => 'How to Check Order Reports',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Order Report</strong> in Menumium provides a complete overview of all orders placed within a specific time frame. You can use it to track sales, monitor statuses, and export order data for analysis. Each report includes details such as order ID, total amount, discounts, and taxes.</p><h2 id="step-1-go-to-reports-analytics" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Go to Reports &amp; Analytics</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dashboard, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>Reports &amp; Analytics</strong> to expand the submenu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Reports &amp; Analytics Navigation" class="wp-image-11687" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-orders-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Orders Report</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the submenu, select <strong>Orders Report</strong>.</li><li>The system will load the <strong>Orders Report</strong> page with today’s data by default.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/orders-report-page-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Orders Report Page" class="wp-image-11694" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/orders-report-page-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/orders-report-page-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/orders-report-page-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/orders-report-page-0a-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/orders-report-page-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-filter-by-date-range" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Filter by Date Range</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the top-right corner, click the <strong>Today</strong> button.</li><li>A calendar will appear where you can select a custom <strong>date range</strong>.</li><li>After choosing the desired dates, click <strong>Apply</strong> to refresh the report.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-by-date-range-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Filter By Date Range" class="wp-image-11698" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-by-date-range-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-by-date-range-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-by-date-range-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-by-date-range-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-by-date-range-0a.webp 1896w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-view-order-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View Order Details</h2><p>The report will display a list of all orders along with their key information:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Order ID</strong></li><li><strong>Total Amount</strong></li><li><strong>Discount</strong></li><li><strong>Tax</strong></li></ul><p>You can also see a status overview:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All Orders</strong> – Total number of orders.</li><li><strong>Ongoing Orders</strong> – Currently being processed.</li><li><strong>Completed Orders</strong> – Successfully fulfilled.</li><li><strong>Cancelled Orders</strong> – Orders canceled by customer or admin.</li><li><strong>Return Orders</strong> – Orders returned after completion.</li><li><strong>Failed to Deliver</strong> – Orders that could not be delivered.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="View Order Details of Reports" class="wp-image-11699" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0a.webp 1896w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>To view a detailed breakdown of any specific order, click the <strong>Eye (👁) icon</strong> under the <strong>Action</strong> column. This will open a page with full order details, including:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Ordered items</li><li>Payment details</li><li>Customer information</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0b-1024x582.webp" alt="View Order Details of Reports" class="wp-image-11700" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0b-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0b-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0b-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-order-details-of-reports-0b.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-export-the-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Export the Report</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>At the top of the order list, click the green <strong>Export</strong> button.</li><li>The system will download the data in <strong>.XLS format</strong>, which you can open in spreadsheet tools like Excel or Google Sheets.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0b-1024x586.webp" alt="Export The Report" class="wp-image-11701" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0b-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0b-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0b-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0b-1536x878.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0b.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The Order Report helps you analyze order activity, track performance, and export structured data for business insights—all in just a few clicks.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                296 => [
                    'id' => 297,
                    'doc_category_id' => 34,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-check-customer-reports',
                    'title' => 'How to Check Customer Reports',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Customer Report</strong> in Menumium allows you to analyze customer activity, monitor their order history, and view detailed analytics for each customer. This feature helps track loyalty, identify inactive or blocked customers, and gain insights into customer behavior.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-reports-analytics" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Reports &amp; Analytics</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dashboard, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Reports &amp; Analytics</strong> to expand the submenu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Reports &amp; Analytics Navigation" class="wp-image-11687" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-the-customers-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Customers Report</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the submenu, select <strong>Customers Report</strong>.</li><li>The system will load the <strong>Customer Report</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-reports-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Customer Reports" class="wp-image-11704" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-reports-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-reports-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-reports-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-reports-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-reports-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-view-customer-summary" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: View Customer Summary</h2><p>At the top of the Customer Report page, you’ll see an overview of customer data, including:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Total Customers</strong></li><li><strong>Active Customers</strong></li><li><strong>Inactive Customers</strong></li><li><strong>Blocked Customers</strong></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-customers-report-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Open The Customers Report" class="wp-image-11706" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-customers-report-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-customers-report-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-customers-report-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-customers-report-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/open-the-customers-report-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-review-the-customer-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Review the Customer List</h2><p>Below the summary, you will find a detailed list of all registered customers.<br>The list includes:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Customer Name</strong></li><li><strong>Total Orders</strong></li><li><strong>Order Statuses</strong> (Delivered, Canceled, Refunded, etc.)</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-summary-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="View Customer Summary" class="wp-image-11707" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-summary-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-summary-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-summary-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-summary-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-summary-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-view-customer-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: View Customer Details</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>To view a specific customer’s details, locate them in the list.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>Eye (ð) icon</strong>.</li><li>This opens the customer’s <strong>Profile Page</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/review-the-customer-list-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Review The Customer List" class="wp-image-11708" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/review-the-customer-list-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/review-the-customer-list-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/review-the-customer-list-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/review-the-customer-list-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/review-the-customer-list-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-explore-the-customer-profile" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Explore the Customer Profile</h2><p>When you click on the <strong>eye</strong> button, it will redirect you to the customer profile under <strong>User Management &gt; Customer Setup</strong>.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Profile Analytics</strong> – Total orders and reservations.</li><li><strong>Order Analytics</strong> – Completion rate, ongoing orders, and cancellation rate.</li><li><strong>Order History</strong> – A complete list of past orders with details like <strong>Order ID, Date, Total Amount, and Status</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-details-0b-1024x584.webp" alt="View Customer Details" class="wp-image-11709" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-details-0b-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-details-0b-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-details-0b-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-details-0b-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-customer-details-0b.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Customer Reports give you a complete picture of each customer’s activity, helping you track loyalty, identify patterns, and improve customer relationship management.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                297 => [
                    'id' => 298,
                    'doc_category_id' => 34,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-check-calculate-vat-taxes',
                    'title' => 'How to Check & Calculate VAT/Taxes',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The VAT/TAX Report in Menumium helps you track and calculate taxes on your sales. You can see and filter the transactions in two ways. One is Order Wise Tax, and another one is “Reservation Wise Tax”.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-vat-tax-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the VAT/TAX Report</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Reports &amp; Analytics</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>VAT/TAX Report</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1024x585.webp" alt="VAT/TAX Report" class="wp-image-9050" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.webp 1887w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-apply-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Apply Filters</h2><p>Once on the VAT/TAX Report page, you can refine your report using filters:</p><p>If you choose to filter it Order Type-wise-</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Select Date Range</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the calendar field and choose a start and end date (e.g., <em>September 1, 2025 – September 4, 2025</em>).</li></ul></li><li><strong>Select Order Type</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Choose one or multiple order types: <strong>Dine In, Take Away, or Home Delivery</strong>.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Select Branch</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>If you have multiple branches, use the dropdown to select locations (e.g., <em>ECB, Lalbag, Main Branch</em>).</li></ul></li></ul><p>After setting your filters, click the <strong>Filter</strong> button.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0a-1024x586.webp" alt="Apply Filters-Reports" class="wp-image-11716" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0a-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0a-1536x878.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0a.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The dashboard will refresh to display:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Total Orders</li><li>Total Order Amount</li><li>Total Tax Amount</li></ul><p>Or, if you want to filter the data reservation-wise,” Click on the <strong>Reservation Wise Tax</strong> tab to switch views.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Select Date Range</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select a specific date range from the calendar. This will filter the report to show reservations made within those dates.</li></ul></li></ul><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Branch</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>If your business has multiple branches, you can select a specific branch from the dropdown menu to see a report for that location only.</li></ul></li></ul><p>After setting your filters, click the Filter button.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0b-1024x577.webp" alt="Apply Filters-Reports" class="wp-image-11720" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0b-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0b-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apply-filters-reports-0b.webp 1888w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You can also:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the <strong>search bar</strong> to quickly find orders by ID or keyword.</li><li>Adjust the number of entries per page (<strong>5, 10, 20, 50, or 100</strong>).</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-export-the-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Export the Report</h2><p>To keep a copy for compliance or analysis:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Export</strong> button.</li><li>The report will download as a <strong>XLS file</strong>, containing all filtered data.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0e-1024x584.webp" alt="Export The Report" class="wp-image-11718" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0e-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0e-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0e-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0e-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0e.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The VAT/TAX report gives you a clear breakdown of tax amounts across branches, dates, and order types, making it easier to stay compliant and analyze your financial performance.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                298 => [
                    'id' => 299,
                    'doc_category_id' => 34,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-check-ingredients-purchase-cost',
                    'title' => 'How to Check Ingredients Purchase Cost',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Ingredients Purchase Cost Report</strong> in Menumium allows you to monitor ingredient expenses, track purchasing trends, and analyze costs by category. This helps in managing budgets and optimizing supplier purchases.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1024x582.webp" alt="Ingredients Purchase Cost" class="wp-image-9051" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-reports-analytics" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Reports &amp; Analytics</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the Menumium <strong>Dashboard</strong>, look at the left-hand navigation panel.</li><li>Click on <strong>Reports &amp; Analytics</strong> to expand the menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Reports &amp; Analytics Navigation" class="wp-image-11687" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access Ingredients Purchase Cost Report</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the expanded menu, select <strong>Ingredients Purchase Cost</strong>.</li><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Ingredient Purchase Cost</strong> page, showing expense and pricing insights.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Access Ingredients Purchase Cost Report" class="wp-image-11724" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-ingredients-purchase-cost-report-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-filter-the-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Filter the Report</h2><p>Use the available filters to refine your report:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Date Range:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the calendar icon to select the start and end dates for the report period.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Category:</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the dropdown menu to filter by a specific ingredient category (e.g., <em>Vegetables, Meat, Dairy</em>).</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-the-report-0c-1024x583.webp" alt="Filter The Report" class="wp-image-11725" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-the-report-0c-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-the-report-0c-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-the-report-0c-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-the-report-0c-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-the-report-0c.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-view-the-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View the Report</h2><p>After applying your filters, click the <strong>View Cost</strong> button.<br>The report table will update to display:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Total Purchased Qty</strong> – Quantity of the ingredient purchased.</li><li><strong>Total Purchase Cost</strong> – The total money spent on the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Purchase Cost Per Unit</strong> – Cost per unit of the ingredient.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-report-0c-1024x582.webp" alt="View The Report" class="wp-image-11726" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-report-0c-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-report-0c-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-report-0c-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-report-0c-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-report-0c.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-export-the-report-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Export the Report (Optional)</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>To save the report, click the <strong>Export</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>The data will be downloaded in a file format (XLS) suitable for spreadsheets and further analysis.</li></ol><p>The Ingredients Purchase Cost Report helps you track spending, evaluate supplier costs, and make data-driven purchasing decisions.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                299 => [
                    'id' => 300,
                    'doc_category_id' => 34,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-check-the-transaction-history-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Check the Transaction History in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Transaction History</strong> feature in Menumium provides a detailed overview of all financial activities, including orders, expenses, and purchases. You can filter, review, and export this data for better financial tracking and reporting.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-reports-analytics" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Reports &amp; Analytics</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand side menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Reports &amp; Analytics</strong> to expand the dropdown menu.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Reports &amp; Analytics Navigation" class="wp-image-11687" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reports-and-analytics-navigation-0a.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-transaction-history" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open Transaction History</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the dropdown, select <strong>Transaction History</strong>.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Transaction History</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0f-1024x584.webp" alt="Export The Report" class="wp-image-11727" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0f-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0f-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0f-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0f-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/export-the-report-0f.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-explore-transaction-tabs" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Explore Transaction Tabs</h2><p>The Transaction History page includes separate tabs for different types of records:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Order</strong> – View all order-related transactions.</li><li><strong>Expense</strong> – Track expenses recorded in the system.</li><li><strong>Purchase</strong> – Review purchase-related transactions.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/explore-transaction-tabs-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="Explore Transaction Tabs" class="wp-image-11731" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/explore-transaction-tabs-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/explore-transaction-tabs-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/explore-transaction-tabs-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/explore-transaction-tabs-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/explore-transaction-tabs-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-filter-transactions" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Filter Transactions</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Filter</strong> button on the right side of the page.</li><li>Select a <strong>Date Range</strong> using the calendar tool.</li><li>Click <strong>Apply</strong> to view transactions within the chosen period.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-transactions-0b-1024x582.webp" alt="Filter Transactions" class="wp-image-11732" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-transactions-0b-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-transactions-0b-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-transactions-0b-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-transactions-0b-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filter-transactions-0b.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-view-transaction-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: View Transaction Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>To see a breakdown of a specific transaction, click the <strong>eye icon</strong> next to it.</li><li>A detailed window will open, showing:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Transaction details</li><li>VAT information</li><li>Tax calculations</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="View Transaction Details" class="wp-image-11733" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0a-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-export-the-history-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Export the History (Optional)</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>To save or share your data, click the <strong>Export</strong> button at the top-right corner.</li><li>The system will generate a downloadable file (XLS) with your filtered transaction records.</li></ul><p>The Transaction History report in Menumium helps you stay on top of your business finances by providing a clear record of orders, expenses, and purchases, complete with VAT and tax details.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0b-1024x584.webp" alt="View Transaction Details" class="wp-image-11734" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0b-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0b-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0b-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0b-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-transaction-details-0b.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                300 => [
                    'id' => 301,
                    'doc_category_id' => 34,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-check-and-create-expenses-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Check and Create Expenses in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Expenses</strong> feature in Menumium allows you to track business costs, categorize spending, and maintain accurate financial records. You can both <strong>review existing expenses</strong> and <strong>create new entries</strong> directly from the dashboard.</p><h2 id="how-to-check-expenses" class="wp-block-heading">How to Check Expenses</h2><h3 id="step-1-navigate-to-reports-analytics" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Reports &amp; Analytics</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Scroll down and click on <strong>Reports &amp; Analytics</strong>.</li><li>A sub-menu will appear. Select <strong>Expenses</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-check-expenses-0b-1024x578.webp" alt="How To Check Expenses" class="wp-image-11738" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-check-expenses-0b-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-check-expenses-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-check-expenses-0b-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-check-expenses-0b-1536x867.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-check-expenses-0b.webp 1909w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-view-the-expense-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: View the Expense List</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The <strong>Expenses List</strong> page will display a table of all recorded expenses.</li><li>You can use the <strong>Search Bar</strong> at the top to find entries by <strong>ID, type, or related keyword</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-expense-list-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="View The Expense List" class="wp-image-11739" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-expense-list-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-expense-list-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-expense-list-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-expense-list-0b-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/view-the-expense-list-0b.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-3-use-filters-for-specific-searches" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Use Filters for Specific Searches</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Expenses List page, click the <strong>Filter</strong> button on the right side.</li><li>A filter panel will appear with options such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Creation Date</strong> – Select a date range.</li><li><strong>Expense Type</strong> – e.g., <em>Rent, Insurance, Office Supplies</em>.</li><li><strong>Branch</strong> – Filter by a specific branch or location.</li><li><strong>Payment Method</strong> – e.g., <em>Cash, Bank Transfer, Card</em>.</li></ul></li><li>After selecting your criteria, click <strong>Apply</strong> to see filtered results.</li><li>To reset filters, click <strong>Reset</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/use-filters-for-specific-searches-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Use Filters For Specific Searches" class="wp-image-11740" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/use-filters-for-specific-searches-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/use-filters-for-specific-searches-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/use-filters-for-specific-searches-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/use-filters-for-specific-searches-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/use-filters-for-specific-searches-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="how-to-create-an-expense" class="wp-block-heading">How to Create an Expense</h2><h3 id="step-1-open-the-expense-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Open the Expense Form</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Expenses List</strong> page, click the <strong>+ Create Expense</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>A <strong>Create Expense</strong> form will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-create-an-expense-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="How To Create An Expense" class="wp-image-11741" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-create-an-expense-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-create-an-expense-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-create-an-expense-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-create-an-expense-0a-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/how-to-create-an-expense-0a.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-fill-out-the-expense-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Fill Out the Expense Details</h3><p>Complete the required fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Expense Type</strong> – Select a category from the dropdown (e.g., <em>Insurance, Utilities</em>).</li><li><strong>Amount</strong> – Enter the expense value.</li><li><strong>Date of Expense</strong> – Choose the date using the calendar icon.</li><li><strong>Payment Method</strong> – Select how the payment was made (e.g., <em>Cash, Card</em>).</li><li><strong>Branch</strong> – Choose the branch this expense applies to.</li><li><strong>Description/Comment</strong> – Add any relevant notes for internal reference.</li><li>Once all fields are filled, click the green <strong>Create</strong> button at the bottom.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear, and the new expense will be added to the <strong>Expenses List</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-expense-details-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="Fill Out The Expense Details" class="wp-image-11742" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-expense-details-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-expense-details-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-expense-details-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-expense-details-0a-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fill-out-the-expense-details-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p><strong><br></strong>By checking and creating expenses in Menumium, you can keep your business finances transparent, organized, and branch-specific, ensuring better financial planning and reporting.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                301 => [
                    'id' => 302,
                    'doc_category_id' => 35,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-create-and-update-taxes-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Create and Update Taxes in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to set up, edit, and update taxes (e.g., VAT or service charges) within Menumium. Properly configured taxes can then be applied to customer orders.</p><h2 id="how-to-create-a-new-tax" class="wp-block-heading">How to Create a New Tax</h2><p>Follow these steps to add a new tax:</p><h3 id="step-1-navigate-to-tax-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Tax Setup</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Tax Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Create Tax</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Tax Button Navigation
" class="wp-image-11124" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-initiate-tax-creation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Initiate Tax Creation</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Tax List</strong> page, click the green <strong>+ Create Tax</strong> button (top-right).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-tax-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Create Tax Button
" class="wp-image-11125" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-tax-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-tax-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-tax-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-tax-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/create-tax-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-3-enter-tax-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Enter Tax Details</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Create Tax</strong> form, fill out:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Tax Name</strong> – Enter a descriptive name (e.g., VAT, Service Charge).</li><li><strong>Tax Rate (%)</strong> – Enter the tax percentage (without the % sign).</li><li><strong>Status</strong> – Toggle ON to activate immediately, or OFF to save as inactive.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-create-1024x576.webp" alt="Create" class="wp-image-9238" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-create-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-create-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-create-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-create-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1.-create.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-4-save-the-tax" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save the Tax</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Create</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear: <em>“The tax was created successfully.”</em></li><li>The new tax will now appear in the <strong>Tax List</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="how-to-edit-or-update-an-existing-tax" class="wp-block-heading">How to Edit or Update an Existing Tax</h2><p>To modify an existing tax:</p><h3 id="step-1-access-edit-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Edit Options</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Tax Setup &gt; Create Tax</strong>, all available <strong>Tax Lists</strong> will show there.</li><li>In the <strong>Tax List</strong>, find the tax to edit.</li><li>Click the <strong>Three-dot menu (â®)</strong> → <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-details-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Edit Tax Details Button" class="wp-image-11127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-details-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-details-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-details-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-details-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-details-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-update-tax-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Update Tax Information</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Modify the <strong>Tax Rate (%)</strong> as required.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Save the Changes</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Update</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear: <em>“The tax was updated successfully.”</em></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-1024x576.webp" alt="Edit Tax" class="wp-image-9242" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-tax.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="how-to-change-a-taxs-status" class="wp-block-heading">How to Change a Tax’s Status</h2><p>You can activate or deactivate a tax without deleting it. Inactive taxes will not apply to orders.</p><h3 id="step-1-access-status-control" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Status Control</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Tax Setup &gt; Create Tax</strong>, all available <strong>Tax Lists</strong> will show there.</li><li>In the <strong>Tax List</strong>, click the <strong>Three-dot menu (â®)</strong> next to a tax.</li><li>Select the <strong>Status</strong> toggle.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Tax Status Button" class="wp-image-11133" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-button-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-button-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-toggle-the-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Toggle the Status</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Switch ON to activate, or OFF to deactivate the tax.</li></ul><h3 id="step-3-confirm-the-change" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Confirm the Change</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation pop-up will appear explaining the effect.</li><li>Click <strong>Confirm</strong>.</li></ul><h3 id="step-4-verify-the-update" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Verify the Update</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A success message will appear: <em>“The tax status was updated successfully.”</em></li><li>The updated status will be reflected in the list.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-1024x576.webp" alt="Tax Status" class="wp-image-9243" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-status.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can easily create, update, or manage the status of taxes across your restaurant branches in Menumium.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                302 => [
                    'id' => 303,
                    'doc_category_id' => 35,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-set-up-tax-settings-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Set Up Tax Settings in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to configure tax settings for your restaurant, including calculation methods, tax types, and optional charges.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><p>Before applying tax settings, you must first create at least one tax rate.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>, go to <strong>Restaurant Management</strong>  &gt; <strong>Tax Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Create Tax</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Tax Button Navigation" class="wp-image-11124" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-button-navigation-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the <strong>Tax Name</strong> and <strong>Tax Rate (%)</strong>.</li><li>Save the tax entry.</li></ul><p>Once created, you can assign these taxes in your system.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-tax-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Tax Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left-side menu, navigate to <strong>Dashboard Icon</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>Setup Tax</strong> to open the Tax Settings page.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-enable-taxes-in-the-system" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enable Taxes in the System</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Tax Settings</strong> page, toggle ON <strong>Allow Tax in the System</strong>.</li><li>Once enabled, additional configuration options will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-toggle-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Setup Tax Toggle" class="wp-image-11136" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-toggle-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-toggle-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-toggle-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-toggle-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-toggle-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-choose-tax-calculation-method" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Choose Tax Calculation Method</h2><p>Select how Menumium should calculate taxes:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Calculate VAT/Tax Include Food’s Price</strong> – This option calculates tax as a portion of the total food price. If selected, the total price shown on the menu already includes tax.</li><li><strong>Calculate VAT/Tax Exclude Food’s Price</strong> – This option calculates tax as an additional charge on top of the food price. This means the final bill will show the food price and then a separate tax amount.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-type-choose-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Tax Type Choose" class="wp-image-11137" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-type-choose-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-type-choose-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-type-choose-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-type-choose-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tax-type-choose-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-tax-types" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure Tax Types</h2><p>Choose how tax should apply across orders (If you choose “Calculate Vat/Tax Exclude Food’s Price”):</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Order Wise Tax</strong> – A single tax rate applies to the entire order.</li><li><strong>Category Wise Tax</strong> – Different tax rates apply by menu category (e.g., food vs. beverages).</li><li><strong>Food Wise Tax</strong> – Different tax rates apply per individual food item.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-type-1024x580.webp" alt="Setup Tax Type" class="wp-image-9247" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-type-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-type-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-type-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-type-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-type.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-set-up-tax-rates" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set Up Tax Rates</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Under <strong>Setup Vat/Tax Rate</strong>, select a previously created tax or create a new one.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-rate-1024x580.webp" alt="Setup Tax Rate
" class="wp-image-9246" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-rate-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-rate-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-rate-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-rate-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-tax-rate.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-configure-additional-charges-optional" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Configure Additional Charges (Optional)</h2><p>You can extend the tax application to extra charges:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle <strong>Setup Delivery Charge</strong> to apply tax to delivery fees.</li><li>Toggle <strong>Setup Tax Rate on Reservations Fee</strong> to apply tax to reservation charges.</li><li>Use the dropdown menus to select the applicable tax.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-additional-charges-1024x581.webp" alt="Configure Additional Charges" class="wp-image-9245" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-additional-charges-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-additional-charges-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-additional-charges-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-additional-charges-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-additional-charges.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-save-your-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Save Your Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all configurations are complete, click <strong>Save</strong> (top-right).</li><li>A success message will confirm your tax settings have been updated.</li></ul><p>With these steps, you can configure taxes in Menumium to match your business needs and local regulations.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                303 => [
                    'id' => 304,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-configure-order-settings-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Configure Order Settings in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to manage and customize the order settings in the Menumium platform, including order types, ID formats, cancellation reasons, token generation, and refund policies.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-order-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Order Settings</h2><p>To begin configuring, access the order and reservation settings in the admin panel:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium dashboard.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Settings</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Orders &amp; Reservation</strong>.</li><li>By default, the <strong>Orders</strong> tab will open, showing options for order management.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Access Order Settings" class="wp-image-12093" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-set-up-order-types" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Set Up Order Types</h2><p>This section allows you to enable or disable the types of orders supported on your platform.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Order Type</strong> section.</li><li>Use the checkboxes to enable or disable options like <strong>Home Delivery</strong>, <strong>Take Away</strong>, <strong>Dine-in</strong>, and <strong>Reservation</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> in the top-right corner to apply your changes.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-types-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Setup Order Types" class="wp-image-12094" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-types-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-types-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-types-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-types-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-types-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-customize-order-id-format" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Customize Order ID Format</h2><p>You can adjust how order IDs are generated to match your business preference.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Navigate to the <strong>Set Order ID Format</strong> section.</li><li>Choose your preferred format (e.g., <em>Date-Month-Year + Order ID</em> or <em>Numeric</em>) from the dropdown.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to confirm the new format.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-order-id-format-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Customize Order Id Format" class="wp-image-12095" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-order-id-format-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-order-id-format-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-order-id-format-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-order-id-format-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customize-order-id-format-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-order-cancellation-reasons" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure Order Cancellation Reasons</h2><p>Predefined cancellation reasons help track and analyze order cancellations by both customers and administrators.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Setup Order Cancel Reason</strong> section.</li><li>Toggle <strong>Setup Cancel Reason</strong> ON to enable the feature.</li></ul><h3 id="for-customer-cancellations" class="wp-block-heading">For Customer cancellations:</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle ON the <strong>For Customer</strong> option.</li><li>Click <strong>Add More Condition</strong> to add a new reason.</li><li>Edit reasons using the pencil icon or delete them using the cross icon.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-customers-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Order Cancellation Reason (Customers)" class="wp-image-12096" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-customers-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-customers-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-customers-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-customers-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-customers-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="for-admin-cancellations" class="wp-block-heading">For Admin cancellations:</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle ON the <strong>For Admin</strong> option.</li><li>Click <strong>Add More Condition</strong> to add reasons for administrator cancellations.</li><li>Edit reasons using the pencil icon or delete them using the cross icon.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> after making any changes.<br></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-admin-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Order Cancellation Reason (Admin)" class="wp-image-12097" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-admin-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-admin-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-admin-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-admin-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-cancellation-reason-admin-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-set-up-the-token-generation-process" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set Up the Token Generation Process</h2><p>This section determines how unique tokens are created for each order.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Select Token Generate Process for Each Order</strong> section.</li><li>Choose one of the following options:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Manually</strong>: Assign tokens manually for each order.</li><li><strong>System Generated</strong>: Let the system automatically create tokens.</li></ul></li><li>If you select <strong>System Generated</strong>, choose the format (e.g., <em>Numeric</em> or <em>Delivery Type + Number</em>) from the dropdown.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply the settings.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-token-generation-process-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Setup Token Generation Process" class="wp-image-12098" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-token-generation-process-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-token-generation-process-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-token-generation-process-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-token-generation-process-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-token-generation-process-0a.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-set-up-order-refunds" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Set Up Order Refunds</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>To configure refund options, go to Refund Settings.</li><li>From there, you can manage how order and reservation refunds work.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-refund-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Setup Order Refund" class="wp-image-12099" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-refund-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-refund-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-refund-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-refund-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/setup-order-refund-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>For detailed steps, see the <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/general-settings/how-to-configure-refund-settings-in-menumium/">Refund Setup Documentation</a>.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
