                304 => [
                    'id' => 305,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-configure-reservation-settings-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Configure Reservation Settings in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to manage and customize reservation settings in Menumium, including booking fees, cancellation policies, payment options, and cancellation reasons.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-reservation-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Reservation Settings</h2><p>To begin configuring reservations, access the reservation management area in the admin panel:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Settings</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Orders &amp; Reservation</strong>.</li><li>Select the <strong>Reservation</strong> tab from the top navigation.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Access Order Settings" class="wp-image-12093" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-enable-advance-booking-fees-for-reservations" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enable Advance Booking Fees for Reservations</h2><p>This option allows restaurants to charge customers a booking fee for reservations.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the <strong>Need Advance Booking Fee for Reservation</strong> section at the top.</li><li>Toggle the switch ON to enable this feature.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> in the top-right corner to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/advance-booking-fee-toggle-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Advance Booking Fee Toggle" class="wp-image-12105" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/advance-booking-fee-toggle-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/advance-booking-fee-toggle-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/advance-booking-fee-toggle-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/advance-booking-fee-toggle-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/advance-booking-fee-toggle-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-set-booking-fees" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Set Booking Fees</h2><p>Once advance booking fees are enabled, you can configure how they are applied.</p><p><strong>Set a Common Booking Fee for All Reservations</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Set Booking Fee for Reservation</strong> section, select <strong>Set Common Booking Fee</strong>.</li><li>Enter the fixed fee amount in the text field.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-common-booking-fee-1024x580.webp" alt="Set Common Booking Fee" class="wp-image-9097" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-common-booking-fee-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-common-booking-fee-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-common-booking-fee-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-common-booking-fee-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-common-booking-fee.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p><strong>Set Individual Booking Fees per Floor or Table</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the same section, select <strong>Set Individual Fee</strong>.</li><li>To apply fees by <strong>floor</strong>, check <strong>Set Floor Reservation Fee</strong>, enter the fee, and set the multiplier, if you want.</li><li>To apply fees by <strong>table</strong>, check <strong>Set Table Reservation Fee</strong>, enter the fee, and set the multiplier, if you want.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply the changes.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-individual-booking-fee-1024x580.webp" alt="Set Individual Booking Fee" class="wp-image-9098" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-individual-booking-fee-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-individual-booking-fee-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-individual-booking-fee-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-individual-booking-fee-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-individual-booking-fee.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-reservation-cancellation-time" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure Reservation Cancellation Time</h2><p>This setting defines how far in advance (minimum lead time) a customer can cancel a reservation.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Min. Reservation Cancellation Time</strong> section.</li><li>Enter the cancellation period (in <strong>Months,</strong> <strong>Days,</strong> or <strong>Hours</strong> using the dropdown).</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-reservation-cancellation-time-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Configure Reservation Cancellation Time" class="wp-image-12107" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-reservation-cancellation-time-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-reservation-cancellation-time-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-reservation-cancellation-time-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-reservation-cancellation-time-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/configure-reservation-cancellation-time-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-set-up-reservation-payment-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set Up Reservation Payment Options</h2><p>You can choose how customers pay the booking fee.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Navigate to the <strong>Payment Option</strong> section.</li><li>Choose one:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Pay in First</strong> – Customers pay the fee when making the reservation.</li><li><strong>Pay Later</strong> – Customers can pay the fee afterward.</li></ul></li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-payment-options-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Reservation Payment Options" class="wp-image-12109" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-payment-options-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-payment-options-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-payment-options-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-payment-options-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/reservation-payment-options-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>To configure refund options on a reservation, go to <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/general-settings/how-to-configure-refund-settings-in-menumium/">Refund Settings</a>.</p><p></p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 2,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                305 => [
                    'id' => 306,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-configure-refund-settings-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Configure Refund Settings in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to manage refund policies and reasons for both orders and reservations in the Menumium dashboard.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-refund-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Refund Settings</h2><p>To begin managing refunds, access the refund management area in the admin panel:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click on <strong>Settings</strong>.</li><li>Select the <strong>Refund</strong> tab from the top navigation.</li><li>The refund configuration options will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Access Order Settings" class="wp-image-12093" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-order-settings-0a.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-enable-order-and-reservation-refunds" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enable Order and Reservation Refunds</h2><p>You can enable refunds for both orders and reservations.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Allow Order Refund</strong> section and toggle it ON.</li><li>Go to the <strong>Allow Reservation Refund</strong> section and toggle it ON.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply these changes.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-toggles-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Refund Toggles" class="wp-image-12118" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-toggles-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-toggles-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-toggles-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-toggles-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-toggles-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-set-a-refund-policy-for-orders" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Set a Refund Policy for Orders</h2><p>After enabling order refunds, you can set up a custom policy.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the <strong>Order Refund Policy Setup</strong> section.</li><li>Toggle the switch ON to activate.</li><li>Write your refund policy in the editor (supports text formatting such as bold, italics, and underline).</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to publish your policy.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/allow-order-refund-1024x580.webp" alt="Allow Order Refund" class="wp-image-9101" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/allow-order-refund-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/allow-order-refund-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/allow-order-refund-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/allow-order-refund-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/allow-order-refund.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-refund-reasons" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure Refund Reasons</h2><p>Predefined refund reasons help track and analyze refund requests effectively.</p><p><strong>For Orders</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Order Refund Reason Setup</strong> section.</li><li>Toggle the switch ON to enable.</li><li>Add reasons separately for <strong>Website Orders</strong> and <strong>POS Orders</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>Add More Condition</strong>, enter a reason, and click <strong>Add</strong>.</li><li>Use the <strong>pencil icon</strong> to edit or the <strong>cross icon</strong> to delete reasons.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><p><strong>For Reservations</strong></p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Scroll to the <strong>Reservation Refund Reason Setup</strong> section.</li><li>Toggle the switch ON to enable.</li><li>Add reasons by clicking <strong>Add More Condition</strong>, entering a reason, and clicking <strong>Add</strong>.</li><li>Use the <strong>pencil icon</strong> to edit or the <strong>cross icon</strong> to remove reasons.</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply changes.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-reasons-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Refund Reasons" class="wp-image-12119" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-reasons-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-reasons-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-reasons-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-reasons-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-reasons-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-set-a-refund-policy-for-reservations" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Set a Refund Policy for Reservations</h2><p>After enabling order refunds, you can set up a custom policy.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the <strong>Reservation Fee Refund Policy Setup</strong> section.</li><li>Toggle the switch ON to activate.</li><li>Write your refund policy in the editor (supports text formatting such as bold, italics, and underline).</li><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to publish your policy.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-policy-0c-1024x580.webp" alt="Refund Policy" class="wp-image-12120" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-policy-0c-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-policy-0c-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-policy-0c-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-policy-0c-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/refund-policy-0c.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 3,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                306 => [
                    'id' => 307,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-configure-default-invoice-settings-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Configure Default Invoice Settings in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to customize the appearance and content of your invoices, including layout, branding, and additional information.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-invoice-content-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Invoice Content Settings</h2><p>To begin configuring invoices, open the invoice setup area:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click on <strong>Settings</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Invoice Setup</strong> from the dropdown menu.</li><li>Go to the <strong>Default Invoice</strong> tab to view customization options.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Invoice Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12125" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-customize-invoice-content" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Customize Invoice Content</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Select Printing Sizes</strong>: Choose your preferred size from the dropdown (currently available: <em>Thermal 85mm</em>; more options are being added soon).</li><li><strong>Set Invoice Date &amp; Time Format</strong>: Choose how date and time are displayed (e.g., <em>dd-mm-yy</em>, <em>dd-mm-yy hh:mm</em>) from the drop down.</li><li><strong>Show Order Date</strong>: Enable this option to display the order date on invoices.</li><li><strong>Show Printing Date</strong>: Enable this option to display the printing date on invoices.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-customize-invoice-content-1024x581.webp" alt="Customize Invoice Content" class="wp-image-9106" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-customize-invoice-content-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-customize-invoice-content-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-customize-invoice-content-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-customize-invoice-content-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-customize-invoice-content.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-add-logo-and-business-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Add Logo and Business Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Logo on Invoice</strong>: Toggle <em>Show Logo on Invoice?</em> ON to include your logo. You can use the existing business logo or upload a new one.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Invoice Logo" class="wp-image-12126" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Business Identification Number</strong>: Toggle ON to display your ID. Enter your <strong>ID Name</strong> and <strong>ID Number</strong>.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Use <strong>+ Add More</strong> to add multiple IDs.</li><li>Use the <strong>x icon</strong> to remove entries.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-id-number-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Business Id Number" class="wp-image-12127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-id-number-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-id-number-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-id-number-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-id-number-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/business-id-number-0b.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Branch Information</strong>: Toggle <em>Show Branch Info on Invoice?</em> ON.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Check the boxes for <strong>Branch Name</strong>, <strong>Phone Number</strong>, <strong>Email</strong>, or <strong>Address</strong> to include this information.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-information-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Branch Information" class="wp-image-12128" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-information-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-information-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-information-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-information-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-information-0b.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-add-terms-and-copyright-text" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Add Terms and Copyright Text</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Terms &amp; Conditions</strong>: Toggle <em>Show terms &amp; conditions?</em> ON and enter your content in the text box.</li><li><strong>Copyright Text</strong>: Toggle <em>Show copyright text?</em> ON and type your desired copyright note.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/terms-copyright-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Terms &amp; Copyright" class="wp-image-12130" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/terms-copyright-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/terms-copyright-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/terms-copyright-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/terms-copyright-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/terms-copyright-0b.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-your-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save Your Settings</h2><p>Once all configurations are complete, click the green <strong>Save</strong> button to apply the changes to your invoices.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 4,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                307 => [
                    'id' => 308,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-change-kitchen-invoice-settings-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Change Kitchen Invoice Settings in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to customize your <strong>Kitchen Invoice Settings</strong>, including adding a logo, displaying order details, managing product information, and adding copyright text.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-settings-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Settings Menu</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click on <strong>Settings</strong> (located at the bottom of the menu).</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-go-to-invoice-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Go to Invoice Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the Settings menu, select <strong>Invoice Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Invoice Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12125" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-setup-navigation-0a.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-the-kitchen-invoice-tab" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select the Kitchen Invoice Tab</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Invoice Setup page, you’ll see two tabs: <strong>Default Invoice</strong> and <strong>Kitchen Invoice</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Kitchen Invoice</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-enable-kitchen-invoice-customization" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Enable Kitchen Invoice Customization</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>By default, kitchen invoices use the same settings as the default invoice.</li><li>To customize, toggle ON <strong>Do you want to set a different invoice for kitchen invoices?</strong></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kitchen-invoice-toggle-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Kitchen Invoice Toggle" class="wp-image-12133" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kitchen-invoice-toggle-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kitchen-invoice-toggle-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kitchen-invoice-toggle-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kitchen-invoice-toggle-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/kitchen-invoice-toggle-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-customize-invoice-logo" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Customize Invoice Logo</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle ON <strong>Show Logo on Invoice?</strong> to display a logo.</li><li>Choose between:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Business Logo</strong> – Use your existing logo.</li><li><strong>Upload New</strong> – Add a new logo (supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP).</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Invoice Logo" class="wp-image-12134" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/invoice-logo-0b.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-set-order-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Set Order Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Go to the <strong>Set Order Information</strong> section.</li><li>Check or uncheck boxes to display details such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Token No</strong></li><li><strong>Order Type</strong></li><li><strong>Table No</strong></li><li><strong>Counter No</strong></li><li><strong>Processing Time</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-information-0b-1024x579.webp" alt="Order Information" class="wp-image-12135" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-information-0b-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-information-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-information-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-information-0b-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/order-information-0b.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-set-product-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Set Product Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Set Product Information</strong> section, select which product details appear on the invoice.</li><li>Options include:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Product Name</strong></li><li><strong>Product Quantity</strong></li><li><strong>Product Price</strong></li><li><strong>Special Instruction</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/product-information-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Product Information" class="wp-image-12136" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/product-information-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/product-information-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/product-information-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/product-information-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/product-information-0b.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-8-add-copyright-text" class="wp-block-heading">Step 8: Add Copyright Text</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Toggle ON <strong>Show copyright text?</strong>.</li><li>Enter your desired text in the provided field.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/copyright-0e-1024x580.webp" alt="Copyright" class="wp-image-12137" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/copyright-0e-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/copyright-0e-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/copyright-0e-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/copyright-0e-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/copyright-0e.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-9-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 9: Save Your Changes</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After making adjustments, click <strong>Save</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation notification will appear once your settings are updated successfully.</li></ul></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 5,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                308 => [
                    'id' => 309,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-manage-branch-wise-access-and-controls-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Manage Branch-Wise Access and Controls in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to configure different levels of access and control for individual branches within the Menumium system.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-branch-access-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Branch Access Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click the <strong>Settings</strong> icon.</li><li>Select <strong>Branch Access Setup</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-access-setup-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="Branch Access Setup Navigation" class="wp-image-12147" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-access-setup-navigation-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-access-setup-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-access-setup-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-access-setup-navigation-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/branch-access-setup-navigation-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-enable-branch-access-controls" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enable Branch Access Controls</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch Access Setup</strong> page, toggle ON <strong>Manage Branch Wise Access &amp; Controls</strong>.</li><li>Once enabled, a list of available branches will appear. Select the branch you want to configure (e.g., <em>Texas</em>).</li></ul><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>If a section is turned OFF, only the <strong>Super Admin</strong> can manage activities for that section.</p></div></div><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-enable-branch-access-controls-1024x580.webp" alt="Enable Branch Access Controls" class="wp-image-9118" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-enable-branch-access-controls-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-enable-branch-access-controls-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-enable-branch-access-controls-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-enable-branch-access-controls-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-enable-branch-access-controls.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-configure-marketing-and-promotion-access" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Configure Marketing and Promotion Access</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find <strong>Give Access to Branch to Manage Marketing &amp; Promotional Activity</strong>.</li><li>Toggle ON to allow the branch to manage promotions.</li><li>Select which promotions the branch can control:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Give Food Discounts</strong></li><li><strong>Coupon</strong></li><li><strong>Happy Hour</strong></li><li><strong>BOGO Offers</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-marketing-and-promotions-1024x580.webp" alt="Marketing and Promotions" class="wp-image-9119" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-marketing-and-promotions-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-marketing-and-promotions-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-marketing-and-promotions-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-marketing-and-promotions-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-marketing-and-promotions.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-configure-menu-management-access" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Configure Menu Management Access</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find <strong>Give Access to Branch to Manage Their Menu</strong>.</li><li>Toggle ON to grant menu control.</li><li>Define the level of control by selecting:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Edit Only Prices</strong> – Branch can change item prices.</li><li><strong>Can On/Off Menu Item</strong> – Branch can show/hide items based on availability.</li><li><strong>Can Update Food Stock</strong> – Branch can update stock counts for food items.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-menu-management-1024x581.webp" alt="Menu Management" class="wp-image-9120" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-menu-management-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-menu-management-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-menu-management-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-menu-management-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-menu-management.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-configure-order-type-access" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Configure Order Type Access</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find <strong>Give Access to Branch to Manage Their Order Type</strong>.</li><li>Toggle ON to allow the branch to manage order types.</li><li>The branch will then control the availability of:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Home Delivery</strong></li><li><strong>Takeaway</strong></li><li><strong>Dine-in</strong></li><li><strong>Reservation</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-manage-order-type-1024x579.webp" alt="Manage Order Type" class="wp-image-9121" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-manage-order-type-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-manage-order-type-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-manage-order-type-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-manage-order-type-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-manage-order-type.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-configure-branch-information-access" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Configure Branch Information Access</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Find <strong>Give Access to Branch to Manage Their Branch Info</strong>.</li><li>Toggle ON to allow the branch to update its own information.</li><li>Select which details the branch can edit:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Basic Information</strong></li><li><strong>Area &amp; Delivery Charge</strong></li><li><strong>Working Hours</strong></li><li><strong>Inventory</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-branch-info-1024x581.webp" alt="Branch Info" class="wp-image-9122" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-branch-info-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-branch-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-branch-info-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-branch-info-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-branch-info.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Save Your Changes</h2><p>After setting up access for the branch, click <strong>Save</strong> to apply the changes.</p></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 6,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                309 => [
                    'id' => 310,
                    'doc_category_id' => 36,
                    'slug' => 'how-to-enable-google-login-for-customers-in-menumium',
                    'title' => 'How to Enable Google Login for Customers in Menumium',
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to enable and configure <strong>Google Login</strong> for customers within the Menumium dashboard, allowing faster and more personalized access.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-customer-login-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Customer Login Settings</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Menumium dashboard</strong>.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Settings</strong> (bottom left).</li><li>Select <strong>Customer Login</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-login-navigation-0b-1024x580.webp" alt="Customer Login Navigation" class="wp-image-12142" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-login-navigation-0b-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-login-navigation-0b-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-login-navigation-0b-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-login-navigation-0b-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/customer-login-navigation-0b.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-enable-google-login" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Enable Google Login</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Customer Login page, locate the <strong>Google Login</strong> option.</li><li>Toggle the switch ON to enable it.</li><li>A new section will appear with fields for:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Callback URL</strong></li><li><strong>Store Client ID</strong></li><li><strong>Store Client Secret Key</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-login-0c-1024x576.webp" alt="Google Login" class="wp-image-12143" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-login-0c-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-login-0c-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-login-0c-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-login-0c-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-login-0c.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-get-google-api-credentials" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Get Google API Credentials</h2><p>To connect Menumium with Google, you need API credentials from the Google Developer Console.</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your <strong>Google Developer Console</strong> and create a new project.</li><li>Navigate to the <strong>Credentials</strong> section.</li><li>Create a new <strong>OAuth 2.0 Client ID</strong> (if you don’t already have one).</li><li>Under <strong>Authorized redirect URIs</strong>, copy the <strong>Callback URL</strong> from Menumium and paste it here.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>This ensures customers are redirected back to your Menumium site after login.</li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="step-4-enter-credentials-in-menumium" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Enter Credentials in Menumium</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Copy the <strong>Client ID</strong> and <strong>Client Secret Key</strong> from your Google project.</li><li>Paste them into the corresponding fields in the Menumium dashboard.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-credentials-0b-1024x576.webp" alt="Enter Credentials" class="wp-image-12144" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-credentials-0b-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-credentials-0b-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-credentials-0b-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-credentials-0b-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-credentials-0b.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-the-configuration" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save the Configuration</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to apply your settings.</li><li>Once saved, Google Login will be available for customers on your site.</li></ul></div>',
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'order' => 7,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                310 => [
                    'id' => 311,
                    'doc_category_id' => 37,
                    'slug' => 'overview',
                    'title' => 'Overview',
                    'content_html' => '<p>6amMart is a complete multivendor and multipurpose eCommerce solution designed for operating various businesses simultaneously like Food, Groceries, eCommerce, Parcel, Pharmacy deliveries, etc from one platform. Developed for convenience, 6amMart offers a seamless experience through mobile apps and web interfaces.</p><p>It is built using Laravel (v12) and Flutter framework to offer a robust and scalable solution.</p><p>Laravel is a PHP framework known for its expressive and elegant syntax. It is robust and easy to understand, providing a solid foundation so you can focus on creating features without worrying about the underlying details.</p><p>Flutter, developed by Google, is an open-source framework for building mobile applications. It is used to create apps for both Android and iOS, making it a primary tool for cross-platform development.</p><p>6amMart consists of the following components –&nbsp;</p><p>3 Mobile Applications:&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Customer Application:</strong> Developed using Flutter, available for Android, iOS, and web.</p><p><strong>Delivery Boy Application:</strong> Developed using Flutter for Android and iOS.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Store Application:</strong> Developed using Flutter, available for Android and iOS.</p><p>2 Web Panels:</p><p><strong>Super Admin Panel:</strong> Built with Laravel, allowing role-based access management.</p><p><strong>Store Panel:</strong> Built with Laravel, allowing store owners to manage roles and access.</p><p>3 Websites:</p><p><strong>Web Application:</strong> Built with NextJS.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Web Application:</strong> Built with Flutter.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Landing Page:</strong> Developed using Laravel Blade.</p><p>Each component is designed to provide seamless functionality and integration, ensuring a smooth experience for all users involved in the 6amMart ecosystem.</p><p></p>',
                    'content_json' => '{}',
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T10:09:37.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T10:13:33.000000Z',
                ],
                311 => [
                    'id' => 312,
                    'doc_category_id' => 38,
                    'slug' => 'overview-2',
                    'title' => 'Overview',
                    'content_html' => '<p>First, you must deploy your admin panel on a remote server.&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p>Use the admin host URL as the base URL and use that for setting up your app.</p></li><li><p>You can also build the customer web using the same base URL. Build the web and deploy to your main domain.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p>Also, you can customise any part of the application according to your own.</p><p><strong>Warning</strong></p><p>If anything goes wrong with the customization you made, we won’t be responsible for that.</p><p></p>',
                    'content_json' => '{}',
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T10:09:39.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T10:18:27.000000Z',
                ],
                312 => [
                    'id' => 313,
                    'doc_category_id' => 39,
                    'slug' => 'prerequisite',
                    'title' => 'Prerequisite',
                    'content_html' => '<p><strong>6amMart</strong> is dependent on PHP version 8.2 or higher and MySQL version 5.7 or later. Additionally, the following server configurations and PHP extensions are necessary:</p><p>1. Mod_rewrite for Apache</p><p>2. BCMath PHP extension</p><p>3. Ctype PHP extension</p><p>4. JSON extension</p><p>5. Mbstring extension</p><p>6. OpenSSL extension</p><p>7. PDO extension</p><p>8. Tokeniser extension</p><p>9. XML extension</p><p>10. Zip extension</p><p>11. Fileinfo extension</p><p>12. Gd extension</p><p>13. Sodium extension</p><p>14. Mysql PDO extension</p><p>Typically, these extensions are enabled by default on most servers. However, it is advisable to verify the configuration with your hosting provider to ensure compatibility with the project.</p><p><strong>WARNING</strong></p><p>Please do this very carefully. We will not be responsible for your mistake.</p><p></p>',
                    'content_json' => '{}',
                    'order' => 1,
                    'status' => 'published',
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T10:09:39.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T10:14:34.000000Z',
                ],
                313 => [
                    'id' => 314,
                    'doc_category_id' => 39,
                    'slug' => 'local',
                    'title' => 'Environment Configuration',
                    'content_html' => '<h2><strong>Local</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#local">#</a></h2><p>Choose the right development environment for your local machine based on the operating system. Follow the instructions below for a smooth setup:</p><p>1. Windows (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://www.apachefriends.org/download.html">XAMPP</a>):</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;– Download and install XAMPP to set up a comprehensive local development environment on Windows.</p><p>2. Linux (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://www.apachefriends.org/download.html">LAMP</a>):</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;– Configure the LAMP stack on your Linux distribution for the local development environment.</p><p>3. MacOS (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://www.mamp.info/en/downloads/">MAMP</a>):</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;– Install MAMP to establish a compatible local development environment on MacOS.</p><p>Each choice gives you a flexible setup that fits well with your computer’s system. Watch the tutorial videos for step-by-step help while installing.</p><p></p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</p><p></p><p></p><h2><strong>CPanel</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#cpanel">#</a></h2><h3><strong>Database Configuration</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#database-configuration">#</a></h3><p>Before starting the admin installation, the database must be configured for the application.</p><p>For creating the database, the following ways must be maintained-</p><ul><li><p>Go to MySQL Databases</p></li></ul><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammrt-doc-admin-application-database-page-ss-1024x548.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Database SS" width="1024" height="548" containerstyle="width: 1024px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><ul><li><p>Create a new database for the application</p></li></ul><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammrt-doc-admin-application-create-a-new-database-ss-1024x547.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Create A New Database SS" width="1024" height="547" containerstyle="width: 1024px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><ul><li><p>Create a user for the database</p></li></ul><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammrt-doc-admin-application-create-user-for-database-ss-1024x545.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Create User For Database SS" width="1024" height="545" containerstyle="width: 1024px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><p></p><p><strong>WARNING</strong></p><p>Avoid using hash (“#”) in your password</p><p></p><ul><li><p>Add the user to the database</p></li></ul><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammrt-doc-admin-application-add-user-to-database-ss-1024x545.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Add User To Database SS" width="1024" height="545" containerstyle="width: 1024px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><ul><li><p>Give privileges to the user</p></li></ul><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammrt-doc-admin-application-add-user-privilege-ss-1024x504.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Provide Previlege To User SS" width="1024" height="504" containerstyle="width: 1024px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><p></p><p><strong>Info</strong></p><p>From one hosting provider to the next, the interface or step differs. Speak with your server provider if you’re having trouble configuring the database. You can also get in touch with us for any type of consulting if you need it.</p><p></p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p><strong>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</strong></p><p></p><p></p><h3><strong>Domain Configuration</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#domain-configuration">#</a></h3><p>Navigate to your cPanel and locate the page for domain configuration. For 6amMart, it is essential to have two domains or subdomains. Utilise your main domain to host the customer web panel.&nbsp;</p><p>Additionally, create a subdomain for the admin panel. For instance, if your domain is ‘example.com’, generate a subdomain such as ‘admin.example.com’ and host the admin panel on that subdomain.</p><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammart-doc-admin-application-domain-configuration-ss-1024x512.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Domain Configuration SS" width="1024" height="512" containerstyle="width: 1024px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</p><p></p><h3><strong>Digital Ocean</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#digital-ocean">#</a></h3><p>Initially, you must configure a droplet to host your application, allowing you to modify the configuration according to your business needs. We advise a minimum specification of 2 cores CPU paired with 4GB of RAM, with the option to increase resources for larger client bases.</p><p>Refer to the tutorial for additional details and guidance.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</p><p></p><h3><strong>Server Setup</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#server-setup">#</a></h3><p>To host an application on a Virtual Private Server (VPS), you need to configure the LAMP stack, which serves as the environment for PHP/Laravel applications. LAMP comprises Linux, Apache2, MySQL, and PHP. Alternatively, NGinx can be used instead of Apache2, but this tutorial focuses only on Apache2 configuration.</p><h4><strong>Installing LAMP Stack</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#installing-lamp-stack">#</a></h4><p>This guide will walk you through the process of setting up a LAMP stack on an Ubuntu server. Make sure you have an Ubuntu server instance with sudo privileges.</p><p>Run the following commands for installing required things-</p><ul><li><p>Step 1: Update Package Lists</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo apt update</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 2: Install Apache</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo apt install apache2 -y</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 3: Install MySQL</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo apt install mysql-server</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 4: Install PHP</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php php-mysql</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 5: Test PHP Processing</p></li></ul><pre><code>echo "&lt;?php phpinfo(); ?&gt;" | sudo tee /var/www/html/info.php</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 6: Additional PHP Modules</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo apt install php-bcmath -ysudo apt install php-ctype -ysudo apt install php-json -ysudo apt install php-mbstring -ysudo apt install php-openssl -ysudo apt install php-pdo -ysudo apt install php-tokenizer -ysudo apt install php-xml -ysudo apt install php-zip -ysudo apt install php-fileinfo -ysudo apt install php-gd -ysudo apt install php-sodium -ysudo apt install php-mysql -y</code></pre><p>Afterward, access the IP address, and you’ll be directed to the default Apache configuration page.</p><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammart-doc-admin-application-apache2-ubuntu-default-page-ss.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application Apache2 Ubuntu Default Page SS" width="850" height="730" containerstyle="width: 850px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><p>Check if the php is working correctly or not by hitting the URL <strong>YOUR_IP/info.php</strong> and you can see the system’s PHP configs.</p><p><img src="https://6ammart.app/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6ammart-doc-admin-application-php-version-ss.webp" alt="6amMart Doc Admin Application PHP Version Page SS" width="901" height="940" containerstyle="width: 901px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block;" wrapperstyle="display: inline-block; float: left; padding-right: 8px;"></p><p><strong>Info</strong></p><p>The following configurations are only for UBUNTU distro.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</p><h3><strong>Configure domain</strong>/<strong>sub-domain</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#configure-domain">#</a></h3><p>Make sure you have an Apache web server installed. For configuring domain or sub-domain in your VPS server, you must configure a vhost (Virtual Host) configuration file. Follow the steps below to configure vhost config file for both domain or sub-domain-</p><ul><li><p>Step 1: Navigate to Apache Sites Directory</p></li></ul><pre><code>cd /etc/apache2/sites-available/</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 2: Create a Virtual Host Configuration File</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/your_domain.com.conf</code></pre><p>Add the following content:</p><pre><code>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;    ServerAdmin webmaster@your_domain.com    ServerAlias www.your_domain.com    ServerName your_domain.com    DocumentRoot /var/www/your_domain.com/public_html    &lt;Directory /var/www/your_domain.com/public_html&gt;        Options -Indexes +FollowSymLinks        AllowOverride All        Require all granted    &lt;/Directory&gt;    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/error.log    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/access.log combined&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;</code></pre><p>Save the file and exit the text editor.</p><ul><li><p>Step 3: Enable the virtual host configuration file</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo a2ensite your_domain.com.conf</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 4: Reload the Apache2 server</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo systemctl reload apache2</code></pre><ul><li><p>Step 5: Test the Virtual Host</p></li></ul><p>Open your web browser and navigate to http://your_domain.com. You should see your website.</p><p><strong>Info</strong></p><p>The following configurations are only for UBUNTU distro.</p><h3><strong>Domain propagation</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#domain-propagation">#</a></h3><ul><li><p>Domain propagation refers to the process of updating DNS (Domain Name System) records across the internet, allowing a newly purchased domain or subdomain to become accessible globally.</p></li><li><p>To initiate the process, configure an A record for your domain and CNAME record for your subdomain. Alternatively, if preferred, you can opt to create an A record for your subdomain instead of a CNAME record.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Info</strong></p><p>Once DNS changes are made, propagation begins. It can take anywhere from a few minutes to 48 hours for DNS changes to propagate worldwide. During this time, some users might see the old site while others see the new one.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p>Once your domain is propagated, check from the follow site – <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://dnschecker.org/">https://dnschecker.org/</a></p><p>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</p><h3><strong>Setup SSL with Certbot on Apache</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#setup-ssl-with-certbot-on-apache">#</a></h3><p>SSL (Secure Socket Layer) is crucial for securing data transmitted between the user’s browser and your web server. Certbot is a free, open-source software tool for automatically managing SSL certificates.</p><p>In this guide, we’ll walk through the process of setting up SSL for your Apache web server using Certbot.</p><p>Before you begin, make sure you have:</p><p>An Apache web server installed.</p><p>A registered domain pointing to your server’s IP address.</p><p>The domain is accessible over HTTP (port 80).</p><p><strong>Step 1: SSH into the server</strong></p><ul><li><p>Access the server hosting your HTTP website via SSH using a user account with sudo privileges.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Step 2: Install snapd</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure that you install snapd and carefully follow any provided instructions to activate classic snap support.</p></li><li><p>Refer to the instructions provided on snapcraft’s website for installing snapd.</p></li></ul><pre><code>install snapd</code></pre><p><strong>Step 3: Remove certbot-auto and any Certbot OS packages</strong></p><ul><li><p>If you have any Certbot packages installed via an OS package manager such as apt, it’s advisable to uninstall them before installing the Certbot snap. This ensures that when you execute the command “certbot,” the snap version is utilized rather than the one from your OS package manager. For removing the certbot from the system run the following command-</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo apt-get remove certbot</code></pre><p><strong>Step 4: Install Certbot</strong></p><ul><li><p>Execute this command on the command line of your machine to install Certbot.</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo snap install --classic certbot</code></pre><p><strong>Step 6: Prepare the Certbot command</strong></p><ul><li><p>Run the following instruction on the command line of your machine to ensure that the certbot command can be executed.</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo ln -s /snap/bin/certbot /usr/bin/certbot</code></pre><p><strong>Step 7: Choose how you’d like to run Certbot</strong></p><ul><li><p>Either get and install your certificates…</p></li><li><p>Run this command to get a certificate and have Certbot edit your apache configuration automatically to serve it, turning on HTTPS access in a single step.</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo certbot --apache</code></pre><ul><li><p>Or, just get a certificate</p></li><li><p>If you’re feeling more conservative and would like to make the changes to your apache configuration by hand, run this command.</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo certbot certonly --apache</code></pre><p><strong>Step 8: Test automatic renewal</strong></p><ul><li><p>he Certbot packages on your system come with a cron job or systemd timer that will renew your certificates automatically before they expire. You will not need to run Certbot again, unless you change your configuration. You can test automatic renewal for your certificates by running this command:</p></li></ul><pre><code>sudo certbot renew --dry-run</code></pre><p><strong>Step 9: Confirm that Certbot worked</strong></p><p>To confirm that your site is set up properly, visit https://yourwebsite.com/ in your browser and look for the lock icon in the URL bar.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong></p><p>Recommended tutorial is below 👇</p><p></p><p></p><h3><strong>MySQL Database and User Setup</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#mysql-database-and-user-setup">#</a></h3><p>Setting up a MySQL database involves creating a database, creating a user, and assigning that user appropriate privileges. This guide will walk you through the process using MySQL commands.</p><p>Before you begin, make sure you have:</p><ul><li><p>MySQL installed on your server.</p></li><li><p>MySQL root access or a user with sufficient privileges.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Step 1: Log in to MySQL</strong></p><pre><code>sudo mysql</code></pre><p><strong>Step 2: Create a Database</strong></p><pre><code>CREATE DATABASE your_database_name;</code></pre><p>Replace <strong>your_database_name</strong> with the desired name for your database.</p><p><strong>Step 3: Create a MySQL User</strong></p><pre><code>CREATE USER \'your_username\'@\'localhost\' IDENTIFIED BY \'your_password\';</code></pre><p>Replace <strong>your_username</strong> with the desired username and <strong>your_password</strong> with the desired password for the user.</p><p><strong>Step 4: Grant All Privileges to the User for the Database</strong></p><pre><code>GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON your_database_name.* TO \'your_username\'@\'localhost\';</code></pre><p><strong>Step 4: Flush the privileges&nbsp;</strong></p><pre><code>FLUSH PRIVILEGES;</code></pre><p>Replace <strong>your_database_name</strong> with the name of the database created in Step 2 and <strong>your_username</strong> with the username created in Step 3</p><p><strong>Step 5: Exit MySQL</strong></p><pre><code>EXIT;</code></pre><p></p><h3><strong>phpMyadmin setup (optional)</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#phpmyadmin-setup">#</a></h3><p>Run the following commands for installing phpmyadmin in your system</p><pre><code>sudo apt update</code></pre><pre><code>sudo apt install phpmyadmin php-mbstring php-zip php-gd php-json php-curl</code></pre><p>Here are the options you should choose when prompted in order to configure your installation correctly:</p><ul><li><p>For the server selection, choose apache2</p></li></ul><p><strong>Warning</strong></p><p>When the prompt appears, “apache2” is highlighted, but not selected. If you do not hit SPACE to select Apache, the installer will not move the necessary files during installation. Hit SPACE, TAB, and then ENTER to select Apache.</p><ul><li><p>Select Yes when asked whether to use dbconfig-common to set up the database</p></li><li><p>You will then be asked to choose and confirm a MySQL application password for phpMyAdmin</p></li></ul><p>Restart the apache2 server-</p><pre><code>sudo systemctl restart apache2</code></pre><h2><strong>Project Setup</strong> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="batterdocs-anchor" href="#project-setup">#</a></h2><p>Upload your project in /var/www/your_domain.com/public_html and unzip the file</p><pre><code>apt install unzip</code></pre><pre><code>unzip your_file_name</code></pre><p>Then give permission to some specific files &amp; folders</p><pre><code>sudo chmod 755 .envsudo chmod 777 modules_statuses.jsonsudo chmod 777 app/Providers/RouteServiceProvider.phpsudo chmod -R 777 storagesudo chmod -R 777 bootstrap/cachesudo chmod -R 777 resources/lang</code></pre><p>Now you are ready to go for the installation.</p>',
