                43 => [
                    'id' => 44,
                    'doc_page_id' => 199,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to update the details of an existing ingredient in Menumium. You can edit information such as the name, category, low stock level, notes, or image.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt;  Inventory Setup</strong> to expand the options.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp" alt="Inventory &amp; Recipe Management" class="wp-image-9127" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/1-1.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-ingredients-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Ingredients List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the expanded menu, click on <strong>Ingredient Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will take you to the <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page, where all existing ingredients are displayed.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="New (Ingredient List)" class="wp-image-12028" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-the-ingredient-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select the Ingredient to Edit</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page, find the ingredient you want to edit.</li><li>You can use the <strong>search bar</strong> at the top of the page to locate it quickly.</li><li>Once found, click the <strong>three-dot icon (â®)</strong> in the <strong>Action</strong> column for that ingredient.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-1024x586.webp" alt="New (Action Column)" class="wp-image-12035" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a-1536x878.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-column-0a.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-open-the-edit-panel" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Open the Edit Panel</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Update Ingredient [ID]</strong> will open, allowing you to modify the ingredient’s details.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-1024x583.webp" alt="Edit Panel" class="wp-image-9138" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-modify-ingredient-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Modify Ingredient Details</h2><p>In the <strong>Update Ingredient</strong> panel, you can update the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Ingredient Name:</strong> Edit the name of the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Category:</strong> Choose a new category from the dropdown. You can also click <strong>+ Add Category</strong> to create a new one.</li><li><strong>Unit Type Category:</strong> View or change the unit type (e.g., Weight, Volume, Quantity).</li><li><strong>Low Stock Level:</strong> Adjust the threshold to trigger low-stock alerts.</li><li><strong>Note:</strong> Add or update notes about the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Ingredient Image:</strong> Replace the existing image by uploading a new one (supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="591" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-1024x591.png" alt="Update Ingredients" class="wp-image-12036" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-1024x591.png 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-300x173.png 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-768x443.png 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c-1536x886.png 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-ingredients-0c.png 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save Your Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After making the desired updates, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom right of the panel.</li><li>A success notification — <strong>“Ingredient updated successfully”</strong> — will appear in the bottom left corner.</li><li>The updated details will now be reflected in the <strong>Ingredients List</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1024x580.webp" alt="Modify Ingredient Details" class="wp-image-9139" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.webp 1878w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You’ve successfully edited an ingredient in Menumium.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
