                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to use the filter options to quickly narrow down your ingredient list in Menumium. Filtering helps you find specific items based on their status, category, or date.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-ingredients-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Ingredients List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt; Inventory Setup</strong> in the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Select <strong>Ingredient Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will open the main <strong>Ingredients List</strong> page.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-open-the-filter-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Filter Menu</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>top-right corner</strong> of the Ingredients List page, click the <strong>Filter</strong> button.</li><li>A filter menu will slide out from the right side of the screen.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15-1024x582.webp" alt="Filter Menu" class="wp-image-9141" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/15.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-apply-filters" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply Filters</h2><p>The filter menu offers multiple options to refine your search:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status Type</strong> – Filter ingredients by status:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All</strong> – Show every ingredient.</li><li><strong>Active</strong> – Show only active ingredients.</li><li><strong>Inactive</strong> – Show only inactive ones.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Creation Date</strong> – Use the calendar to select a date range for when ingredients were first added.</li><li><strong>Modified Date</strong> – Choose a date range to find ingredients that were recently updated.</li><li><strong>Category</strong> – Select one or more categories from the dropdown to show only ingredients belonging to those categories.</li><li><strong>Sort By</strong> – Rearrange the ingredient list using options such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Newest to Oldest</strong></li><li><strong>Most Purchased</strong></li><li><strong>Out of Stock First</strong></li><li><strong>Closest to Expiry</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="587" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-0a-1024x587.webp" alt="New (Filter)" class="wp-image-12050" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-0a-1024x587.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-0a-768x440.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-0a-1536x880.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-0a.webp 1882w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-view-the-filtered-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View the Filtered List</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Once you’ve selected your filters, click the <strong>Apply</strong> button at the bottom of the filter menu.</li><li>The Ingredients List will refresh to display only the items matching your criteria.</li><li>To remove filters and view the full list again, click <strong>Reset</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="592" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-1024x592.webp" alt="New (Filter Apply)" class="wp-image-12046" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-1024x592.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-768x444.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-1536x887.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d.webp 1866w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can easily filter and manage your ingredient list to focus on the items that matter most.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                46 => [
                    'id' => 47,
                    'doc_page_id' => 202,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to mark ingredients as waste, track their costs, and manage waste records in Menumium’s inventory system. Managing waste is critical for maintaining accurate stock records and understanding your restaurant’s overall food cost.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-ingredients-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Ingredients List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt; Inventory Setup</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Ingredients</strong> to open the <strong>Ingredient List</strong> page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="New (Ingredient List)" class="wp-image-12028" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-ingredient-list-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-convert-an-ingredient-to-waste" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Convert an Ingredient to Waste</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Ingredient List</strong> page, find the item you want to mark as waste.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column for that ingredient, click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Convert to Waste</strong> from the dropdown.</li><li>A <strong>Convert to Waste</strong> pop-up window will appear:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the <strong>quantity</strong> of the ingredient to waste.</li><li>Click the <strong>Convert to Waste</strong> button.</li></ul></li><li>A confirmation message will appear at the bottom of the screen confirming the waste action.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/convert-an-ingredient-to-waste-1.webp" alt="Convert an Ingredient to Waste" class="wp-image-9808" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/convert-an-ingredient-to-waste-1.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/convert-an-ingredient-to-waste-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/convert-an-ingredient-to-waste-1-768x437.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-view-the-waste-list" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: View the Waste List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the left-hand menu, go to <strong>Inventory Setup</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Waste</strong>.</li><li>The <strong>Waste Ingredients List</strong> page will display all items marked as waste, showing:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Ingredient name</li><li>Quantity wasted</li><li>Date</li><li>Associated cost</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18-1024x584.webp" alt="Waste Ingredients List" class="wp-image-9144" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-manage-waste-ingredients" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Manage Waste Ingredients</h2><p>From the <strong>Waste Ingredients List</strong>, you can take the following actions</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>View Details</strong> – Open a detailed view to see related information such as purchase records and initial stock by clicking the view icon.</li><li><strong>Move Back to Inventory</strong> – If an ingredient was marked as waste by mistake, click <strong>Back to Inventory (</strong>three-dot menu<strong>)</strong> to restore it to active stock.</li><li><strong>Delete a Waste Record</strong> – Permanently remove a waste record by selecting <strong>Delete</strong> from the three-dot menu. Confirm the deletion in the pop-up window.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="587" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-waste-three-dot-0a-1024x587.webp" alt="New Waste Three Dot" class="wp-image-12042" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-waste-three-dot-0a-1024x587.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-waste-three-dot-0a-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-waste-three-dot-0a-768x440.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-waste-three-dot-0a-1536x880.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-waste-three-dot-0a.webp 1882w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can track ingredient waste, monitor its cost impact, and keep your inventory accurate in Menumium.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                47 => [
                    'id' => 48,
                    'doc_page_id' => 203,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through creating a <strong>Purchase Inventory Report</strong>, which allows you to log ingredient purchases, track costs, and update your inventory levels in Menumium.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-inventory-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Inventory Management</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management &gt; Purchase Inventory</strong></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-inventory-management-0e-1024x582.webp" alt="Access Inventory Management" class="wp-image-12061" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-inventory-management-0e-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-inventory-management-0e-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-inventory-management-0e-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-inventory-management-0e-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/access-inventory-management-0e.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-go-to-purchase-inventory" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Go to Purchase Inventory</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the submenu, select <strong>Purchase Inventory</strong>.</li><li>Choose <strong>Purchase Ingredients</strong> to begin creating a new purchase report.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-purchase-ingredient-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="New Purchase Ingredient" class="wp-image-12056" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-purchase-ingredient-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-purchase-ingredient-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-purchase-ingredient-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-purchase-ingredient-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-purchase-ingredient-0a.webp 1899w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-add-ingredients" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Add Ingredients</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the <strong>search bar</strong> to find the ingredients you’ve purchased.</li><li>Click on each ingredient to add it to your purchase list.</li><li>The selected items will appear on the left side of your screen in the <strong>ingredient list</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21-1024x585.webp" alt="Add Ingredients" class="wp-image-9147" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-enter-update-purchase-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Enter &amp; Update Purchase Details</h2><p>For each ingredient added:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Purchase Unit</strong> </li><li><strong>Purchase Quantity</strong></li><li><strong>Unit Price</strong></li><li><strong>Discount</strong></li><li><strong>Tax/VAT</strong></li></ul><h2 id="step-5-review-the-total-cost" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Review the Total Cost</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the right-hand side, the <strong>Billings</strong> section will automatically calculate:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Subtotal</strong> – Total before adjustments.</li><li><strong>Total Cost</strong> – Final calculated purchase cost.</li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="step-6-log-supplier-and-purchaser" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Log Supplier and Purchaser</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Purchase Info</strong> section:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the <strong>Supplier</strong> from the dropdown list.</li><li>Select the <strong>Purchaser</strong> responsible for the transaction.</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-log-supplier-and-purchaser-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="New Log Supplier &amp; Purchaser" class="wp-image-12058" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-log-supplier-and-purchaser-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-log-supplier-and-purchaser-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-log-supplier-and-purchaser-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-log-supplier-and-purchaser-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-log-supplier-and-purchaser-0a.webp 1899w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-complete-the-report" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Complete the Report</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the <strong>Paid Amount</strong> for the purchase.</li><li>Optionally, add notes in the <strong>Comment</strong> field.</li><li>Click the green <strong>Purchase</strong> button to save the report and update your inventory.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-billing-and-comment-0a-1024x584.webp" alt="New Billing &amp; Comment" class="wp-image-12059" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-billing-and-comment-0a-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-billing-and-comment-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-billing-and-comment-0a-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-billing-and-comment-0a-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-billing-and-comment-0a.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Once saved, your purchased ingredients will be logged, inventory counts updated, and costs tracked in Menumium.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                48 => [
                    'id' => 49,
                    'doc_page_id' => 204,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The Inventory <strong>Purchase History</strong> feature allows you to review, filter, and manage all past ingredient purchases. You can quickly view details, download invoices, or edit records for better inventory tracking.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-inventory-purchase-history-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Inventory Purchase History Page</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Purchase Inventory</strong>.</li><li>From the submenu, click on <strong>Purchase History</strong>.</li></ol><p>This will open the <strong>Purchase History dashboard</strong>, which displays a table of all recorded purchases.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22-1024x583.webp" alt="Purchase History dashboard" class="wp-image-9148" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-view-purchase-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: View Purchase Details</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the purchase list, locate the transaction you want to check.</li><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column, click the <strong>View Details</strong> (eye icon).</li><li>A pop-up window will appear showing a detailed summary, including:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Purchase ID</strong></li><li><strong>Date and Time</strong></li><li><strong>Supplier Information</strong></li><li><strong>Total Ingredients &amp; Amount</strong></li><li><strong>List of Purchased Ingredients</strong> (with quantity, unit price, tax, and total).</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="591" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-view-purchase-details-0a-1024x591.webp" alt="New View Purchase Details" class="wp-image-12066" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-view-purchase-details-0a-1024x591.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-view-purchase-details-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-view-purchase-details-0a-768x443.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-view-purchase-details-0a-1536x886.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-view-purchase-details-0a.webp 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>From the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> in the same row, you can also:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Download Invoice</strong> for the purchase.</li><li><strong>Edit Purchase</strong> if corrections are required.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-purchase-0u-1024x583.webp" alt="Edit Purchase" class="wp-image-12065" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-purchase-0u-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-purchase-0u-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-purchase-0u-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-purchase-0u-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-purchase-0u.webp 1882w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-search-for-a-specific-purchase" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Search for a Specific Purchase</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Above the table, locate the <strong>Search bar</strong>.</li><li>Enter keywords such as <strong>Purchase ID, Item Name, or related key</strong>.</li><li>The table will update instantly to display only matching records.</li></ol><h2 id="step-4-filter-purchase-history" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Filter Purchase History</h2><p>To refine your view, use the <strong>Filter</strong> options.</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Click the <strong>Filter</strong> button at the top-right of the table.</li><li>A filter panel will slide out with the following options:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Purchase Date</strong> – Select a date or date range.</li><li><strong>Employee</strong> – Filter by the staff member who recorded the purchase.</li><li><strong>Sort By</strong> – Arrange results by:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Date</li><li>Purchase Amount (Low → High or High → Low).</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>After selecting your criteria, click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li><li>To reset and view the full list again, click <strong>Reset</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="592" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-1024x592.webp" alt="New (Filter Apply)" class="wp-image-12046" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-1024x592.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-768x444.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d-1536x887.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-filter-apply-0d.webp 1866w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>By following these steps, you can easily monitor your purchase history, track supplier costs, and maintain accurate inventory records.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                49 => [
                    'id' => 50,
                    'doc_page_id' => 205,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through setting up and configuring the <strong>Inventory Model</strong> for a specific branch. Enabling the inventory model ensures accurate tracking of ingredients and stock usage.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-branch-setup-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the Branch Setup Menu</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Restaurant Management &gt; Restaurant Setup</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Branch Setup</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="552" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23-1024x552.webp" alt="Branch Setup Menu" class="wp-image-9149" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23-1024x552.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23-300x162.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23-768x414.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23-1536x828.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.webp 1909w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-the-branch-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Branch to Edit</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Branch List</strong> page, locate the branch you want to configure.</li><li>Click on the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> (â®) next to that branch.</li><li>From the dropdown, choose <strong>Edit Details</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-branch-edit-details-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="New Branch Edit Details" class="wp-image-12069" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-branch-edit-details-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-branch-edit-details-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-branch-edit-details-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-branch-edit-details-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-branch-edit-details-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-navigate-to-the-inventory-tab" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Navigate to the Inventory Tab</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the branch’s settings page, you’ll see multiple tabs.</li><li>Click on the <strong>Inventory</strong> tab to open the inventory settings.</li></ol><h2 id="step-4-activate-inventory-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Activate Inventory Management</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Find the <strong>Inventory Management Model</strong> toggle switch.</li><li>Click the toggle to turn it <strong>ON</strong>.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>The switch will turn <strong>green</strong> when activated.</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-toggle-on-0a-1024x582.webp" alt="Inventory Toggle On" class="wp-image-12071" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-toggle-on-0a-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-toggle-on-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-toggle-on-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-toggle-on-0a-1536x873.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/inventory-toggle-on-0a.webp 1897w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-select-the-inventory-usage-model" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Select the Inventory Usage Model</h2><p>Once inventory management is enabled, select how inventory will be deducted:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Deduct Inventory after Order Confirmation</strong> – Stock decreases immediately after an order is confirmed.</li><li><strong>Deduct Inventory when Preparing Recipe/Raw Food</strong> – Stock decreases when ingredients are used to prepare food.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25-1024x582.webp" alt="Inventory Usage Model" class="wp-image-9151" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25-1024x582.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.webp 1891w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Choose the option that best fits your restaurant’s workflow by clicking the corresponding radio button.</p><h2 id="step-6-save-your-settings" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Save Your Settings</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After choosing your usage model, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the top-right of the page.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear:<br><strong>“Business settings updated successfully.”</strong></li></ol><p>Your <strong>Inventory Model</strong> is now active for the selected branch and ready to use.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                50 => [
                    'id' => 51,
                    'doc_page_id' => 206,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Creating a recipe allows you to track the ingredients used in each menu item. This ensures <strong>accurate stock deductions</strong> and provides better insights into <strong>costing and profit analysis</strong>.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Recipe Setup Page</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong> in the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Select <strong>Recipe Setup</strong>.</li><li>You will be taken to the <strong>Recipe List</strong> page, where all existing recipes are displayed.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20-1024x583.webp" alt="Recipe Setup Page" class="wp-image-9146" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.webp 1895w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-create-a-new-recipe" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Create a New Recipe</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the top-right of the Recipe List page, click the <strong>Create Recipe</strong> button.</li><li>A <strong>Create Recipe</strong> modal window will appear.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1-1024x583.webp" alt="Create a New Recipe" class="wp-image-9183" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2-1.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-in-recipe-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill in Recipe Details</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Recipe Name:</strong> Enter the name of the recipe (e.g., <em>Choco Lava Shake</em>).</li><li><strong>Status:</strong> Toggle this switch <strong>ON</strong> to make the recipe active.</li><li><strong>Recipe Thumbnail:</strong> Upload an image of the recipe (optional but recommended). Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, WEBP.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="590" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-recipe-0a-1024x590.webp" alt="New Create Recipe" class="wp-image-12074" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-recipe-0a-1024x590.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-recipe-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-recipe-0a-768x443.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-recipe-0a-1536x885.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-create-recipe-0a.webp 1870w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-add-ingredients" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Add Ingredients</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Ingredients Info</strong> section, click the <strong>Select Ingredients</strong> dropdown.</li><li>Add each ingredient required for the recipe.</li><li>For every ingredient added, specify the <strong>Unit</strong> (e.g., liter, gram, piece).</li><li>(Optional) Mark certain items as <strong>Critical Ingredients</strong>.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Critical ingredients are essential to the dish and should be closely monitored to prevent stock-outs.</li></ul></li><li>Continue until all recipe ingredients have been listed.</li></ol><h2 id="step-5-save-the-recipe" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save the Recipe</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After entering all details and ingredients, click the <strong>Create</strong> button at the bottom of the modal.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear:<br><strong>“Recipe added successfully.”</strong></li><li>Your new recipe will now be listed on the <strong>Recipe List</strong> page.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="591" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-2-1024x591.webp" alt="Save the Recipe" class="wp-image-9184" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-2-1024x591.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-2-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-2-768x443.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-2-1536x887.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3-2.webp 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>You have successfully created a recipe in Menumium. It will now automatically track ingredient usage when linked to menu items.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                51 => [
                    'id' => 52,
                    'doc_page_id' => 207,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of <strong>assigning a recipe to a specific food item</strong> in Menumium’s inventory and recipe management system.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><p>Before assigning a recipe, make sure that:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A <strong>Food Item</strong> has already been created in the system.</li><li>A <strong>Recipe</strong> has already been created and saved.</li></ul><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-page" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Recipe Setup Page</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong> section in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Recipe Setup</strong> from the dropdown menu.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Recipe List</strong> page, where all your recipes are displayed.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="New Navigate To The Recipe Setup" class="wp-image-12076" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-navigate-to-the-recipe-setup-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-select-a-recipe-to-assign" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select a Recipe to Assign</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the recipe you want to assign (e.g., <em>Choco Lava Shake</em>).</li><li>On the right side of the recipe row, click the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Assign Recipe to Food</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-2-1024x586.webp" alt="Assign Recipe to Food" class="wp-image-9186" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-2-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-2-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-2-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-2-1536x878.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4-2.webp 1885w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-select-the-food-item" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Select the Food Item</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>A new window titled <strong>Assign Recipe to Food</strong> will appear.</li><li>In the <strong>Select Food</strong> search bar, type the food name, ID, or keyword to find the food item.</li><li>Click on the correct food item from the search results.</li><li>Once selected, the food item will display along with its ingredient details below.</li></ol><h2 id="step-4-confirm-and-save" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Confirm and Save</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Review the selected food item and recipe ingredients to ensure they are accurate.</li><li>Click the green <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom of the window.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear:<br><strong>“Food recipe added successfully.”</strong></li></ol><p>You have now successfully linked a recipe to a food item. Menumium will automatically track ingredient usage whenever this food item is ordered.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                52 => [
                    'id' => 53,
                    'doc_page_id' => 208,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will walk you through the process of editing an existing recipe in Menumium. Editing a recipe allows you to update its details, change its ingredients, or modify its status.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-inventory-recipe-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong> to expand the menu.</li><li>In the expanded sub-menu, select <strong>Recipe Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will open the <strong>Recipe List</strong> page, which displays all your existing recipes.</li></ol><h2 id="step-2-select-the-recipe-to-edit" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select the Recipe to Edit</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the recipe you wish to update by scrolling through the list or using the <strong>Search Bar</strong>.</li><li>On the right side of the recipe’s row, click the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown, select <strong>Edit Recipe</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-2-1024x584.webp" alt="Recipe to Edit" class="wp-image-9189" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-2-1024x584.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-2-768x438.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-2-1536x876.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5-2.webp 1890w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-update-recipe-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Update Recipe Details</h2><p>In the <strong>Update Recipe</strong> form, you can edit the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Recipe Name</strong> – Change the name of the recipe.</li><li><strong>Status</strong> – Toggle the switch to activate or deactivate the recipe.</li><li><strong>Recipe Thumbnail</strong> – Update the recipe’s image by clicking on the current thumbnail and uploading a new one.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="589" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-and-update-recipe-0a-1024x589.webp" alt="Edit &amp; Update Recipe" class="wp-image-12080" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-and-update-recipe-0a-1024x589.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-and-update-recipe-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-and-update-recipe-0a-768x442.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-and-update-recipe-0a-1536x884.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-and-update-recipe-0a.webp 1873w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-modify-ingredients" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Modify Ingredients</h2><p>Scroll to the <strong>Ingredients Info</strong> section to adjust the recipe composition:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Add Ingredients</strong> – Use the dropdown to add new items.</li><li><strong>Update Units</strong> – Adjust the measurement unit (e.g., grams, liters) for each ingredient.</li><li><strong>Mark as Critical</strong> – Check the box to mark essential ingredients that require close stock monitoring.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="591" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-ingredients-0a-1024x591.webp" alt="Modify Ingredients" class="wp-image-12081" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-ingredients-0a-1024x591.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-ingredients-0a-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-ingredients-0a-768x443.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-ingredients-0a-1536x886.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/modify-ingredients-0a.webp 1869w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-save-your-changes" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Save Your Changes</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once you’ve made all necessary edits, click the green <strong>Update</strong> button at the bottom of the form.</li><li>A success message will appear:<br><strong>“Recipe updated successfully.”</strong></li></ol><p>Your recipe has now been updated. The changes will be applied immediately across your system for accurate stock tracking and order management.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                53 => [
                    'id' => 54,
                    'doc_page_id' => 209,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Recipe List</strong> on your Menumium dashboard can be filtered using multiple criteria, allowing you to quickly find and manage specific recipes.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-recipe-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Recipe Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand side menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Recipe Setup</strong> to open the <strong>Recipe List</strong> page.</li></ol><h2 id="step-2-open-the-filter-menu" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the Filter Menu</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Recipe List</strong> page, locate the <strong>Filter</strong> button at the top-right corner.</li><li>Click it to open the <strong>Filter Sidebar</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-2-1024x585.webp" alt="Open the Filter Menu" class="wp-image-9192" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-2-1024x585.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-2-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-2-1536x877.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6-2.webp 1888w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-apply-filter-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply Filter Options</h2><p>You can filter recipes by the following criteria:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status Type</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All</strong> – Displays all recipes regardless of status.</li><li><strong>Active</strong> – Shows only active recipes.</li><li><strong>Inactive</strong> – Shows only inactive recipes.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Ingredients Name</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the dropdown list to find recipes that contain specific ingredients.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Food Name</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select a food name from the dropdown to locate its associated recipe.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Creation Date Range</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Set a start and end date to filter recipes created within that period.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Modification Date Range</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Set a start and end date to filter recipes modified within that period.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Sort By</strong><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Default (Newest to Oldest)</strong> – Shows the latest recipes first.</li><li><strong>Oldest to Newest</strong> – Displays the earliest recipes first.</li><li><strong>Last Updated</strong> – Lists recipes most recently updated first.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="590" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-2-1024x590.webp" alt="Sort By" class="wp-image-9194" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-2-1024x590.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-2-300x173.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-2-768x442.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-2-1536x885.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7-2.webp 1873w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-view-filtered-results" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View Filtered Results</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After selecting your filters, click the green <strong>Apply</strong> button at the bottom of the sidebar.</li><li>The Recipe List will update instantly to show only the results that match your criteria.</li></ol><p>ð¡ To reset your view, simply clear the filters or click the <strong>Reset</strong> button.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                54 => [
                    'id' => 55,
                    'doc_page_id' => 210,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Process Food</strong> feature allows you to manage food items that are cooked or prepared in your kitchen. When enabled, the inventory is automatically reduced <strong>recipe-wise</strong> as foods are processed and prepared. This ensures accurate stock tracking and helps monitor expiration dates.</p><h2 id="prerequisites" class="wp-block-heading">Prerequisites</h2><p>Before setting up <strong>Process Food</strong>, make sure you have:</p><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Set the <strong>Inventory Model</strong> to ‘<em>Deduct Inventory when prepare recipe-wise food</em>.’</li><li>Completed your <strong>Food Setup</strong>.</li><li>Completed your <strong>Recipe Setup</strong>.</li></ol><h2 id="step-by-step-guide" class="wp-block-heading">Step-by-Step Guide</h2><h3 id="step-1-navigate-to-process-food" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Process Food</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dashboard, go to the <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong> tab in the left-hand sidebar.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1-1024x583.webp" alt="Navigate to Process Food" class="wp-image-9196" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8-1.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Process Food, </strong>then<strong> + Prepare Food</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/go-to-purchase-inventory-0a-1024x578.webp" alt="Go To Purchase Inventory" class="wp-image-12055" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/go-to-purchase-inventory-0a-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/go-to-purchase-inventory-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/go-to-purchase-inventory-0a-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/go-to-purchase-inventory-0a-1536x867.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/go-to-purchase-inventory-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-2-choose-food-items" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Choose Food Items</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the <strong>Search Bar</strong> to find specific food items.</li><li>Click on items to add them to the <strong>processing cart</strong>.</li><li>You can select <strong>multiple food items</strong> at once.</li><li>If the item has variations (e.g., <em>Small, Medium, Large</em>), specify the <strong>quantity</strong> for each variation.</li></ol><h3 id="step-3-fill-out-the-process-food-info" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill Out the Process Food Info</h3><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Process Date</strong> – Select the date when the food processing takes place.</li><li><strong>Expired Date</strong> – Choose the date when the processed food will expire.</li><li><strong>Process By</strong> – The system auto-detects the user performing the process.</li><li><strong>Transfer to Waste List After Expire</strong> – Check this option if the food should automatically move to the <strong>Waste List</strong> after expiration.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="578" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/process-food-info-0a-1024x578.webp" alt="Process Food Info" class="wp-image-12085" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/process-food-info-0a-1024x578.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/process-food-info-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/process-food-info-0a-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/process-food-info-0a-1536x867.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/process-food-info-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h3 id="step-4-confirm-and-process" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Confirm and Process</h3><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Review the <strong>Process Food Summary</strong> to verify all quantities.</li><li>Add any notes in the <strong>Comment Box</strong> if needed.</li><li>Click the <strong>Process Food</strong> button to finalize.</li><li>A success message will appear confirming the process.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="585" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-and-process-2.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10136" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-and-process-2.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-and-process-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirm-and-process-2-768x439.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="where-to-find-the-process-food-list" class="wp-block-heading">Where to Find the Process Food List</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the sidebar, go to <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>Process Food</strong> &gt; <strong>Processed Food List</strong></li><li>The <strong>Processed Food List Page</strong> will appear, showing all processed food entries with details such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Process ID</li><li>Person who processed</li><li>Total Quantity</li><li>Current Stock</li><li>Expired Stock</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="584" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/find-the-process-food-list-2.webp" alt="Find The Process Food List" class="wp-image-10140" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/find-the-process-food-list-2.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/find-the-process-food-list-2-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/find-the-process-food-list-2-768x438.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="how-to-use-the-action-menu-in-processed-food-list" class="wp-block-heading">How to Use the Action Menu in Processed Food List</h2><p>For each processed entry, you’ll find an <strong>Action Menu</strong> (three dots) on the right side. Options include:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Quick Details (Eye Icon):</strong> Opens a pop-up with a summary of items, quantities, and user details.</li><li><strong>View Details:</strong> Opens full information about the processed food, including comments.</li><li><strong>Edit Processed:</strong> Lets you add, remove, or modify processed items and their quantities.</li><li><strong>Convert to Waste:</strong> Moves expired or unusable processed food items into the <strong>Waste List</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="582" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/action-menu-in-processed-food-list.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10148" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/action-menu-in-processed-food-list.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/action-menu-in-processed-food-list-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/action-menu-in-processed-food-list-768x437.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>With these steps, you can set up, track, and manage your processed food inventory efficiently.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                55 => [
                    'id' => 56,
                    'doc_page_id' => 211,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Menumium provides a detailed <strong>In/Out Log</strong> to help you track every movement of your ingredients — including stock additions, deductions, purchases, and waste. This ensures transparency and accuracy in your inventory records.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-inventory-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Inventory Section</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand navigation menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>Inventory &amp; Recipe Management</strong> to expand the sub-menu.</li></ol><h2 id="step-2-access-inventory-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access Inventory Setup</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the expanded menu, select <strong>Inventory Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will open a page with all inventory-related options.</li></ol><h2 id="step-3-open-the-in-out-log" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Open the In/Out Log</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Inventory Setup</strong> page, locate and click on <strong>Ingredients In/Out Log</strong>.</li><li>This will open the <strong>In/Out Log History</strong> table.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-in-out-log-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="New In-Out Log" class="wp-image-12089" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-in-out-log-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-in-out-log-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-in-out-log-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-in-out-log-0a-1536x875.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-in-out-log-0a.webp 1893w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-view-the-log-history" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View the Log History</h2><p>The <strong>In/Out Log History</strong> table shows a detailed record of ingredient movements. Each entry includes:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: The name of the ingredient.</li><li><strong>Date</strong>: The date and time of the stock movement.</li><li><strong>In/Out Stock</strong>: The quantity added (+) or deducted (–).</li><li><strong>Stock Info</strong>: Context of the update, such as initial stock, updated stock, or balance.</li><li><strong>Update Type</strong>: The reason for the update (e.g., <em>Process Food, Initial, Purchase, Waste</em>).</li><li><strong>Action</strong>: A button to view detailed information about the log entry.</li></ul><h2 id="step-5-view-detailed-log-entry" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: View Detailed Log Entry</h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="583" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-icon-0a-1024x583.webp" alt="New Action Icon" class="wp-image-12090" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-icon-0a-1024x583.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-icon-0a-300x171.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-icon-0a-768x437.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-icon-0a-1536x874.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/new-action-icon-0a.webp 1894w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>To see more details about a specific log, click the <strong>View</strong> icon in the <strong>Action</strong> column.</li><li>A pop-up will appear, showing:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Ingredient name</li><li>Update type (reason)</li><li>Quantity added or removed</li><li>Date and time of the transaction</li></ul></li><li>Click the <strong>X</strong> button at the top-right to close the pop-up.</li></ol><p>With these steps, you can easily monitor and review every change in your ingredient stock, helping you stay in full control of your restaurant’s inventory.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                56 => [
                    'id' => 57,
                    'doc_page_id' => 212,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to create a new order through the <strong>Point of Sale (POS) system</strong> in Menumium. The POS allows you to quickly process dine-in, takeaway, or delivery orders with accurate billing and customer tracking.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-the-pos-system" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access the POS System</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Click on <strong>POS Management</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>New Sale</strong> to open the POS ordering page.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-start-a-new-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Start a New Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Create New Order</strong> page.</li><li>This is where you will add items, set order details, and complete the billing process.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-add-items-to-the-cart" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Add Items to the Cart</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Browse menu items displayed on the left side of the screen.</li><li>Use the <strong>Search Bar</strong> to quickly find items or filter by category.</li><li>Click the <strong>green (+) icon</strong> next to an item to add it to the cart.</li><li>A pop-up will appear, allowing you to adjust the <strong>quantity</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-items-to-the-cart-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Add Items To The Cart" class="wp-image-10991" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-items-to-the-cart-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-items-to-the-cart-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-items-to-the-cart-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-items-to-the-cart-0a-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-items-to-the-cart-0a.webp 1902w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Add to Cart</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-add-to-cart-0a-1024x580.webp" alt="POS Add To Cart" class="wp-image-10992" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-add-to-cart-0a-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-add-to-cart-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-add-to-cart-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-add-to-cart-0a-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-add-to-cart-0a.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-specify-order-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Specify Order Details</h2><p>In the <strong>Order Information</strong> section (right side of the screen), choose the order type:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Dine In</strong> – For customers dining at the restaurant.</li><li><strong>Take Away</strong> – For pickup orders.</li><li><strong>Home Delivery</strong> – For delivery orders.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-POS-specify-order-details-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Specify Order Details" class="wp-image-9463" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-POS-specify-order-details-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-POS-specify-order-details-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-POS-specify-order-details-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-POS-specify-order-details-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/3.-POS-specify-order-details.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-add-customer-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Add Customer Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Customer</strong> section, either keep the default <strong>Walk-In Customer</strong> or select an existing one.</li><li>To add a new customer:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>+ Add New Customer</strong>.</li><li>Enter their <strong>Name, Phone Number, and Email</strong>.</li></ul></li><li>This step is especially useful for delivery and repeat customers.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-POS-customer-information-1024x579.webp" alt="POS Customer Information" class="wp-image-9464" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-POS-customer-information-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-POS-customer-information-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-POS-customer-information-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-POS-customer-information-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/4.-POS-customer-information.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-billing-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Billing Information</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Review the breakdown under <strong>Billing</strong>:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Subtotal, Food Discount, Extra Discount, Coupon Discount, and VAT/Tax</strong>.</li><li>The system will calculate the <strong>Total Bill</strong> automatically.</li></ul></li><li>Under <strong>Payment</strong>, choose:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Pay After Eating</strong> or <strong>Pay First</strong>.</li><li>If <strong>Pay First</strong>, select from available methods:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Cash</strong></li><li><strong>Card</strong></li><li><strong>Mobile Banking</strong></li><li><strong>Others</strong></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-POS-payment-options-1024x580.webp" alt="POS Payment Options" class="wp-image-9465" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-POS-payment-options-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-POS-payment-options-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-POS-payment-options-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-POS-payment-options-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/5.-POS-payment-options.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-7-place-the-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 7: Place the Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After confirming all details, click <strong>Place Order</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation pop-up will appear asking if you want to <strong>Print an Invoice</strong>.</li><li>Printing options include:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Full Invoice</strong></li><li><strong>Only Customer Invoice</strong></li><li><strong>Only Kitchen Invoice</strong></li></ul></li><li>Choose <strong>Print</strong> or <strong>Don’t Print</strong> to finalize.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-POS-invoice-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Invoice" class="wp-image-9466" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-POS-invoice-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-POS-invoice-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-POS-invoice-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-POS-invoice-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/6.-POS-invoice.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-8-view-the-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 8: View the Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A success message will appear once the order is created.</li><li>Click <strong>View Order</strong> to open full details, including order status and history.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-POS-view-order-1024x581.webp" alt="POS View Order" class="wp-image-9467" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-POS-view-order-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-POS-view-order-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-POS-view-order-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-POS-view-order-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/7.-POS-view-order.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Using the Menumium POS, you can easily create and manage orders with accurate billing, flexible payment options, and customer tracking—all from one streamlined interface.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                57 => [
                    'id' => 58,
                    'doc_page_id' => 213,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to track, update, and finalize ongoing orders within the <strong>Menumium POS (Point of Sale)</strong> system. Managing order statuses ensures smooth coordination between staff, kitchen, and customers.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-pos-dashboard" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the POS Dashboard</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Menumium Dashboard</strong>, go to the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Under <strong>POS Management</strong>, click on <strong>New Sale</strong>.</li><li>This opens the <strong>Create New Order</strong> screen.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-ongoing-orders" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access Ongoing Orders</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the POS screen, look at the <strong>top-right corner</strong>.</li><li>Click the <strong>Ongoing Orders</strong> button.</li><li>A pop-up window will appear, displaying a list of all currently active orders.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-POS-ongoing-orders-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Ongoing Orders" class="wp-image-9468" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-POS-ongoing-orders-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-POS-ongoing-orders-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-POS-ongoing-orders-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-POS-ongoing-orders-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/8.-POS-ongoing-orders.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-monitor-order-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Monitor Order Status</h2><p>Inside the <strong>Ongoing Orders</strong> window:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Use the <strong>Search Bar</strong> to find a specific order by <strong>Order ID</strong> or <strong>Customer Info</strong>.</li><li>Use the tabs below the search bar to filter orders:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>All Orders</strong> – Shows every ongoing order.</li><li><strong>Confirmed</strong> – Orders placed and awaiting preparation.</li><li><strong>Cooking</strong> – Orders currently being prepared.</li><li><strong>Ready to Serve/Handover</strong> – Orders completed by the kitchen, ready for service or pickup.</li><li><strong>Eating</strong> – Orders served and being consumed by customers.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-POS-track-ongoing-orders-1024x579.webp" alt="POS Track Ongoing Orders" class="wp-image-9469" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-POS-track-ongoing-orders-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-POS-track-ongoing-orders-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-POS-track-ongoing-orders-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-POS-track-ongoing-orders-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9.-POS-track-ongoing-orders.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-update-order-status" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Update Order Status</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the order you wish to update.</li><li>On the right-hand side, use the <strong>Status Dropdown</strong> to change its current stage.</li><li>Available status options include:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Confirmed</strong></li><li><strong>Cooking</strong></li><li><strong>Ready to Serve</strong></li><li><strong>Eating</strong></li><li><strong>Completed</strong></li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-POS-on-going-order-status-update-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Ongoing Order Status Update" class="wp-image-9470" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-POS-on-going-order-status-update-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-POS-on-going-order-status-update-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-POS-on-going-order-status-update-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-POS-on-going-order-status-update-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/10.-POS-on-going-order-status-update.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>Updating the status here automatically syncs with the <strong>kitchen</strong> and <strong>customer</strong> in real time.</p></div></div><h2 id="step-5-finalize-and-complete-an-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Finalize and Complete an Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>When an order is fully served and paid, set its status to <strong>Completed</strong>.</li><li>The order will move from <strong>Ongoing Orders</strong> to the <strong>Completed Records</strong>, closing the process.</li></ul><p>By regularly updating ongoing orders in the POS, you ensure clear communication between the kitchen, staff, and customers—leading to faster service, fewer errors, and smoother operations.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                58 => [
                    'id' => 59,
                    'doc_page_id' => 214,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>The <strong>Hold Order</strong> feature in Menumium POS allows you to temporarily save a customer’s order without completing payment. This is especially useful when the customer isn’t ready to pay immediately or needs to finalize their order later.</p><h2 id="step-1-create-and-hold-an-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Create and Hold an Order</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Menumium Dashboard</strong>, go to the <strong>POS Management</strong> section in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click <strong>New Sale</strong> to launch the POS interface.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Add items to the cart by clicking the green <strong>Add (+)</strong> icon next to each product.</li><li>Once all items are in the cart, click the <strong>Hold Order</strong> button at the <strong>bottom-right corner</strong> of the screen.</li><li>A success message will appear at the <strong>bottom-left</strong>, confirming that the cart has been updated and the order is now on hold.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-POS-hold-order-1024x580.webp" alt="POS Hold Order" class="wp-image-9471" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-POS-hold-order-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-POS-hold-order-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-POS-hold-order-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-POS-hold-order-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/11.-POS-hold-order.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-resume-a-held-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Resume a Held Order</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the POS screen, click the <strong>Hold Orders</strong> button at the <strong>top-right corner</strong>.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-POS-hold-order-list-button-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Hold Order List Button" class="wp-image-9472" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-POS-hold-order-list-button-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-POS-hold-order-list-button-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-POS-hold-order-list-button-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-POS-hold-order-list-button-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/12.-POS-hold-order-list-button.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>A <strong>Hold Orders</strong> pop-up will appear, displaying a list of all current held orders.</li><li>Use the <strong>Search Bar</strong> to find an order by its <strong>Order ID</strong> or <strong>Customer Information</strong>.</li><li>Next to each order, you will see two options:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Remove</strong> – Permanently deletes the held order.</li><li><strong>Resume</strong> – Loads the order items back into the cart so you can continue the transaction.</li></ul></li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-POS-hold-order-details-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Hold Order Details" class="wp-image-9473" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-POS-hold-order-details-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-POS-hold-order-details-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-POS-hold-order-details-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-POS-hold-order-details-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/13.-POS-hold-order-details.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The Hold Order feature ensures flexibility in managing sales, allowing staff to pause and resume transactions smoothly without losing any cart details.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                59 => [
                    'id' => 60,
                    'doc_page_id' => 215,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to create, edit, and organize food items within the Menumium <strong>Point of Sale (POS)</strong> system. You can manage menu items, update details, and maintain stock with just a few clicks.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-food-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access Food Management</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From your <strong>Menumium Dashboard</strong>, go to the <strong>POS Management</strong> section in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Click on <strong>New Sale</strong> to launch the POS interface.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>left side of the food list</strong>, click <strong>Manage Food</strong>.</li><li>You will be redirected to the <strong>Food List</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-POS-access-food-management-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Access Food Management" class="wp-image-9474" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-POS-access-food-management-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-POS-access-food-management-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-POS-access-food-management-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-POS-access-food-management-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/14.-POS-access-food-management.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-manage-food-items" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Manage Food Items</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Create Food:</strong> Click the <strong>Create Food</strong> button to add a new menu item. <em>(For details, check “<a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/food-management/how-to-filter-or-export-category-in-food-management-2/">How to Create a Food</a>” guide.)</em></li><li><strong>Quick View:</strong> Click the <strong>eye icon</strong> next to any food item to open a pop-up with details such as ingredients, price, and availability.</li><li><strong>Edit Details:</strong> Click the <strong>three-dot menu</strong> next to a food item and select <strong>Edit Details</strong> to modify information, price, or variations.</li><li><strong>Update Stock:</strong> Choose <strong>Update Stock</strong> to quickly adjust inventory for the selected item.</li><li><strong>Update Price:</strong> Select <strong>Update Price</strong> to directly change the cost of the food item.</li><li><strong>Move to Trash:</strong> To remove an item from the active menu, select <strong>Move to Trash</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-view-options-0a-1024x577.webp" alt="POS Food Management View Options" class="wp-image-11015" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-view-options-0a-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-view-options-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-view-options-0a-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-view-options-0a-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-view-options-0a.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-use-filter-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Use Filter Options</h2><p>Click the <strong>Filter</strong> button on the Food List page to refine your search:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status:</strong> Filter by <strong>All, Active, or Inactive</strong>.</li><li><strong>Category &amp; Sub-Category:</strong> Narrow results to specific menu categories.</li><li><strong>Creation Date &amp; Modified Date:</strong> Sort by when items were added or last updated.</li></ul><h2 id="step-4-import-export-food-data" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Import &amp; Export Food Data</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Export Data:</strong> Download a file containing your current food list.</li><li><strong>Import Data:</strong> Upload new food items in bulk for faster menu setup.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-import-export-and-filter-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="POS Food Management Import, Export And Filter" class="wp-image-11017" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-import-export-and-filter-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-import-export-and-filter-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-import-export-and-filter-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-import-export-and-filter-0a-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/pos-food-management-import-export-and-filter-0a.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>The POS Food Management system makes it easy to keep your menu updated, control stock, and streamline food operations in just a few steps.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                60 => [
                    'id' => 61,
                    'doc_page_id' => 216,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to create a customer reservation directly from the <strong>Point of Sale (POS)</strong> system in Menumium. Reservations made here can include customer details, table selection, and billing info.</p><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>T<em>o make a reservation from POS you must add atleast one food item to the cart. If you want to make a reservation without adding food to the cart beforehand, you can check the <a href="https://menumium.com/documentation/table-reservation/how-to-create-a-reservation/">How to Create a Reservation</a> from table &amp; reservation documentation. </em></p></div></div><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-pos" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to POS</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, click on <strong>POS Management</strong> in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Select <strong>New Sale</strong> to open the POS interface.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-reservation-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Reservation Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the POS interface, add food to the cart. Remember without adding food to the cart you won’t be able to make a reservation directly from the POS.</li><li>Click the <strong>Make Reservation</strong> button at the top of the screen.</li><li>A new window titled <strong>Make Reservation</strong> will open.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-POS-make-reservation-1024x580.webp" alt="POS Make Reservation" class="wp-image-9476" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-POS-make-reservation-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-POS-make-reservation-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-POS-make-reservation-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-POS-make-reservation-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/16.-POS-make-reservation.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-fill-in-reservation-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Fill in Reservation Information</h2><p>In the <strong>Make Reservation</strong> window, complete the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Reservation Date:</strong> Choose the reservation date from the calendar.</li><li><strong>Reservation Time:</strong> Select the reservation time.</li><li><strong>Number of Persons:</strong> Enter the total number of guests.</li><li><strong>Floor:</strong> Select the floor where the guests will be seated.</li><li><strong>Choose Table:</strong> Select <strong>Full Floor</strong> or choose a specific available table.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="586" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Fill-in-reservation-information-1024x586.webp" alt="Fill In Reservation Information" class="wp-image-9477" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Fill-in-reservation-information-1024x586.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Fill-in-reservation-information-300x172.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Fill-in-reservation-information-768x439.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Fill-in-reservation-information-1536x879.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/17.-Fill-in-reservation-information.webp 1886w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-add-customer-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Add Customer Information</h2><p>Under the <strong>Customer Info</strong> section:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Existing Customer:</strong> Search and select a registered customer.</li><li><strong>New Customer:</strong> Click <strong>+ Add New Customer</strong> to create a new profile (enter name, phone, and email).</li><li><strong>Walk-In Customer:</strong> Keep the default option if no profile is required.</li><li>Optionally, you can add <strong>Contact Person Info</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Reservation-customer-info-1024x580.webp" alt="Reservation - Customer Info" class="wp-image-9478" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Reservation-customer-info-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Reservation-customer-info-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Reservation-customer-info-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Reservation-customer-info-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/18.-Reservation-customer-info.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-handle-billing" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Handle Billing</h2><p>If applicable, under the <strong>Billings</strong> section:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Advance Booking Fee:</strong> Enter the fee amount.</li><li><strong>Payment Method:</strong> Select Cash.</li><li><strong>Paid Amount:</strong> Enter the amount received.</li><li>The <strong>Due Amount</strong> will be calculated automatically.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Reservation-billing-1024x579.webp" alt="Reservation - Billing" class="wp-image-9479" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Reservation-billing-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Reservation-billing-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Reservation-billing-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Reservation-billing-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/19.-Reservation-billing.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-finalize-reservation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Finalize Reservation</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Review all reservation details and add any notes in the <strong>Comments</strong> section.</li><li>Click the <strong>Create Reservation</strong> button at the bottom of the form.</li><li>A notification will appear: <strong>“Reservation Successfully Added.”</strong></li></ul></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                61 => [
                    'id' => 62,
                    'doc_page_id' => 217,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide will show you how to link an existing reservation to a new order directly from the Point of Sale (POS) screen in Menumium. Linking ensures the order is correctly tied to the customer’s reservation.</p><h2 id="step-1-access-pos" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Access POS</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left navigation menu, select <strong>POS Management</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>New Sale</strong> to open the order creation screen.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-add-items-to-the-cart" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Add Items to the Cart</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Browse the menu and add the desired food items to the cart.</li></ol><h2 id="step-3-expand-customer-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Expand Customer Information</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the right-hand side of the screen, go to the <strong>Order Information</strong> section.</li><li>Click <strong>Advanced Field</strong> under <strong>Customer Information</strong> to expand more options.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Link-reservation-advanced-field-1024x579.webp" alt="Link Reservation - Advanced Field" class="wp-image-9480" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Link-reservation-advanced-field-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Link-reservation-advanced-field-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Link-reservation-advanced-field-768x434.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Link-reservation-advanced-field-1536x868.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20.-Link-reservation-advanced-field.webp 1909w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-Link-Reservation-button-1024x580.webp" alt="Link Reservation Button" class="wp-image-9481" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-Link-Reservation-button-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-Link-Reservation-button-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-Link-Reservation-button-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-Link-Reservation-button-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/21.-Link-Reservation-button.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-link-a-reservation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Link a Reservation</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the <strong>Link Reservation</strong> option. A search box will appear.</li><li>Enter the <strong>Reservation ID, Customer Name, or Phone Number</strong> to find the relevant reservation.</li><li>Choose the correct reservation from the search results.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-Link-reservation-search-result-1024x580.webp" alt="Link Reservation Search Result" class="wp-image-9482" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-Link-reservation-search-result-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-Link-reservation-search-result-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-Link-reservation-search-result-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-Link-reservation-search-result-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/22.-Link-reservation-search-result.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>A reservation must already exist in the system. You can create one either from <strong>Table &amp; Reservation Management</strong> or directly from the <strong>POS</strong>.</p></div></div><h2 id="step-5-verify-and-confirm" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Verify and Confirm</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Review the reservation details (Customer Name, Number of People, Assigned Table).</li><li>Click <strong>Link Reservation</strong> to connect the reservation with the order.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.-Link-reservation-review-1024x580.webp" alt="Link Reservation Review" class="wp-image-9484" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.-Link-reservation-review-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.-Link-reservation-review-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.-Link-reservation-review-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.-Link-reservation-review-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/23.-Link-reservation-review.webp 1904w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-finalize-the-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Finalize the Order</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>Once all other order details are complete, click <strong>Place Order</strong>.</li><li>Choose your preferred printing option:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Full Invoice</strong></li><li><strong>Kitchen Invoice</strong></li><li><strong>Don’t Print</strong></li></ul></li><li>Confirm to finalize the order.</li></ol><p>The reservation is now successfully linked to the POS order, ensuring smooth operations and accurate records.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                62 => [
                    'id' => 63,
                    'doc_page_id' => 218,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide explains how to apply manual discounts, coupons, and promotional offers when creating an order in the Menumium Point of Sale (POS) system.</p><h2 id="step-1-add-items-to-the-cart" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Add Items to the Cart</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the left navigation, select <strong>POS Management</strong>.</li><li>Click on <strong>New Sale</strong> to open the order creation screen.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp" alt="Start A New Order" class="wp-image-10990" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/start-a-new-order-0a.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Select the food items from the menu by clicking the <strong>( + ) icon</strong> next to each item.</li><li>All selected items will appear in the <strong>Cart List</strong> on the right side of the screen.</li></ul><h2 id="step-2-apply-a-coupon" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Apply a Coupon</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Billings</strong> section, click on <strong>Coupon Discount</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/24.-POS-billing-section-coupon-discount-1024x579.webp" alt="POS Billing Section Coupon Discount" class="wp-image-9485" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/24.-POS-billing-section-coupon-discount-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/24.-POS-billing-section-coupon-discount-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/24.-POS-billing-section-coupon-discount-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/24.-POS-billing-section-coupon-discount-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/24.-POS-billing-section-coupon-discount.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up titled <strong>Available Coupon</strong> will appear.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter a coupon code manually in the field, OR</li><li>Select from the available coupons listed.</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.-POS-billing-section-coupon-apply-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Billing Section Coupon Apply" class="wp-image-9486" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.-POS-billing-section-coupon-apply-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.-POS-billing-section-coupon-apply-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.-POS-billing-section-coupon-apply-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.-POS-billing-section-coupon-apply-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/25.-POS-billing-section-coupon-apply.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>. The coupon discount will be added to the order total.</li></ul><h2 id="step-3-apply-an-extra-discount" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply an Extra Discount</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Cart List</strong>, scroll to the <strong>Billings</strong> section.</li><li>Click on <strong>Extra Discount</strong>. A pop-up window will appear.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/26.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-1024x580.webp" alt="POS Billing Section Extra Discount" class="wp-image-9487" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/26.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/26.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/26.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/26.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/26.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Enter the discount amount, choosing either a <strong>fixed amount ($)</strong> or a <strong>percentage (%)</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>. The discount will be reflected in the total bill.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/27.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-apply-1024x581.webp" alt="POS Billing Section Extra Discount Apply" class="wp-image-9488" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/27.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-apply-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/27.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-apply-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/27.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-apply-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/27.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-apply-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/27.-POS-billing-section-extra-discount-apply.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-use-automatic-promotions-bogo-happy-hour" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Use Automatic Promotions (BOGO &amp; Happy Hour)</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>BOGO (Buy One Get One)</strong> and <strong>Happy Hour</strong> offers are automatically applied if the customer’s order meets the conditions.</li><li>To view all available offers, click on the <strong>Promotions</strong> button at the top right (next to the “Full Screen” button).</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/28.-POS-view-all-available-offers-1024x580.webp" alt="POS View All Available Offers" class="wp-image-9489" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/28.-POS-view-all-available-offers-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/28.-POS-view-all-available-offers-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/28.-POS-view-all-available-offers-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/28.-POS-view-all-available-offers-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/28.-POS-view-all-available-offers.webp 1906w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Here you can see details of active <strong>Coupons</strong>, <strong>Happy Hour</strong>, and <strong>BOGO</strong> offers.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="580" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/29.-POS-available-active-promotional-offers-1024x580.webp" alt="POS - Available Active Promotional Offers" class="wp-image-9490" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/29.-POS-available-active-promotional-offers-1024x580.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/29.-POS-available-active-promotional-offers-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/29.-POS-available-active-promotional-offers-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/29.-POS-available-active-promotional-offers-1536x870.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/29.-POS-available-active-promotional-offers.webp 1905w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-finalize-the-order" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Finalize the Order</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>After applying discounts and coupons, click on <strong>Place Order</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation pop-up will appear: <em>“Do you want to Print Invoice?”</em></li><li>Choose your printing preference:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Full Invoice</li><li>Only Customer</li><li>Only Kitchen Invoice</li><li>Don’t Print</li></ul></li><li>Confirm your choice, and the order will be successfully placed with the final bill.</li></ol><p>Discounts, coupons, and promotions are now applied, ensuring a smooth checkout experience.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                63 => [
                    'id' => 64,
                    'doc_page_id' => 219,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide outlines the steps to create a new Point of Sale (POS) counter within Menumium. POS counters help you manage sales and orders efficiently by creating dedicated stations for transactions.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-counters-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Counters Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the main dashboard, click on the <strong>POS Management</strong> icon in the left-hand menu.</li><li>Select the <strong>Counters</strong> tab.</li><li>You will be directed to the <strong>Counter List</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="Counter Navigation" class="wp-image-11032" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-open-the-new-counter-creation-form" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Open the New Counter Creation Form</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Counter List</strong> page, you will see a default counter already set up by Menumium.</li><li>To add a new counter, click the <strong>Create New Counter</strong> button located at the top-right corner.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/30.-Counter-list-1024x576.webp" alt="Counter List" class="wp-image-9491" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/30.-Counter-list-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/30.-Counter-list-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/30.-Counter-list-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/30.-Counter-list-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/30.-Counter-list.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-enter-counter-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Enter Counter Details</h2><p>In the <strong>Create New Counter</strong> pop-up window, fill in the following fields:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Counter No.</strong>: Enter a unique number or name for the counter (<strong>mandatory</strong>).</li><li><strong>Floor</strong>: Select the floor where the counter is located from the dropdown menu.<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>If floors are not yet set up, click on <strong>See Floor Setup</strong> to create them.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Instruction (Optional):</strong> Add any notes, such as <em>“For takeout orders only”</em> or <em>“Beverage counter.”</em></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/31.-enter-counter-detaails-1024x576.webp" alt="Enter Counter Details" class="wp-image-9492" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/31.-enter-counter-detaails-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/31.-enter-counter-detaails-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/31.-enter-counter-detaails-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/31.-enter-counter-detaails-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/31.-enter-counter-detaails.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-finalize-counter-creation" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Finalize Counter Creation</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After completing the details, click the green <strong>Create</strong> button.</li><li>A confirmation notification will appear at the bottom-left of the screen:<br><em>“Counter added successfully.”</em></li><li>The new counter will now be listed in the <strong>Counter List</strong>.</li></ul><p>Your POS counter is now created and ready to use for transactions.</p></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:17.000000Z',
                ],
                64 => [
                    'id' => 65,
                    'doc_page_id' => 220,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This documentation will guide you through the process of filtering and viewing counter details within the Menumium POS system. This feature allows you to quickly locate specific counters and review their status and order history.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-the-counters-section" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to the Counters Section</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Log in to your Menumium dashboard.</li><li>From the left-hand menu, click on <strong>POS Management</strong>.</li><li>From the submenu, select <strong>Counters</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="579" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp" alt="Counter Navigation" class="wp-image-11032" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-1024x579.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a-1536x869.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-navigation-0a.webp 1907w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-access-the-filter-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Access the Filter Options</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Counter List</strong> page, you will see a list of all counters.</li><li>To refine this list, click the <strong>Filter</strong> button in the top-right corner of the table.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-filter-button-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Counter Filter Button" class="wp-image-11035" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-filter-button-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-filter-button-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-filter-button-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-filter-button-0a-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/counter-filter-button-0a.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-apply-filters-and-sort-options" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Apply Filters and Sort Options</h2><p>A filter panel will appear with the following options:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Status</strong>: Filter counters by <strong>All</strong>, <strong>Active</strong>, or <strong>Inactive</strong>.</li><li><strong>Floor</strong>: Select a floor if you have multiple floors configured.</li><li><strong>Sort By</strong>: Choose from <strong>Default (Newest to Oldest)</strong>, <strong>Oldest to Newest</strong>, or <strong>Last Updated</strong>.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/32.-counter-filter-1024x576.webp" alt="Counter Filter" class="wp-image-9493" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/32.-counter-filter-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/32.-counter-filter-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/32.-counter-filter-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/32.-counter-filter-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/32.-counter-filter.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>After selecting your filters, click <strong>Apply</strong> to update the list.</p><h2 id="step-4-view-counter-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: View Counter Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Locate the counter you want to view in the list.</li><li>Click the <strong>three-dot icon (â®)</strong> under the Action column and select <strong>View Details</strong>. Alternatively, click the <strong>eye button</strong> for a quick view.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/33.-view-counter-detials-1024x576.webp" alt="View Counter Details" class="wp-image-9494" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/33.-view-counter-detials-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/33.-view-counter-detials-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/33.-view-counter-detials-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/33.-view-counter-detials-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/33.-view-counter-detials.webp 1917w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A pop-up will display details such as:<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Counter ID</li><li>Assigned Floor</li><li>Instructions (if any)</li><li>Total number of orders linked to the counter</li><li>Status toggle (Active/Inactive)</li></ul></li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/34.-counter-view-pop-up-1024x576.webp" alt="Counter View Pop Up" class="wp-image-9495" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/34.-counter-view-pop-up-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/34.-counter-view-pop-up-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/34.-counter-view-pop-up-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/34.-counter-view-pop-up-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/34.-counter-view-pop-up.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-edit-counter-details" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Edit Counter Details</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong>, select <strong>Edit</strong>.</li><li>A pop-up window will allow you to update the <strong>counter name, floor, or instructions</strong>.</li><li>Click <strong>Update</strong> to save the changes.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/35.-edit-counter-button-1024x581.webp" alt="Edit Counter Button" class="wp-image-9496" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/35.-edit-counter-button-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/35.-edit-counter-button-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/35.-edit-counter-button-768x436.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/35.-edit-counter-button-1536x872.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/35.-edit-counter-button.webp 1901w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-counter-details-view-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Edit Counter Details View" class="wp-image-11036" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-counter-details-view-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-counter-details-view-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-counter-details-view-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-counter-details-view-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/edit-counter-details-view-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-delete-a-counter" class="wp-block-heading">Step 6: Delete a Counter</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>three-dot menu (â®)</strong>, select <strong>Delete</strong>.</li><li>A confirmation prompt will appear.</li><li>Click <strong>Delete</strong> to confirm.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/36.-delete-counter-button-1024x577.webp" alt="Delete Counter Button" class="wp-image-9497" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/36.-delete-counter-button-1024x577.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/36.-delete-counter-button-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/36.-delete-counter-button-768x433.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/36.-delete-counter-button-1536x865.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/36.-delete-counter-button.webp 1916w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><div class="wp-block-group doc-tip"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><p><strong>Note</strong></p><p>Deleting a counter is permanent and cannot be undone.</p></div></div><p>By using these filter and management options, you can efficiently organize and monitor counters in your POS system.</p></div>',
