                127 => [
                    'id' => 128,
                    'doc_page_id' => 283,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>Creating customer profiles in <strong>Menumium</strong> helps you maintain records of your regular customers, including their contact details and addresses. This makes it easier to manage orders, reservations, and customer relationships.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-customer-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to Customer Setup</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>From the <strong>Dashboard</strong>, open the left-hand sidebar.</li><li>Under the <strong>User Management</strong> section, click on <strong>Customer Setup</strong>.</li><li>This will take you to the <strong>Customer List</strong> page.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="574" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-1024x574.webp" alt="Navigate To Customer Setup" class="wp-image-10870" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-1024x574.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-1536x861.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-2-add-a-new-customer" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Add a New Customer</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>On the <strong>Customer List</strong> page, click the green <strong>+ Add New Customer</strong> button in the top-right corner.</li><li>A pop-up window will appear for adding customer details.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-customer-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Add New Customer" class="wp-image-10872" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-customer-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-customer-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-customer-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-customer-0a-1536x862.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/add-new-customer-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-enter-customer-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Enter Customer Information</h2><p>Fill in the customer’s details in the form:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Name</strong> – Enter the full name of the customer.</li><li><strong>Phone</strong> – Provide the customer’s phone number.</li><li><strong>Email</strong> – Enter the customer’s email address.</li><li><strong>Customer Image</strong> – Upload an image by clicking <strong>Browse</strong> or drag and drop a file (formats supported: JPG, PNG, JPEG, WEBP).</li><li><strong>Address</strong> – To add an address, click <strong>+ Add Address</strong> and fill in the fields.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="581" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-customer-information-1024x581.webp" alt="Enter Customer Information" class="wp-image-10867" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-customer-information-1024x581.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-customer-information-300x170.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-customer-information-768x435.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-customer-information-1536x871.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/enter-customer-information.webp 1903w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-4-save-the-profile" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Save the Profile</h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After entering all the details, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom of the window.</li><li>A confirmation message will appear.</li><li>The new customer profile will now be listed in the <strong>Customer List</strong>.</li></ul></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                ],
                128 => [
                    'id' => 129,
                    'doc_page_id' => 284,
                    'user_id' => 1,
                    'content_json' => null,
                    'content_html' => '<div class="wpd6-article-content"><p>This guide walks you through the process of updating a customer’s information in the Menumium dashboard. Use this feature to correct or modify a customer’s <strong>name, phone number, email, or profile image</strong>.</p><h2 id="step-1-navigate-to-user-management" class="wp-block-heading">Step 1: Navigate to User Management</h2><p>From the Menumium dashboard, go to the left-hand sidebar and click on <strong>User Management</strong> to expand the menu.</p><h2 id="step-2-select-customer-setup" class="wp-block-heading">Step 2: Select Customer Setup</h2><p>Within the expanded menu, click on <strong>Customer Setup</strong>. This will open the <strong>Customer List</strong> page, showing all registered customers.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="574" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-1024x574.webp" alt="Navigate To Customer Setup" class="wp-image-10870" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-1024x574.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-300x168.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a-1536x861.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/navigate-to-customer-setup-0a.webp 1915w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-3-find-the-customer-to-update" class="wp-block-heading">Step 3: Find the Customer to Update</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>On the Customer List page, locate the customer you want to update.</li><li>Use the <strong>Search bar</strong> at the top of the page to quickly find them by name, phone number, or email.</li></ol><h2 id="step-4-open-the-edit-customer-details-window" class="wp-block-heading">Step 4: Open the Edit Customer Details Window</h2><ol class="wp-block-list"><li>In the <strong>Action</strong> column of the customer’s row, click on the <strong>three-dot icon (â®)</strong>.</li><li>From the dropdown menu, select <strong>Edit Customer</strong>.</li><li>A pop-up window titled <strong>Edit Customer</strong> will appear.</li></ol><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-and-edit-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Search &amp; Edit" class="wp-image-10875" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-and-edit-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-and-edit-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-and-edit-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-and-edit-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/search-and-edit-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-5-update-the-information" class="wp-block-heading">Step 5: Update the Information</h2><p>In the <strong>Edit Customer</strong> window, you can update the following details:</p><ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Name</strong> – Update or correct the customer’s full name.</li><li><strong>Phone</strong> – Edit the customer’s contact number.</li><li><strong>Email</strong> – Update their email address.</li><li><strong>Image</strong> – Upload or replace the customer’s profile image.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-customer-info-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Update Customer Info" class="wp-image-10877" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-customer-info-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-customer-info-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-customer-info-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-customer-info-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-customer-info-0a.webp 1918w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><h2 id="step-6-save-the-changes" class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Step 6: Save the Changes</strong></h2><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>After making the necessary updates, click the <strong>Update</strong> button at the bottom of the pop-up window.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-10879" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><ul class="wp-block-list"><li>A confirmation message will appear, indicating that the customer’s details were successfully updated.</li></ul><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="575" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirmation-message-customer-update-0a-1024x575.webp" alt="Confirmation Message Customer Update" class="wp-image-10928" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirmation-message-customer-update-0a-1024x575.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirmation-message-customer-update-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirmation-message-customer-update-0a-768x431.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirmation-message-customer-update-0a-1536x863.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/confirmation-message-customer-update-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure><p>Your customer’s information is now up to date in the system.</p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-1024x576.webp" alt="Update &amp; Save" class="wp-image-10879" srcset="https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-1024x576.webp 1024w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-300x169.webp 300w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-768x432.webp 768w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://menumium.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/update-and-save-0a.webp 1919w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure></div>',
                    'change_summary' => 'Cloned from version 1.0',
                    'is_snapshot' => true,
                    'created_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
                    'updated_at' => '2026-02-09T09:58:19.000000Z',
